Dialogue: 0,0:00:03.78,0:00:05.10,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Got it\N知道了
Dialogue: 0,0:00:09.24,0:00:12.00,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,The poor have lost their safety net.\N穷人失去了社会保障网。
Dialogue: 0,0:00:21.44,0:00:25.76,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Well, isn't it just that this next part doesn't let Brother NO name say a few words, right?\N嗯，接下来这一部分是不是根本不让无名氏兄弟说几句话呢？
Dialogue: 0,0:00:25.76,0:00:28.34,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,NO name bro is working on this in China, right?\N有个不知名的兄弟在中国做这个项目，对吧？
Dialogue: 0,0:00:28.34,0:00:29.84,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Brother, say a few words.\N兄弟，说几句话吧。
Dialogue: 0,0:00:29.84,0:00:31.04,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Is it today?\N是今天吗？
Dialogue: 0,0:00:31.04,0:00:31.92,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Hey hello hey\N嘿，你好，嘿
Dialogue: 0,0:00:31.92,0:00:33.22,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Hey, uh, can you hear me?\N嘿，呃，你能听到我说话吗？
Dialogue: 0,0:00:33.22,0:00:33.92,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Can you hear me?\N你能听到我吗？
Dialogue: 0,0:00:34.92,0:00:35.12,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Hey\N嘿
Dialogue: 0,0:00:35.12,0:00:36.51,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Hello hello uh\N你好你好呃
Dialogue: 0,0:00:36.51,0:00:37.55,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,It's like this\N就是这样
Dialogue: 0,0:00:37.55,0:00:38.91,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,I'm just here for fun\N我只是来玩的
Dialogue: 0,0:00:38.91,0:00:41.86,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Because my family has been doing this in China for over 30 years\N因为我家在中国从事这项工作已经超过 30 年了。
Dialogue: 0,0:00:41.86,0:00:45.42,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Actually, I was working under a very big boss doing that\N事实上，我当时是在一个大老板手下做这件事的。
Dialogue: 0,0:00:45.42,0:00:47.36,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Anyway, I'm doing this now too.\N总之，我现在也在做这件事。
Dialogue: 0,0:00:47.36,0:00:49.66,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,in a sense\N从某种意义上说
Dialogue: 0,0:00:49.66,0:00:53.30,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Because maybe everyone doesn't know about this insurance thing, uh\N因为可能并非每个人都了解保险这回事，呃……
Dialogue: 0,0:00:53.30,0:00:54.98,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Children can inherit their parents' business.\N子女可以继承父母的企业。
Dialogue: 0,0:00:54.98,0:00:55.98,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,So in this regard\N所以在这方面
Dialogue: 0,0:00:55.98,0:00:57.90,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,It should probably be considered one of the relatively large ones in the country.\N它应该算是全国规模相对较大的城市之一。
Dialogue: 0,0:00:57.90,0:01:00.28,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,So I have a bit more experience in this area.\N我在这个领域有一些经验。
Dialogue: 0,0:01:00.28,0:01:03.85,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,A couple of days ago I saw the news about ACA's all sorts of crazy price hikes\N几天前我看到新闻，说 ACA（平价医疗法案）导致各种疯狂的价格上涨。
Dialogue: 0,0:01:03.85,0:01:10.00,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,it just occurred to me that I should find someone to understand it better\N我突然想到，我应该找个人来更好地理解这件事。
Dialogue: 0,0:01:10.00,0:01:11.29,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Talk about it, talk about it\N谈谈它，谈谈它
Dialogue: 0,0:01:11.29,0:01:16.83,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Well, I think that the vast majority of Chinese people,\N嗯，我认为绝大多数中国人，
Dialogue: 0,0:01:16.83,0:01:17.73,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Including myself\N包括我自己
Dialogue: 0,0:01:17.73,0:01:19.26,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Although I have also studied in the United States\N虽然我也曾在美国留学
Dialogue: 0,0:01:19.26,0:01:20.70,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,have also been enrolled in health insurance in the U.S.\N他们也已在美国参加了医疗保险。
Dialogue: 0,0:01:20.70,0:01:21.39,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,even got reimbursed\N甚至还获得了报销
Dialogue: 0,0:01:21.39,0:01:23.79,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,I always catch colds and run a fever occasionally.\N我总是容易感冒，偶尔还会发烧。
Dialogue: 0,0:01:23.79,0:01:26.40,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,However, many people may uh\N然而，许多人可能会……
Dialogue: 0,0:01:26.40,0:01:29.23,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,uh, an important issue that many are unaware of\N呃，一个很多人都不了解的重要问题。
Dialogue: 0,0:01:29.23,0:01:30.59,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Because everyone is still young\N因为大家都还年轻。
Dialogue: 0,0:01:30.59,0:01:36.23,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,The United States does not have universal healthcare for people before normal retirement.\N美国没有为正常退休前的人们提供全民医疗保健。
Dialogue: 0,0:01:36.23,0:01:39.50,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,there is no universal healthcare coverage\N目前尚无全民医疗保健覆盖。
Dialogue: 0,0:01:39.50,0:01:42.05,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,There is no safety net for this.\N这件事没有任何保障措施。
Dialogue: 0,0:01:42.05,0:01:45.23,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,There has never been so-called non-existent\N从来没有所谓的“不存在的”。
Dialogue: 0,0:01:45.23,0:01:48.08,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,It does not have a universal healthcare system either.\N它也没有全民医疗保健体系。
Dialogue: 0,0:01:48.08,0:01:48.72,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,What does this mean\N这是什么意思？
Dialogue: 0,0:01:48.72,0:01:50.48,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,In China, this is called a primary-level hospital\N在中国，这被称为基层医院
Dialogue: 0,0:01:50.48,0:01:51.12,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,secondary hospital\N二级医院
Dialogue: 0,0:01:51.12,0:01:54.12,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,People usually go to third-tier hospitals, specifically third-tier grade A hospitals, right?\N人们通常会去三级医院，特别是三级甲等医院，对吧？
Dialogue: 0,0:01:54.12,0:01:55.12,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,What is a community hospital?\N什么是社区医院？
Dialogue: 0,0:01:55.12,0:01:57.34,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,not even secondary-level hospitals are covered\N连二级医院都不在承保范围内。
Dialogue: 0,0:01:57.34,0:01:59.09,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,None of them have been built\N它们都还没有建成。
Dialogue: 0,0:01:59.09,0:02:02.59,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,You can understand it as because the hospitals built in China\N你可以理解为，因为中国建造的医院……
Dialogue: 0,0:02:02.59,0:02:04.43,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,The land is all provided by the state, right?\N土地都是国家提供的，对吧？
Dialogue: 0,0:02:04.43,0:02:07.40,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Look at those hospitals in the city center being redeveloped\N看看市中心那些正在重建的医院吧。
Dialogue: 0,0:02:07.40,0:02:09.84,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,building skyscrapers regardless of floor area ratios\N不顾容积率建造摩天大楼
Dialogue: 0,0:02:09.84,0:02:11.80,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,as long as the hospital wants to build it\N只要医院愿意建就行
Dialogue: 0,0:02:11.80,0:02:13.47,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,everything has to make way for the hospital\N一切都必须为医院让路。
Dialogue: 0,0:02:13.47,0:02:15.12,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,The hospital can just build a new building whenever it wants.\N医院可以随时新建大楼。
Dialogue: 0,0:02:15.12,0:02:17.53,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Natural lighting doesn't matter at all\N自然光线完全不重要。
Dialogue: 0,0:02:17.53,0:02:21.75,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Well, in the evil United States\N嗯，在邪恶的美国
Dialogue: 0,0:02:21.75,0:02:23.69,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,You and I might think it can be understood this way\N你我或许都认为可以这样理解
Dialogue: 0,0:02:23.69,0:02:29.15,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Basically, all hospitals nationwide are like Putian-style medical institutions, right?\N基本上，全国所有医院都像莆田式的医疗机构，对吧？
Dialogue: 0,0:02:29.15,0:02:31.31,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,just with a longer history\N只是历史更长一些而已。
Dialogue: 0,0:02:31.31,0:02:33.71,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,newer Putian-style hospitals\N莆田式新医院
Dialogue: 0,0:02:33.71,0:02:35.72,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Hehe, right?\N呵呵，对吧？
Dialogue: 0,0:02:35.72,0:02:39.19,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,If your goal is profit, then openly state that your purpose is profit-seeking.\N如果你的目标是盈利，那就公开声明你的目的是追求利润。
Dialogue: 0,0:02:39.19,0:02:42.62,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,I didn't take my medicine today, feeling super cute.\N我今天没吃药，感觉自己超级可爱。
Dialogue: 0,0:02:42.62,0:02:44.86,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Because back then it could have been a church or\N因为当时它可能是一座教堂，或者
Dialogue: 0,0:02:44.86,0:02:45.50,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,universities\N大学
Dialogue: 0,0:02:45.50,0:02:46.81,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,a very wealthy tycoon\N一位非常富有的商业巨头
Dialogue: 0,0:02:46.81,0:02:48.03,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,donate\N捐
Dialogue: 0,0:02:48.03,0:02:49.06,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,ah established a university\N啊，建立了一所大学
Dialogue: 0,0:02:49.06,0:02:50.00,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Such schools are average\N这类学校的平均水平
Dialogue: 0,0:02:50.00,0:02:52.66,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,But that kind of hospital usually has better business.\N但这类医院通常生意更好。
Dialogue: 0,0:02:52.66,0:02:54.47,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,but it was mentioned that\N但有人提到……
Dialogue: 0,0:02:54.47,0:02:57.22,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,I previously added those three questions for ALEX\N我之前给亚历克斯提了那三个问题。
Dialogue: 0,0:02:57.22,0:02:57.87,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,the first one\N第一个
Dialogue: 0,0:02:57.87,0:03:03.09,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,That is to say, his entire medical system is also different.\N也就是说，他的整个医疗体系也与以往不同。
Dialogue: 0,0:03:03.09,0:03:05.68,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Even if he studied at this hospital back then\N即使他当时在这家医院学习过
Dialogue: 0,0:03:05.68,0:03:08.87,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,This is Brother Nalan's medical reimbursement form in China\N这是纳兰哥在中国的医疗报销单。
Dialogue: 0,0:03:08.87,0:03:10.03,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,has its own foundation\N有其自身的基础
Dialogue: 0,0:03:10.03,0:03:13.08,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,can be less dependent on this market income\N可以减少对市场收入的依赖
Dialogue: 0,0:03:13.08,0:03:16.80,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Each of his doctors costs hundreds of thousands\N他的每个医生都要花费数十万美元。
Dialogue: 0,0:03:16.80,0:03:17.56,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,several hundred thousand\N几十万
Dialogue: 0,0:03:17.56,0:03:19.89,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,millions of people trained\N数百万人接受过培训
Dialogue: 0,0:03:20.02,0:03:23.03,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,That's not all, not just that\N但这还不是全部，不仅仅是这些。
Dialogue: 0,0:03:23.03,0:03:24.09,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Let me explain\N让我解释一下
Dialogue: 0,0:03:24.09,0:03:26.99,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Let me tell you about the medical training in the United States,\N让我来给你介绍一下美国的医学培训情况。
Dialogue: 0,0:03:26.99,0:03:28.76,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,medical student training cycle\N医学生培训周期
Dialogue: 0,0:03:28.76,0:03:30.72,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,A person enters university at the age of 18\N一个人 18 岁进入大学。
Dialogue: 0,0:03:31.72,0:03:34.65,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,He can become a doctor at around the age of 30.\N他大约 30 岁就可以成为一名医生。
Dialogue: 0,0:03:34.84,0:03:35.88,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,12 years\N12 年
Dialogue: 0,0:03:35.88,0:03:42.75,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,The average annual cost ranges from approximately $180,000 to $320,000.\N平均每年的费用约为 18 万美元至 32 万美元。
Dialogue: 0,0:03:42.75,0:03:45.75,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,that's about 180,000 to 420,000\N那大约是 18 万到 42 万。
Dialogue: 0,0:03:45.75,0:03:47.44,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,180,000 to 420,000 US dollars\N18 万至 42 万美元
Dialogue: 0,0:03:47.44,0:03:53.77,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Brothers, the average annual training cost year after year\N兄弟们，每年的平均训练费用都在增加。
Dialogue: 0,0:03:54.00,0:03:56.65,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,180,000 to 420,000\N18 万至 42 万
Dialogue: 0,0:03:56.65,0:03:58.53,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Not only is the training system so expensive\N培训系统不仅价格昂贵。
Dialogue: 0,0:03:58.53,0:04:00.99,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,It's all about certification and licensing\N一切都与认证和执照有关。
Dialogue: 0,0:04:00.99,0:04:01.66,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,you become a doctor\N你成为了一名医生
Dialogue: 0,0:04:01.66,0:04:04.78,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Being a doctor is, in a sense, something that has become rare to see in China.\N从某种意义上说，在中国，当医生已经变得越来越少见了。
Dialogue: 0,0:04:04.78,0:04:06.81,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,is a very ancient guild system\N这是一个非常古老的行会制度。
Dialogue: 0,0:04:06.81,0:04:08.46,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,I'm just adjusting the beauty filter\N我正在调整美颜滤镜
Dialogue: 0,0:04:08.46,0:04:09.65,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,or this person\N或者这个人
Dialogue: 0,0:04:09.65,0:04:12.87,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,to maintain the high income of the group already within it\N为了维持集团内部已有的高收入
Dialogue: 0,0:04:13.38,0:04:14.75,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Yes\N是的
Dialogue: 0,0:04:15.21,0:04:17.06,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,So there are many doctors in China\N所以中国有很多医生。
Dialogue: 0,0:04:17.06,0:04:18.69,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,I know I know many doctors\N我知道我认识很多医生
Dialogue: 0,0:04:18.69,0:04:19.89,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,because we have dealings with them\N因为我们与他们有业务往来。
Dialogue: 0,0:04:19.89,0:04:22.68,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Some of them would say they envy the American doctor system\N他们中有些人会说，他们羡慕美国的医疗体系。
Dialogue: 0,0:04:22.68,0:04:24.23,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,how much money he can make\N他能赚多少钱
Dialogue: 0,0:04:24.23,0:04:25.91,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,I know exactly what to say\N我知道该说什么。
Dialogue: 0,0:04:25.91,0:04:27.31,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Thank goodness it's anonymous now\N幸好现在是匿名的了。
Dialogue: 0,0:04:27.31,0:04:28.50,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,No one knows my name\N没有人知道我的名字
Dialogue: 0,0:04:28.50,0:04:30.23,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,You're talking bullshit\N你在胡说八道。
Dialogue: 0,0:04:30.23,0:04:32.52,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,This this if you were at XiDa\N如果你在西大，这就是你
Dialogue: 0,0:04:32.52,0:04:33.88,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,You wouldn't even have a chance to become a doctor\N你甚至连成为医生的机会都没有。
Dialogue: 0,0:04:33.88,0:04:35.02,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Why is it you\N为什么是你？
Dialogue: 0,0:04:35.02,0:04:37.27,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,there's no you\N没有你
Dialogue: 0,0:04:37.27,0:04:38.81,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Your family has no money.\N你家没钱。
Dialogue: 0,0:04:38.81,0:04:41.15,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Second, you're not from a medical family\N第二，你并非出身于医学世家。
Dialogue: 0,0:04:41.15,0:04:42.29,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,no such connections\N没有此类联系
Dialogue: 0,0:04:42.29,0:04:45.56,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Why on earth should it be your turn to become a doctor\N为什么偏偏轮到你当医生了？
Dialogue: 0,0:04:46.80,0:04:48.56,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Who provides your standardized residency training?\N谁提供你们的标准化住院医师培训？
Dialogue: 0,0:04:55.72,0:04:58.19,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Let me tell you something\N让我告诉你一些事
Dialogue: 0,0:04:58.19,0:05:00.39,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,So, let me tell you something\N所以，让我告诉你一些事
Dialogue: 0,0:05:00.39,0:05:02.68,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,As for me,\N至于我，
Dialogue: 0,0:05:02.68,0:05:05.64,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,I was planning to study 4+4 back then, right?\N我当时是打算学习 4+4 的，对吧？
Dialogue: 0,0:05:05.64,0:05:07.90,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,I was planning to do the 4+4 program.\N我原本计划参加 4+4 项目。
Dialogue: 0,0:05:08.14,0:05:08.82,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,you know\N你知道
Dialogue: 0,0:05:08.82,0:05:10.88,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,That's why I was able to do the 4+4 program.\N这就是我能够参加 4+4 项目的原因。
Dialogue: 0,0:05:10.88,0:05:14.93,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Hey, I have, I have a recommendation letter\N嘿，我有，我有一封推荐信。
Dialogue: 0,0:05:14.93,0:05:16.52,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Hey bros\N嘿，兄弟们
Dialogue: 0,0:05:16.52,0:05:19.70,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,You know, I can only get into the program because I have this recommendation letter.\N你知道，我能进入这个项目全靠这封推荐信。
Dialogue: 0,0:05:19.70,0:05:21.16,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,You know what\N你知道吗
Dialogue: 0,0:05:21.36,0:05:23.28,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Someone said why am I so low\N有人问我为什么我这么低落
Dialogue: 0,0:05:23.28,0:05:26.07,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Liu Sun'er is lingering here\N刘桑儿在这里逗留了一段时间。
Dialogue: 0,0:05:26.07,0:05:29.36,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Brother, it's hanging right here\N兄弟，它就挂在这里。
Dialogue: 0,0:05:29.82,0:05:32.23,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Yeah, it's just that some of these medical professionals in the country\N是的，只是这个国家的一些医疗专业人员……
Dialogue: 0,0:05:32.23,0:05:34.11,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,He wants to learn this\N他想学习这个
Dialogue: 0,0:05:38.98,0:05:41.95,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,This has now been essentially eliminated by the 4+4 policy, right?\N现在“4+4”政策基本上已经消除了这个问题，对吧？
Dialogue: 0,0:05:41.95,0:05:43.39,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,I'm not sure about the latest situation.\N我不确定最新情况如何。
Dialogue: 0,0:05:43.39,0:05:48.50,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Yeah, it was, then what? It got taken down.\N是啊，然后呢？就被撤下来了。
Dialogue: 0,0:05:48.50,0:05:51.77,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Then what about the second part? Their insurance regulation is also different.\N那么第二部分呢？他们的保险监管也不同。
Dialogue: 0,0:05:51.77,0:05:54.19,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,The Chinese insurance regulatory,\N中国保险监管机构
Dialogue: 0,0:05:54.19,0:05:55.79,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Of course, many people have complaints about it\N当然，很多人对此都有抱怨。
Dialogue: 0,0:05:55.79,0:05:58.82,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,But generally speaking, they claim to boast\N但总的来说，他们声称自己很自豪
Dialogue: 0,0:05:58.82,0:06:02.10,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,It claims to be for the healthcare of the people, right?\N它声称是为了人民的医疗保健，对吧？
Dialogue: 0,0:06:02.10,0:06:03.48,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,the common people and insurance companies\N普通民众和保险公司
Dialogue: 0,0:06:03.48,0:06:07.52,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,if any of you have actually filed a complaint with the insurance regulatory authority\N如果你们当中有人已经向保险监管机构提出过投诉的话
Dialogue: 0,0:06:07.52,0:06:11.81,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,you'll know that in most cases, the insurance regulatory authority sides with the ordinary people\N你会知道，在大多数情况下，保险监管机构会站在普通民众一边。
Dialogue: 0,0:06:11.81,0:06:13.55,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,because the two of you can argue, right\N因为你们两个可以争论，对吧。
Dialogue: 0,0:06:13.55,0:06:15.73,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Unless, uh, there's a situation in China\N除非，呃，中国那边发生了什么事。
Dialogue: 0,0:06:15.73,0:06:19.67,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Yes yes yes, it's quite fair on both sides\N是的，是的，这对双方都很公平。
Dialogue: 0,0:06:19.67,0:06:20.79,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,what illnesses you had before\N你以前得过哪些疾病？
Dialogue: 0,0:06:20.79,0:06:21.35,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,indeed not mentioned\N确实没有提及
Dialogue: 0,0:06:21.35,0:06:22.50,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,This is also recorded in the medical history, right?\N这一点也记录在病历里，对吧？
Dialogue: 0,0:06:22.50,0:06:25.35,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,This black-and-white written evidence cannot be forged.\N这种白纸黑字的书面证据是伪造不了的。
Dialogue: 0,0:06:25.35,0:06:27.02,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,without this thing\N如果没有这东西
Dialogue: 0,0:06:27.02,0:06:28.75,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,the vast majority of unclear cases\N绝大多数不明案件
Dialogue: 0,0:06:28.75,0:06:30.67,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Healthcare is all about supporting ordinary people\N医疗保健的本质在于支持普通民众。
Dialogue: 0,0:06:30.67,0:06:34.14,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Because ordinary folks are not medical professionals, right?\N因为普通人不是医疗专业人员，对吧？
Dialogue: 0,0:06:34.14,0:06:36.12,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,You come up with so many convoluted clauses\N你写出了这么多晦涩难懂的条款。
Dialogue: 0,0:06:36.12,0:06:37.26,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,I don't understand, right?\N我不明白，对吧？
Dialogue: 0,0:06:37.26,0:06:38.64,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Anyway, the money was already paid at that time\N总之，当时钱已经付清了。
Dialogue: 0,0:06:38.64,0:06:40.79,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,You can't possibly give me nothing at all, right?\N你不可能什么都不给我，对吧？
Dialogue: 0,0:06:40.79,0:06:46.37,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,This is a medical system based on the American and Western model\N这是一个基于美国和西方模式的医疗体系
Dialogue: 0,0:06:48.07,0:06:49.48,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,What does it emphasize?\N它强调的是什么？
Dialogue: 0,0:06:49.48,0:06:50.94,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,it emphasizes fairness\N它强调公平性
Dialogue: 0,0:06:50.94,0:06:52.37,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,so-called fairness\N所谓的公平
Dialogue: 0,0:06:52.37,0:06:53.12,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,He is the elephant\N他是那头大象
Dialogue: 0,0:06:53.12,0:06:53.95,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,You are an ant\N你是一只蚂蚁
Dialogue: 0,0:06:53.95,0:06:54.94,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,We want fairness\N我们想要公平。
Dialogue: 0,0:06:54.94,0:06:56.01,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Everyone, you step on it\N大家，都踩上去！
Dialogue: 0,0:06:56.01,0:06:56.54,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,it steps on you\N它踩在你身上
Dialogue: 0,0:06:56.54,0:06:57.22,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Let's try the preview\N我们来试试预览功能。
Dialogue: 0,0:06:57.22,0:06:58.75,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Both parties hire their own lawyers\N双方各自聘请律师。
Dialogue: 0,0:06:58.75,0:07:00.62,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,cross-examination, right\N交叉询问，右
Dialogue: 0,0:07:00.62,0:07:02.67,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,You want to prove that over 30 years ago\N你想证明这一点是在 30 多年前。
Dialogue: 0,0:07:02.67,0:07:06.81,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,that unreported case of pneumonia back then and your current knee\N那起未上报的肺炎病例，以及你现在的膝盖问题
Dialogue: 0,0:07:06.81,0:07:08.66,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Is this so-called meniscus damage related?\N这种所谓的半月板损伤与此有关吗？
Dialogue: 0,0:07:08.66,0:07:10.22,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Let's hear what the insurance company has to say\N让我们听听保险公司怎么说。
Dialogue: 0,0:07:10.22,0:07:11.82,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,He believes there is a connection\N他认为两者之间存在联系。
Dialogue: 0,0:07:11.82,0:07:12.38,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,provide evidence\N提供证据
Dialogue: 0,0:07:12.38,0:07:12.82,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,123\N｛1001｝
Dialogue: 0,0:07:12.82,0:07:13.62,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,his legal team\N他的法律团队
Dialogue: 0,0:07:13.62,0:07:14.88,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,his lifelong team said\N他毕生的团队说
Dialogue: 0,0:07:14.88,0:07:16.90,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Please, average citizen A, come here\N请普通市民 A 过来一下
Dialogue: 0,0:07:16.90,0:07:19.39,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Give an example\N举例说明
Dialogue: 0,0:07:20.98,0:07:24.00,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,This is just fucking terrifying, okay?\N这简直太可怕了，好吗？
Dialogue: 0,0:07:24.00,0:07:26.43,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Oh because everyone is just like, oh dear\N哦，因为每个人都像这样，哦，亲爱的
Dialogue: 0,0:07:26.43,0:07:28.31,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Because I often encounter this kind of problem\N因为我经常遇到这类问题
Dialogue: 0,0:07:28.31,0:07:30.56,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Someone said, um,\N有人说，嗯，
Dialogue: 0,0:07:30.56,0:07:33.75,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,What's the difference between getting insurance in mainland China and abroad?\N在中国大陆购买保险和在国外购买保险有什么区别？
Dialogue: 0,0:07:33.75,0:07:34.82,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Actually, I don't even need to\N实际上，我甚至不需要
Dialogue: 0,0:07:34.82,0:07:36.75,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,I said just try applying for insurance yourself and you'll see\N我说，你就自己去申请保险试试就知道了。
Dialogue: 0,0:07:36.75,0:07:37.79,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,insuring in China\N在中国投保
Dialogue: 0,0:07:37.79,0:07:39.85,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,for example, asking you 33 or 35 questions\N例如，问你 33 个或 35 个问题
Dialogue: 0,0:07:39.85,0:07:40.73,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,it's over\N结束了
Dialogue: 0,0:07:40.73,0:07:42.93,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Although each question may appear extremely complex\N尽管每个问题看起来都极其复杂。
Dialogue: 0,0:07:42.93,0:07:44.12,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Once you finish asking, it's over\N问完之后，就结束了。
Dialogue: 0,0:07:44.12,0:07:45.20,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,won't ask you another question\N不会再问你其他问题了
Dialogue: 0,0:07:46.32,0:07:49.23,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,in some delightful places\N在一些令人愉悦的地方
Dialogue: 0,0:07:49.23,0:07:51.55,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,There's always a line underneath that says\N下面总会有一行字说：
Dialogue: 0,0:07:51.55,0:07:56.27,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Is there anything else you think should be mentioned but hasn't been said?\N您认为还有什么应该提及但尚未提及的吗？
Dialogue: 0,0:07:56.68,0:08:00.13,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Well, this thing is legally unobjectionable.\N嗯，这件事在法律上没有任何问题。
Dialogue: 0,0:08:00.13,0:08:02.99,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,but hehe\N呵呵
Dialogue: 0,0:08:02.99,0:08:04.97,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,This is really going to cause a dispute.\N这肯定会引发一场争端。
Dialogue: 0,0:08:04.97,0:08:06.87,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,This is an open-ended contract\N这是一份开放式合同。
Dialogue: 0,0:08:06.87,0:08:07.99,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,comrade\N同志
Dialogue: 0,0:08:08.31,0:08:10.79,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,And then when the time comes, the banking and insurance regulator says they're here to ensure fairness.\N然后，时机成熟时，银行和保险监管机构会说，他们来这里是为了确保公平。
Dialogue: 0,0:08:10.79,0:08:12.21,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Was there such a clause back then?\N当时有这样的条款吗？
Dialogue: 0,0:08:12.21,0:08:13.53,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Did you answer honestly?\N你如实回答了吗？
Dialogue: 0,0:08:13.53,0:08:16.74,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Did you answer every question that needed to be answered?\N你是否回答了所有需要回答的问题？
Dialogue: 0,0:08:16.74,0:08:19.60,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Oh my god, right\N我的天啊，没错
Dialogue: 0,0:08:19.60,0:08:23.85,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,And then, and then, and then, and also, uh,\N然后，然后，然后，还有，呃，
Dialogue: 0,0:08:23.85,0:08:25.79,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Because, precisely because, uh\N因为，正是因为，呃
Dialogue: 0,0:08:25.79,0:08:27.76,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Let's talk about the underlying logic of business.\N我们来谈谈商业的根本逻辑。
Dialogue: 0,0:08:27.76,0:08:30.64,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,because domestically, to take a step back,\N因为在国内，退一步讲，
Dialogue: 0,0:08:30.64,0:08:32.49,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,there's universal healthcare coverage, right\N有全民医保，对吧？
Dialogue: 0,0:08:32.49,0:08:35.30,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,so the so-called uh\N所以所谓的呃
Dialogue: 0,0:08:35.30,0:08:37.78,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Well, let me first make a direct comparison with the US.\N好吧，首先让我直接与美国进行比较。
Dialogue: 0,0:08:37.78,0:08:39.37,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,so-called medical insurance\N所谓的医疗保险
Dialogue: 0,0:08:39.37,0:08:43.71,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,it primarily serves middle-class and above individuals\N它主要服务于中产阶级及以上人群。
Dialogue: 0,0:08:43.71,0:08:44.78,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Right, right?\N对吧？
Dialogue: 0,0:08:44.78,0:08:47.42,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,But generally speaking, there are also those in China that cost a few thousand yuan\N但总的来说，在中国也有一些售价几千元人民币的。
Dialogue: 0,0:08:47.42,0:08:49.04,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,the medical insurance that costs tens of thousands a year\N每年花费数万美元的医疗保险
Dialogue: 0,0:08:49.04,0:08:51.88,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,That mainly serves the middle class and above\N这主要服务于中产阶级及以上人群。
Dialogue: 0,0:08:51.88,0:08:54.54,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,add icing on the cake to build reputation\N锦上添花，提升声誉
Dialogue: 0,0:08:54.54,0:08:57.44,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,This circle isn't that big either.\N这个圆圈也不算大。
Dialogue: 0,0:08:57.44,0:08:58.48,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Word spreads fast.\N消息传播得很快。
Dialogue: 0,0:08:58.48,0:08:59.91,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,if you don't do it well, right\N如果你做得不好，对吧？
Dialogue: 0,0:08:59.91,0:09:02.60,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Who are you going to sell to next year, right?\N你明年打算把产品卖给谁？
Dialogue: 0,0:09:02.60,0:09:05.00,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,So in the lovely United States\N所以，在美丽的美国
Dialogue: 0,0:09:06.32,0:09:07.25,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,You have to buy it whether you want to or not\N不管你愿不愿意，你都得买。
Dialogue: 0,0:09:07.25,0:09:08.25,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,You have to buy it whether you want to or not\N不管你愿不愿意，你都得买。
Dialogue: 0,0:09:08.25,0:09:10.00,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,You either buy it or buy me\N你要么买它，要么买我。
Dialogue: 0,0:09:10.00,0:09:12.46,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,And then here comes the uh\N然后，呃……
Dialogue: 0,0:09:12.46,0:09:13.79,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,often seen in American TV shows\N经常出现在美国电视节目中
Dialogue: 0,0:09:13.79,0:09:15.25,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,everyone will see something like in-network\N每个人都会看到类似网络内的内容。
Dialogue: 0,0:09:15.25,0:09:18.12,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,the term in-network out-of-network in China\N中国术语中的“院内/院外”
Dialogue: 0,0:09:18.12,0:09:21.29,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,People would ask, is this a secondary hospital or not, right?\N人们会问，这是一家二级医院吗？
Dialogue: 0,0:09:21.29,0:09:22.23,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,secondary and above hospitals\N二级及以上医院
Dialogue: 0,0:09:22.23,0:09:23.47,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,you are indeed a hospital, right\N你们确实是家医院，对吧？
Dialogue: 0,0:09:23.47,0:09:25.01,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,If it's a private hospital, right\N如果是私立医院，对吧？
Dialogue: 0,0:09:25.01,0:09:26.41,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,The state also has a dedicated registry for this.\N该州还为此设立了专门的登记处。
Dialogue: 0,0:09:26.41,0:09:28.17,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,as long as it can be found in the national registry\N只要能在国家登记册中找到就行
Dialogue: 0,0:09:28.17,0:09:30.08,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,that thing of yours can just be called a hospital\N你那玩意儿简直就可以叫医院。
Dialogue: 0,0:09:30.08,0:09:31.50,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,The US doesn't have this\N美国没有这个
Dialogue: 0,0:09:31.50,0:09:34.01,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Then who is going to certify that this thing is called a hospital\N那么，谁来认证这东西能被称为医院呢？
Dialogue: 0,0:09:34.01,0:09:34.94,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,or what is it called\N或者它叫什么来着
Dialogue: 0,0:09:34.94,0:09:37.32,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Oh, the insurance company, right\N哦，是保险公司，对吧？
Dialogue: 0,0:09:37.32,0:09:41.63,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,So the evaluation system ends up being controlled by the insurance companies.\N因此，评估体系最终被保险公司所控制。
Dialogue: 0,0:09:41.63,0:09:43.17,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Just think about the horror in this\N想想这有多恐怖
Dialogue: 0,0:09:43.17,0:09:44.46,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,The insurance company pays for it.\N保险公司会支付这笔费用。
Dialogue: 0,0:09:44.46,0:09:47.47,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Ah, this thing in the insurance company\N啊，保险公司里的这事儿
Dialogue: 0,0:09:47.47,0:09:50.26,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,he considers it to be something called, uh, good\N他认为这是一种叫做……好的东西。
Dialogue: 0,0:09:50.26,0:09:51.49,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,called a proper hospital\N被称为正规医院
Dialogue: 0,0:09:51.49,0:09:52.78,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,in the eyes of the insurance company\N在保险公司眼中
Dialogue: 0,0:09:52.78,0:09:53.90,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,it is not considered a legitimate hospital\N它不被视为正规医院。
Dialogue: 0,0:09:53.90,0:09:55.61,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,This is only the first derivative\N这只是导数的一阶导数。
Dialogue: 0,0:09:55.61,0:09:56.35,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,because he has no other choice\N因为他别无选择
Dialogue: 0,0:09:56.35,0:09:57.42,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,the state doesn't intervene\N国家不进行干预
Dialogue: 0,0:09:57.42,0:09:58.60,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,then the enterprises have to take care of it\N那么企业就必须负责处理这件事。
Dialogue: 0,0:09:58.60,0:09:59.75,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,You think it seems reasonable\N你觉得这似乎合情合理
Dialogue: 0,0:09:59.75,0:10:01.13,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,What is the second derivative?\N二阶导数是什么？
Dialogue: 0,0:10:01.13,0:10:05.39,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,The second derivative is like, oh they need to cooperate with each other.\N二阶导数就像是，哦，他们需要互相合作。
Dialogue: 0,0:10:05.39,0:10:07.70,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,I recognize you as a legitimate hospital\N我认可贵院是一家正规医院。
Dialogue: 0,0:10:07.70,0:10:10.15,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,I even guide and retain patients\N我甚至还能指导和留住病人。
Dialogue: 0,0:10:10.15,0:10:10.87,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,No, I call it customer\N不，我称之为客户
Dialogue: 0,0:10:10.87,0:10:12.38,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,patient referral\N患者转诊
Dialogue: 0,0:10:12.38,0:10:14.87,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,It's about the patients you get, right?\N关键在于你接诊的病人，对吧？
Dialogue: 0,0:10:14.87,0:10:16.50,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Then you have to give me benefits\N那么你就得给我好处。
Dialogue: 0,0:10:16.50,0:10:17.79,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,You've got to give me a discount, right?\N你得给我打折，对吧？
Dialogue: 0,0:10:17.79,0:10:21.50,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,What's more, you even have to consult me first about the treatment plan, right?\N而且，你甚至还要先跟我商量治疗方案，对吧？
Dialogue: 0,0:10:21.50,0:10:24.35,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,This patient was referred by me\N这位病人是我转诊的。
Dialogue: 0,0:10:24.35,0:10:25.73,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,This illness of his, right?\N是他的这种病，对吧？
Dialogue: 0,0:10:25.73,0:10:28.12,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Should it be radiotherapy and chemotherapy or conservative treatment\N应该采用放疗联合化疗还是保守治疗？
Dialogue: 0,0:10:28.12,0:10:29.45,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,You ask me first\N你先问我
Dialogue: 0,0:10:29.45,0:10:30.64,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,after consulting me\N咨询过我之后
Dialogue: 0,0:10:30.64,0:10:32.75,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,You should tell the patient how much is appropriate\N你应该告诉患者合适的剂量是多少。
Dialogue: 0,0:10:32.75,0:10:34.00,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,We both reach an agreement\N我们双方达成一致
Dialogue: 0,0:10:34.00,0:10:35.05,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Then you go and tell others\N然后你再去告诉其他人。
Dialogue: 0,0:10:35.05,0:10:37.44,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,That is, that is, this is it\N也就是说，也就是说，就是这样。
Dialogue: 0,0:10:37.44,0:10:39.64,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Is this the content from that short video just now?\N这是刚才那个短视频的内容吗？
Dialogue: 0,0:10:39.64,0:10:40.38,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,right\N正确的
Dialogue: 0,0:10:40.38,0:10:44.25,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,You must start with the cheapest treatment option\N你必须从最便宜的治疗方案开始。
Dialogue: 0,0:10:44.86,0:10:45.96,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,If you don't do this\N如果你不这样做
Dialogue: 0,0:10:45.96,0:10:48.65,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,I simply won't cover the patient\N我绝不会为病人承担费用。
Dialogue: 0,0:10:48.65,0:10:50.58,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,not even aware\N甚至都没意识到
Dialogue: 0,0:10:51.19,0:10:53.07,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Domestic healthcare also has its own issues.\N国内医疗保健也存在自身问题。
Dialogue: 0,0:10:53.07,0:10:54.35,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,In the past, everyone in China complained a lot\N过去，中国人总是抱怨个不停。
Dialogue: 0,0:10:54.35,0:10:56.50,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,saying 'oh, I'll give you one that insurance covers\N他说：“哦，我会给你一个保险涵盖的。”
Dialogue: 0,0:10:56.50,0:10:57.83,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,give you one that medical insurance won't cover\N给你一份医疗保险不承保的保单
Dialogue: 0,0:10:57.83,0:10:58.66,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Hey, you have two options\N嘿，你有两个选择
Dialogue: 0,0:10:58.66,0:11:00.25,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,You choose the more expensive option, doctor, sigh\N医生，你选择了更贵的方案，唉。
Dialogue: 0,0:11:00.25,0:11:01.96,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,These issues do exist\N这些问题确实存在。
Dialogue: 0,0:11:01.96,0:11:04.41,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Of course, the government has now taken very strong measures to address these issues\N当然，政府现在已经采取了非常强有力的措施来解决这些问题。
Dialogue: 0,0:11:04.41,0:11:05.17,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Right, hmm\N对，嗯。
Dialogue: 0,0:11:05.17,0:11:07.10,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Everyone may have some experience with this\N每个人都可能对此有所了解。
Dialogue: 0,0:11:07.10,0:11:09.10,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,You may also know that sometimes it might be overcorrected\N您可能也知道，有时可能会矫枉过正。
Dialogue: 0,0:11:09.10,0:11:10.08,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,this this again\N这又来了
Dialogue: 0,0:11:10.08,0:11:12.87,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,But in lovely America\N但在美丽的美国
Dialogue: 0,0:11:12.87,0:11:15.57,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,This is the norm\N这是常态
Dialogue: 0,0:11:15.57,0:11:17.11,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,And then there will be\N然后就会有
Dialogue: 0,0:11:17.11,0:11:19.50,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,After the first and second points, we then come to the third point\N在第一点和第二点之后，我们接下来讨论第三点。
Dialogue: 0,0:11:19.50,0:11:21.62,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,So why would I come across these real-life cases\N那么，我为什么会遇到这些真实案例呢？
Dialogue: 0,0:11:21.62,0:11:24.52,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Hey everyone, well, for ordinary people, right\N大家好，嗯，对于普通人来说，对吧？
Dialogue: 0,0:11:24.52,0:11:25.80,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,The premium you pay is also cheap\N你支付的保费也很便宜。
Dialogue: 0,0:11:25.80,0:11:26.89,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,the gemstone you choose is also of poor quality\N你选择的宝石质量也很差。
Dialogue: 0,0:11:26.89,0:11:28.53,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,the plan you chose is also poor, right\N你选择的方案也很糟糕，对吧？
Dialogue: 0,0:11:28.53,0:11:30.58,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,you you you all these you originally you were excluded\N你们，你们，你们所有人，最初都被排除在外了。
Dialogue: 0,0:11:30.58,0:11:33.65,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Being excluded or whatever, it all comes back to the same source—you understand that, right? The rich, well, it's not for nothing that America is said to be a paradise for the wealthy.\N被排斥也好，其他什么也罢，归根结底都是同一个问题——你明白吧？富人嘛，美国被称为富人的天堂并非浪得虚名。
Dialogue: 0,0:11:33.65,0:11:34.05,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,You understand\N你明白
Dialogue: 0,0:11:34.05,0:11:35.15,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,those wealthy people, right\N那些有钱人，对吧？
Dialogue: 0,0:11:35.15,0:11:36.86,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Isn't it said that America is a paradise for the rich?\N不是有人说美国是富人的天堂吗？
Dialogue: 0,0:11:36.86,0:11:37.75,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,You have money\N你有钱
Dialogue: 0,0:11:37.75,0:11:39.10,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,You can find the best doctors\N你可以找到最好的医生
Dialogue: 0,0:11:39.10,0:11:40.10,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,you purchase the best\N你购买的是最好的
Dialogue: 0,0:11:40.10,0:11:42.91,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,this this this this this this insurance policy right\N这份保险单对
Dialogue: 0,0:11:42.91,0:11:44.72,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,You should be fine, right?\N你应该没事的，对吧？
Dialogue: 0,0:11:44.72,0:11:46.20,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,there is still a problem\N问题依然存在。
Dialogue: 0,0:11:46.20,0:11:47.15,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Why\N为什么
Dialogue: 0,0:11:47.15,0:11:50.05,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Because when it reaches that stage\N因为当它达到那个阶段时
Dialogue: 0,0:11:50.05,0:11:52.00,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,In other words, it comes back to the same point\N换句话说，问题又回到了原点。
Dialogue: 0,0:11:52.00,0:11:53.39,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,because there is no universal healthcare safety net\N因为没有全民医疗保健安全网。
Dialogue: 0,0:11:53.39,0:11:56.80,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,no one has your back\N没人会为你撑腰
Dialogue: 0,0:11:56.80,0:11:58.35,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,There is really no such insurance policy\N实际上并不存在这样的保险政策。
Dialogue: 0,0:11:58.35,0:11:59.69,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,they renewed it for you for 30 years\N他们为你续签了 30 年。
Dialogue: 0,0:11:59.69,0:12:00.28,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,50 years\N50 年
Dialogue: 0,0:12:00.28,0:12:01.40,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,You might already be 70 years old now\N你现在可能已经 70 岁了。
Dialogue: 0,0:12:01.40,0:12:03.11,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,However, the past few years have been very good.\N然而，过去几年都非常好。
Dialogue: 0,0:12:03.11,0:12:05.92,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Today, this company is truly shocking.\N今天，这家公司真是令人震惊。
Dialogue: 0,0:12:05.92,0:12:11.12,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,He said, 'Ugh, well, I'm not going to cover these things.'\N他说：“唉，这些事我就不报道了。”
Dialogue: 0,0:12:11.12,0:12:13.51,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,or if you previously had diabetes\N或者如果您之前患有糖尿病
Dialogue: 0,0:12:13.51,0:12:14.39,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,I also give it to you every year\N我每年也都会把它送给你。
Dialogue: 0,0:12:14.39,0:12:16.12,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,continue your coverage without excluding diabetes\N继续享有您的保险保障，糖尿病保险不予排除。
Dialogue: 0,0:12:16.12,0:12:18.36,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,But starting this year, our company's policy has changed\N但从今年开始，我们公司的政策发生了变化。
Dialogue: 0,0:12:18.36,0:12:19.48,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,You really had diabetes before\N你以前真的得过糖尿病。
Dialogue: 0,0:12:19.48,0:12:21.26,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,I really can't renew it for you now.\N我现在真的无法帮你续费了。
Dialogue: 0,0:12:21.26,0:12:22.71,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,or this condition must be excluded\N或者必须排除这种情况。
Dialogue: 0,0:12:22.71,0:12:24.11,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,which medications to exclude for you\N哪些药物你应该停用
Dialogue: 0,0:12:24.11,0:12:27.95,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,He can really change it anytime.\N他随时都可以改变主意。
Dialogue: 0,0:12:27.95,0:12:29.75,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Of course, such problems also exist domestically in China\N当然，中国国内也存在类似的问题。
Dialogue: 0,0:12:29.75,0:12:31.52,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,is supervised by the CBIRC\N受银保监会监管
Dialogue: 0,0:12:31.52,0:12:33.16,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,there's banking and insurance regulation in place\N银行业和保险业已有相关监管规定。
Dialogue: 0,0:12:33.16,0:12:36.32,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Then everyone might notice that there are some things\N然后大家可能会注意到有些事情
Dialogue: 0,0:12:36.32,0:12:36.79,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,some products\N部分产品
Dialogue: 0,0:12:36.79,0:12:39.08,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,maybe this company and that company have similar names in them\N也许这家公司和那家公司名称很相似。
Dialogue: 0,0:12:39.08,0:12:40.27,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,have the same thing\N有同样的东西
Dialogue: 0,0:12:40.27,0:12:43.13,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,they are all called so-and-so or such-and-such\N它们都叫某某某
Dialogue: 0,0:12:43.13,0:12:45.77,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,these are the ones with the same name\N这些是同名的。
Dialogue: 0,0:12:45.77,0:12:49.22,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,These are regulations that only the China Banking and Insurance Regulatory Commission would have at this level.\N这些是只有中国银行保险监督管理委员会才会制定的此类规定。
Dialogue: 0,0:12:49.22,0:12:50.66,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,you want to call it this name\N你想叫它这个名字
Dialogue: 0,0:12:50.66,0:12:52.26,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,you must\N你必须
Dialogue: 0,0:12:52.26,0:12:53.59,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Actually, this is somewhat similar to ACA\N实际上，这与《平价医疗法案》(ACA) 有些类似。
Dialogue: 0,0:12:53.59,0:12:55.02,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,as long as you're called ACA\N只要你叫 ACA
Dialogue: 0,0:12:55.02,0:12:56.45,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,You must cover pre-existing conditions\N您必须涵盖既有疾病。
Dialogue: 0,0:12:56.45,0:12:58.94,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,You have to admit it, right?\N你不得不承认这一点，对吧？
Dialogue: 0,0:12:58.94,0:13:00.55,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,In fact, appropriate regulation is beneficial\N事实上，适当的监管是有益的。
Dialogue: 0,0:13:00.55,0:13:04.84,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,It is beneficial for both clients to maintain a balance between the two sides.\N保持双方利益平衡对双方客户都有好处。
Dialogue: 0,0:13:04.84,0:13:06.79,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,But anyway in the U.S.\N但无论如何，在美国
Dialogue: 0,0:13:06.79,0:13:07.32,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,for this and that\N为了这个和那个
Dialogue: 0,0:13:07.32,0:13:10.34,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,including the transgender issues you mentioned about Obama\N包括你提到的奥巴马的跨性别问题。
Dialogue: 0,0:13:10.34,0:13:11.98,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,he inserted quite a few personal agendas\N他掺杂了不少个人目的。
Dialogue: 0,0:13:11.98,0:13:13.77,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,resulting in that not being the majority\N因此，这种情况并非占多数。
Dialogue: 0,0:13:13.77,0:13:17.62,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,To be precise, he takes it as his own\N确切地说，他把它当作自己的。
Dialogue: 0,0:13:18.50,0:13:21.78,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Everyone, think about it, you all, and then brothers\N大家，好好想想，还有兄弟们。
Dialogue: 0,0:13:21.78,0:13:23.00,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Just imagine\N试想一下
Dialogue: 0,0:13:23.00,0:13:26.79,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,In regions with half of the U.S. population, totaling 150 million people\N在美国人口占一半的地区，总人口达 1.5 亿人
Dialogue: 0,0:13:26.79,0:13:32.62,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,alter all textbooks to promote transgenderism\N修改所有教科书以宣扬跨性别主义
Dialogue: 0,0:13:32.62,0:13:34.98,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,All teachers promote gender transition\N所有教师都提倡性别转换
Dialogue: 0,0:13:34.98,0:13:37.87,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,from the kindergarten stage\N从幼儿园阶段
Dialogue: 0,0:13:39.74,0:13:42.21,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Alright, let's put these aside for now.\N好了，我们先把这些放在一边。
Dialogue: 0,0:13:42.21,0:13:44.47,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,So, let's say if I were really rich, right\N假设我真的很有钱，对吧？
Dialogue: 0,0:13:44.47,0:13:45.97,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,I don't even need insurance\N我甚至不需要保险。
Dialogue: 0,0:13:45.97,0:13:47.40,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,I can pay everything in cash\N我可以用现金支付所有款项。
Dialogue: 0,0:13:47.40,0:13:49.39,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,I have 20 billion, right\N我有 200 亿，对吧？
Dialogue: 0,0:13:49.39,0:13:52.67,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Can't I just pay in cash, right?\N我可以直接付现金吗？
Dialogue: 0,0:13:52.67,0:13:54.50,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,There will still be problems\N问题依然存在。
Dialogue: 0,0:13:54.50,0:13:56.17,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,What's the issue?\N问题是什么？
Dialogue: 0,0:13:56.17,0:13:57.77,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Sigh, here we go again.\N唉，又来了。
Dialogue: 0,0:13:57.77,0:14:00.17,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,The American medical system is plagued by a slew of obstacles\N美国医疗体系面临诸多障碍。
Dialogue: 0,0:14:00.17,0:14:01.46,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,including referrals and a bunch of other obstacles\N包括转诊和其他一系列障碍
Dialogue: 0,0:14:01.46,0:14:01.89,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,and then\N进而
Dialogue: 0,0:14:01.89,0:14:02.41,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,As we all know\N我们都知道
Dialogue: 0,0:14:02.41,0:14:05.35,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,American doctors see far fewer patients per year compared to their Chinese counterparts.\N与中国同行相比，美国医生每年接诊的病人数量要少得多。
Dialogue: 0,0:14:05.35,0:14:07.66,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Well, let me, let me, let me give you the numbers.\N好，让我，让我，让我把数字告诉你。
Dialogue: 0,0:14:07.66,0:14:12.28,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,On average, an American doctor sees about 30 patients per year.\N美国医生平均每年接诊约 30 位病人。
Dialogue: 0,0:14:12.28,0:14:14.52,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,around 50 people\N大约 50 人
Dialogue: 0,0:14:14.92,0:14:18.88,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Is the special department currently performing surgeries or is it just about performing surgeries?\N该专科部门目前是否开展手术，还是仅仅负责开展手术？
Dialogue: 0,0:14:18.88,0:14:23.66,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,On average, they see about 4.4 patients per week.\N他们平均每周接诊约 4.4 位患者。
Dialogue: 0,0:14:23.66,0:14:27.69,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,That would mean performing about 50 surgeries a year.\N这意味着每年要进行大约 50 例手术。
Dialogue: 0,0:14:27.69,0:14:32.79,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,it's about twenty to thirty surgeries a week, which averages to 4.4 per week\N每周大约有 20 到 30 台手术，平均每周 4.4 台。
Dialogue: 0,0:14:32.79,0:14:36.75,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,that's seeing fewer than five patients a week\N也就是说，每周接诊的患者少于五位。
Dialogue: 0,0:14:37.13,0:14:40.05,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,This then leads to a very critical issue\N这就引出了一个非常关键的问题。
Dialogue: 0,0:14:40.05,0:14:42.86,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Actually, his skill level is\N实际上，他的技能水平是
Dialogue: 0,0:14:42.86,0:14:45.25,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Although he may have the world's most innovative drugs\N尽管他可能拥有世界上最具创新性的药物。
Dialogue: 0,0:14:45.25,0:14:47.96,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Because anyway, the standards for his experiments are lax\N总之，他的实验标准很宽松。
Dialogue: 0,0:14:48.65,0:14:54.16,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,But his actual practical skills are poor and not up to par.\N但他实际操作技能很差，达不到标准。
Dialogue: 0,0:14:54.16,0:14:58.02,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Yes, very much so, I just can't say who.\N是的，确实如此，但我不能透露是谁。
Dialogue: 0,0:14:58.74,0:15:03.70,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,I have, I have... oh, how should I put it... oh, how should I say this...\N我有，我有……哦，我该怎么说呢……哦，我该怎么说呢……
Dialogue: 0,0:15:03.70,0:15:06.39,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,I want to see how to say it, oh, this needs to protect someone's privacy\N我想看看该怎么说，哦，这需要保护某人的隐私
Dialogue: 0,0:15:06.39,0:15:08.82,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,It's just a very small matter\N这只是件小事。
Dialogue: 0,0:15:09.62,0:15:11.98,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Let me say it for everyone, old Rockefeller\N让我替大家说一句，老洛克菲勒
Dialogue: 0,0:15:11.98,0:15:16.40,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Young Rockefeller underwent surgery in Beijing\N年轻的洛克菲勒在北京接受了手术
Dialogue: 0,0:15:16.40,0:15:17.52,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,This also exists\N这也存在。
Dialogue: 0,0:15:17.52,0:15:20.71,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Then, well, I just wanted to say it's a very minor surgery\N然后，嗯，我只想说这只是个小手术。
Dialogue: 0,0:15:20.71,0:15:23.87,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,maybe involving, like,\N可能涉及，比如，
Dialogue: 0,0:15:23.87,0:15:24.63,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,for men who are interested in this\N对于对此感兴趣的男士来说
Dialogue: 0,0:15:24.63,0:15:28.20,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,a minor surgery involving the urethra\N涉及尿道的小手术
Dialogue: 0,0:15:28.20,0:15:30.26,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,performed when the person was in their thirties or forties\N手术时该人正值三十多岁或四十多岁。
Dialogue: 0,0:15:30.26,0:15:33.12,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,And then, at the very end during the puncture,\N然后，在穿刺的最后阶段，
Dialogue: 0,0:15:33.12,0:15:36.26,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,accidentally punctured one of the urethras\N不小心刺破了其中一根尿道
Dialogue: 0,0:15:36.26,0:15:38.99,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,So, as you know, people have two kidneys, right?\N如你所知，人有两个肾脏，对吧？
Dialogue: 0,0:15:38.99,0:15:39.78,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,right\N正确的
Dialogue: 0,0:15:39.78,0:15:41.12,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,one of them is not working well\N其中一个不太好用。
Dialogue: 0,0:15:41.12,0:15:43.31,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,You actually don't know for sure right away, right?\N你其实不能马上确定，对吧？
Dialogue: 0,0:15:43.31,0:15:46.51,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Sigh, and then this Taoist priest stood up, hey\N唉，然后这位道士站了起来，嘿。
Dialogue: 0,0:15:46.51,0:15:48.17,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,It's growing\N它正在增长
Dialogue: 0,0:15:48.17,0:15:49.23,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,It cannot be cleared\N无法清除
Dialogue: 0,0:15:49.23,0:15:52.36,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,one kidney was already rendered useless\N其中一个肾脏已经失去功能。
Dialogue: 0,0:15:53.12,0:15:56.12,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Then you don't discover this problem until you're in your 50s\N直到你 50 多岁，才会发现这个问题。
Dialogue: 0,0:15:58.01,0:15:59.89,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,and then you can never replace this gem again\N这样一来，你就再也无法取代这颗宝石了。
Dialogue: 0,0:15:59.89,0:16:01.74,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Because these are all major issues\N因为这些都是重大问题。
Dialogue: 0,0:16:01.74,0:16:03.65,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,It's already good enough that they originally renewed your insurance.\N他们当初同意续保就已经很好了。
Dialogue: 0,0:16:03.65,0:16:06.22,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Then in another couple of years when you're in your 60s\N然后再过几年，等你六十多岁的时候……
Dialogue: 0,0:16:06.22,0:16:07.74,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,and then they say\N然后他们说
Dialogue: 0,0:16:07.74,0:16:10.03,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,it's definitely because you only have one kidney\N那肯定是因为你只有一个肾脏。
Dialogue: 0,0:16:10.03,0:16:11.58,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,it's more prone to problems, right?\N它更容易出问题，对吧？
Dialogue: 0,0:16:11.58,0:16:12.98,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,such as taking some medications\N例如服用某些药物
Dialogue: 0,0:16:12.98,0:16:14.91,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Previously, this medication was all reimbursable.\N以前，这种药物的费用全部可以报销。
Dialogue: 0,0:16:14.91,0:16:16.72,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Then one day after turning 65, maybe\N然后，在 65 岁生日后的某一天，也许
Dialogue: 0,0:16:16.72,0:16:18.27,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,He said, 'Oh, this policy has changed'\N他说：“哦，这项政策变了。”
Dialogue: 0,0:16:18.27,0:16:20.67,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,This medication is no longer covered by your insurance.\N您的保险已不再涵盖此药物。
Dialogue: 0,0:16:20.67,0:16:23.72,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Yes, everything is fine when you're young\N是的，年轻的时候一切都很好。
Dialogue: 0,0:16:23.72,0:16:25.10,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,as you get older\N随着年龄增长
Dialogue: 0,0:16:25.10,0:16:26.74,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,screwed\N螺丝
Dialogue: 0,0:16:27.41,0:16:32.29,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Then this issue is something that even if you have billions\N那么，即使你拥有数十亿，这个问题也依然存在。
Dialogue: 0,0:16:32.29,0:16:37.73,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,It's something you can't even save no matter what.\N这是无论如何都无法挽救的东西。
Dialogue: 0,0:16:38.58,0:16:41.50,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,It's like, oh my, I don't even know how to put it\N真是，哎呀，我都不知道该怎么形容了。
Dialogue: 0,0:16:41.50,0:16:43.91,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,This matter is all real.\N这件事都是真的。
Dialogue: 0,0:16:43.91,0:16:44.74,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,I really\N我真的
Dialogue: 0,0:16:44.74,0:16:47.25,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,I swear to heaven these things really happened\N我向上帝发誓，这些事真的发生过。
Dialogue: 0,0:16:47.25,0:16:52.12,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,So the result is that for Chinese people, it's still manageable in the end\N所以结果是，对中国人来说，最终还是可以应对的。
Dialogue: 0,0:16:52.12,0:16:53.73,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Actually, they're all first-generation Chinese immigrants\N实际上，他们都是第一代中国移民。
Dialogue: 0,0:16:53.73,0:16:55.00,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,were all born and raised in China\N我们都在中国出生长大。
Dialogue: 0,0:16:55.00,0:16:58.44,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,still know what the situation is like back home, uh\N仍然知道家乡的情况，嗯。
Dialogue: 0,0:16:58.44,0:17:02.44,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,I've seen that basically, once they reach a certain age, they all have to come back.\N我发现，基本上，一旦他们到了某个年龄，他们都必须回来。
Dialogue: 0,0:17:02.44,0:17:03.74,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,They all have to come back\N他们都必须回来
Dialogue: 0,0:17:03.74,0:17:05.44,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,they all have to come back\N他们都得回来
Dialogue: 0,0:17:05.44,0:17:06.96,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,He definitely has to come back\N他肯定得回来。
Dialogue: 0,0:17:06.96,0:17:09.65,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,If this doesn't come back, you'll lose it, oh dear\N如果它找不回来，你就失去它了，哦，亲爱的
Dialogue: 0,0:17:09.65,0:17:11.82,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,I'm here with all this medical English and whatnot\N我带着这些医学英语之类的东西来了
Dialogue: 0,0:17:11.82,0:17:13.34,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,I won't say anymore\N我不会再说了。
Dialogue: 0,0:17:13.34,0:17:16.99,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Everyone in China who has ever sought or seen a specialist\N在中国，所有曾经寻求或看过专科医生的人
Dialogue: 0,0:17:16.99,0:17:18.91,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,shouldn't instinctively raise an alarm\N不应该本能地发出警报
Dialogue: 0,0:17:18.91,0:17:22.04,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,All men are brothers and share the same heart; good things\N所有人都是兄弟，心意相通；美好的事物
Dialogue: 0,0:17:22.04,0:17:25.06,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Good doctors everywhere require the right connections.\N优秀的医生都需要良好的人脉关系。
Dialogue: 0,0:17:25.06,0:17:28.43,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Back in China, you might have managed through scalpers\N在中国，你或许可以通过黄牛党买到货。
Dialogue: 0,0:17:28.43,0:17:29.50,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,through insurance companies through\N通过保险公司
Dialogue: 0,0:17:29.50,0:17:32.41,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,how can you still manage to find one, right\N你怎么还能找到一个呢？对吧？
Dialogue: 0,0:17:32.41,0:17:34.71,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Such people are somewhat related to you\N这些人与你有些关联。
Dialogue: 0,0:17:34.71,0:17:36.57,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,not to mention distant relatives by marriage, just two degrees of separation\N更别提远房姻亲了，仅仅两层关系就足以让他们彼此疏远。
Dialogue: 0,0:17:36.57,0:17:39.21,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Remember who you are, like your sister-in-law's younger sister, right?\N记住你是谁，就像你嫂子的妹妹一样，对吧？
Dialogue: 0,0:17:39.21,0:17:42.70,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,This matter can still be said to carry a bit of human compassion.\N这件事仍然可以说蕴含着一丝人性的光辉。
Dialogue: 0,0:17:42.85,0:17:46.50,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,this in, in, in the lovely America\N这在，在，在美丽的美国
Dialogue: 0,0:17:46.50,0:17:47.42,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Who are you?\N你是谁？
Dialogue: 0,0:17:47.42,0:17:50.33,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,You, who are you? Some distant relative or in-law?\N你是谁？远房亲戚还是姻亲？
Dialogue: 0,0:17:50.33,0:17:52.77,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,You are a first-generation immigrant\N你是第一代移民。
Dialogue: 0,0:17:52.77,0:17:54.20,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,You're nothing\N你什么都不是
Dialogue: 0,0:17:54.20,0:17:56.90,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Especially since you're still Chinese\N尤其因为你还是中国人。
Dialogue: 0,0:18:01.22,0:18:03.90,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Oh, should I mute myself first?\N哦，我应该先把自己静音吗？
Dialogue: 0,0:18:04.66,0:18:08.22,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Well, just think about it, right?\N想想看，对吧？
Dialogue: 0,0:18:11.25,0:18:13.49,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Just imagine\N试想一下
Dialogue: 0,0:18:14.13,0:18:16.56,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Sometimes the first thing these people do when returning to China is go to the hospital.\N有时这些人回到中国后做的第一件事就是去医院。
Dialogue: 0,0:18:16.56,0:18:17.25,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Yeah\N是的
Dialogue: 0,0:18:17.25,0:18:19.45,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,What do you think?\N你怎么认为？
Dialogue: 0,0:18:20.53,0:18:22.74,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Sigh, then let's share another case.\N唉，那我们再分享另一个案例吧。
Dialogue: 0,0:18:22.74,0:18:25.53,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,You said, then, you kept mentioning this, it just occurred to me\N你当时说，你一直提到这件事，我突然想到了。
Dialogue: 0,0:18:25.53,0:18:29.90,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Uh, uh, uh, as everyone knows, the United States doesn't have universal healthcare.\N呃，呃，呃，众所周知，美国没有全民医疗保健。
Dialogue: 0,0:18:29.90,0:18:31.48,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,but Canada does have it\N但加拿大确实有。
Dialogue: 0,0:18:31.48,0:18:32.74,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Right?\N正确的？
Dialogue: 0,0:18:32.74,0:18:34.01,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Canada and the UK have it\N加拿大和英国都有它
Dialogue: 0,0:18:34.01,0:18:37.01,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Then, but actually, their system is quite similar\N但实际上，他们的系统非常相似。
Dialogue: 0,0:18:37.01,0:18:40.42,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,it will lead to the situation where the first consultation\N这将导致第一次磋商出现这种情况。
Dialogue: 0,0:18:40.42,0:18:42.33,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,You must first consult a family doctor\N您必须先咨询家庭医生。
Dialogue: 0,0:18:42.33,0:18:43.55,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,you cannot seek\N你不能寻求
Dialogue: 0,0:18:43.55,0:18:45.16,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,the so-called hospitals in China\N中国所谓的医院
Dialogue: 0,0:18:45.16,0:18:46.43,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,You can walk in anytime and get treated\N您可以随时前来就诊。
Dialogue: 0,0:18:46.43,0:18:48.19,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,It's not like this abroad.\N国外的情况并非如此。
Dialogue: 0,0:18:48.19,0:18:49.95,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,The so-called large hospitals abroad\N国外的所谓大型医院
Dialogue: 0,0:18:49.95,0:18:52.45,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,is like the headquarters office building of Sinopec\N就像中国石化的总部办公大楼一样。
Dialogue: 0,0:18:52.45,0:18:54.21,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,You enter and there's a beautiful receptionist lady\N你进去后，会看到一位漂亮的接待员女士。
Dialogue: 0,0:18:54.21,0:18:54.80,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,first ask you\N首先问你
Dialogue: 0,0:18:54.80,0:18:55.95,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Do you have an appointment?\N你有预约吗？
Dialogue: 0,0:18:55.95,0:18:56.84,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Who do you want to see\N你想见谁
Dialogue: 0,0:18:56.84,0:19:00.00,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,No, he's not here for our kind of walk-in registration.\N不，他不是来参加我们这种无需预约的登记活动的。
Dialogue: 0,0:19:00.00,0:19:02.67,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,He's not here to get a consultation number from us\N他来这里不是为了向我们索要咨询电话号码。
Dialogue: 0,0:19:03.19,0:19:06.17,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,This is the headquarters office building of Sinopec, right?\N这是中国石化总部办公楼，对吧？
Dialogue: 0,0:19:06.17,0:19:07.11,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,The receptionist asks you\N前台接待员问你
Dialogue: 0,0:19:07.11,0:19:08.55,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,very sweetly asks you\N非常温柔地问你
Dialogue: 0,0:19:08.55,0:19:09.61,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Do you have an appointment?\N你有预约吗？
Dialogue: 0,0:19:09.61,0:19:10.75,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Who would you like to see\N你想见谁
Dialogue: 0,0:19:10.75,0:19:12.74,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Then check and verify for you\N然后为您核实确认。
Dialogue: 0,0:19:12.74,0:19:14.55,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,If you don't have one, sorry\N如果你没有，抱歉。
Dialogue: 0,0:19:14.55,0:19:16.51,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,You won't be able to see\N你将无法看到
Dialogue: 0,0:19:16.51,0:19:18.15,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,never see the good\N从未看到好处
Dialogue: 0,0:19:18.15,0:19:20.86,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,So first, if there's any issue, please call your family doctor\N所以首先，如果有任何问题，请致电您的家庭医生。
Dialogue: 0,0:19:20.86,0:19:25.53,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,However, please be aware that discussing medical conditions over the phone is not allowed.\N但是请注意，不允许通过电话讨论医疗状况。
Dialogue: 0,0:19:25.53,0:19:26.70,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Right\N正确的
Dialogue: 0,0:19:26.70,0:19:31.65,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,You must, ah, also pay an additional 50% service fee, ah.\N您还必须支付额外的 50% 服务费。
Dialogue: 0,0:19:31.65,0:19:32.97,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Can you really escape it, huh?\N你真的能逃脱吗？
Dialogue: 0,0:19:32.97,0:19:33.43,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,negotiable\N可协商
Dialogue: 0,0:19:33.43,0:19:34.80,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,I don't know as much as you do\N我懂得不如你多。
Dialogue: 0,0:19:34.80,0:19:35.91,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,And then\N进而
Dialogue: 0,0:19:35.91,0:19:39.57,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Yesterday I said, 'Oh my, I have terrible stomach pain.'\N昨天我说：“哎呀，我肚子疼得厉害。”
Dialogue: 0,0:19:39.57,0:19:41.85,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Can I come next Tuesday?\N我下周二可以来吗？
Dialogue: 0,0:19:41.85,0:19:43.01,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Next Tuesday is not convenient\N下周二不方便
Dialogue: 0,0:19:43.01,0:19:46.86,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,How about Thursday morning? Okay, it's scheduled, right?\N周四上午怎么样？好的，已经安排好了，对吧？
Dialogue: 0,0:19:46.86,0:19:49.32,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Oh, you... Attorney Wang\N哦，你……王律师
Dialogue: 0,0:19:49.32,0:19:50.69,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Your problem, oh dear\N你的问题，哦，亲爱的。
Dialogue: 0,0:19:50.69,0:19:52.02,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,I don't know what to do either\N我也不知道该怎么办。
Dialogue: 0,0:19:52.02,0:19:55.84,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Alright then, I'll have you go get a few tests done first, okay?\N好的，那我先安排你去做几个检查，好吗？
Dialogue: 0,0:19:55.84,0:20:00.16,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,This is still not a hospital, just Lab A and Lab B.\N这里还不是医院，只是 A 实验室和 B 实验室。
Dialogue: 0,0:20:00.16,0:20:02.14,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Then after the tests were done\N测试结束后
Dialogue: 0,0:20:02.14,0:20:03.18,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,tests were conducted\N进行了测试。
Dialogue: 0,0:20:03.18,0:20:05.59,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Then, well, you just have to wait\N那么，你就只能等了。
Dialogue: 0,0:20:05.59,0:20:07.08,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,The quickest wait is a week\N最快等待时间为一周。
Dialogue: 0,0:20:07.08,0:20:09.10,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Some have to wait as long as three months.\N有些人甚至要等上三个月。
Dialogue: 0,0:20:09.10,0:20:12.56,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Someone said, let me tell you, in our lab...\N有人说，让我告诉你，在我们实验室里……
Dialogue: 0,0:20:12.56,0:20:13.94,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Our lab is relatively fast.\N我们的实验室速度相对较快。
Dialogue: 0,0:20:13.94,0:20:16.98,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Our lab only needs to wait a little over 70 days\N我们的实验室只需要等待 70 多天。
Dialogue: 0,0:20:16.98,0:20:18.51,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,more than two months\N两个多月
Dialogue: 0,0:20:18.51,0:20:19.72,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Our lab is relatively fast\N我们的实验室速度相对较快。
Dialogue: 0,0:20:22.22,0:20:23.07,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,And then\N进而
Dialogue: 0,0:20:23.07,0:20:24.81,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Then when the test results come out\N然后等检测结果出来的时候
Dialogue: 0,0:20:24.81,0:20:25.81,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,later, right\N稍后，对
Dialogue: 0,0:20:25.81,0:20:28.75,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,he can then match it with his referral letter\N然后他可以将其与他的推荐信进行比对。
Dialogue: 0,0:20:28.75,0:20:33.64,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,with these test results can you see the first specialist doctor\N凭这些检查结果，您可以去看第一位专科医生吗？
Dialogue: 0,0:20:33.64,0:20:37.75,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,For example, only if it's gynecology will they refer you to a specialist, okay\N例如，只有妇科疾病他们才会把你转诊给专科医生，好吗？
Dialogue: 0,0:20:37.75,0:20:39.61,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,You have to schedule another appointment with the specialist doctor\N您需要再次预约专科医生。
Dialogue: 0,0:20:39.61,0:20:40.22,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,and also wait in line\N还要排队
Dialogue: 0,0:20:40.22,0:20:41.58,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Right?\N正确的？
Dialogue: 0,0:20:41.58,0:20:43.41,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Okay, three months have passed, and then another three months went by\N好吧，三个月过去了，然后又过了三个月。
Dialogue: 0,0:20:43.41,0:20:45.34,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,You've got an appointment with the specialist, yay!\N你已经预约了专家，太棒了！
Dialogue: 0,0:20:45.34,0:20:47.78,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Oh, you're having this stomachache\N哦，你肚子疼啊
Dialogue: 0,0:20:47.78,0:20:49.63,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,You're already bleeding heavily\N你已经大量出血了。
Dialogue: 0,0:20:49.63,0:20:51.34,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Well, I think in your case\N嗯，我觉得就你的情况而言……
Dialogue: 0,0:20:51.34,0:20:54.14,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,You should get another CT scan of your abdomen.\N你应该再做一次腹部 CT 扫描。
Dialogue: 0,0:20:54.14,0:20:54.98,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Oh I see\N我懂了
Dialogue: 0,0:20:54.98,0:20:56.64,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,You go to that whatever hospital to get it done\N你去那家医院做这个手术
Dialogue: 0,0:20:56.64,0:20:58.46,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Hey, is your insurance accepted there? Ah\N嘿，你的保险在那里适用吗？啊
Dialogue: 0,0:20:58.46,0:21:00.09,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Your insurance doesn't cover that.\N你的保险不包括这个。
Dialogue: 0,0:21:00.09,0:21:00.94,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Let me check again like this\N让我再这样检查一遍。
Dialogue: 0,0:21:00.94,0:21:02.80,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Then go ahead and do that again, okay\N那就再做一遍，好吗？
Dialogue: 0,0:21:02.80,0:21:04.35,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,You still stayed for three months\N你还是待了三个月。
Dialogue: 0,0:21:04.35,0:21:05.75,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,finally came out and said oh\N最后他终于开口说了声“哦”。
Dialogue: 0,0:21:05.75,0:21:08.03,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,It seems like you might have uterine fibroids.\N你看起来好像患有子宫肌瘤。
Dialogue: 0,0:21:08.03,0:21:11.60,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Ah, but, but for this surgery we need to take another... uh\N啊，但是，但是这次手术我们需要再……呃
Dialogue: 0,0:21:11.60,0:21:12.32,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Well, let me see\N嗯，让我看看
Dialogue: 0,0:21:12.32,0:21:14.95,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Let me prescribe you some painkillers first.\N我先给你开点止痛药。
Dialogue: 0,0:21:14.95,0:21:16.20,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Because, you see, I have to prescribe\N因为，你看，我必须开处方。
Dialogue: 0,0:21:16.20,0:21:17.29,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,I can prescribe medication for you now.\N我现在可以给你开药了。
Dialogue: 0,0:21:17.29,0:21:19.05,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,I can prescribe you some birth control pills.\N我可以给你开一些避孕药。
Dialogue: 0,0:21:19.05,0:21:21.55,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,because birth control pills regulate estrogen levels\N因为避孕药可以调节雌激素水平
Dialogue: 0,0:21:21.55,0:21:24.07,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,can help alleviate this issue for you\N可以帮助你缓解这个问题。
Dialogue: 0,0:21:24.07,0:21:25.48,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Right?\N正确的？
Dialogue: 0,0:21:25.48,0:21:26.88,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,This is not even next week.\N这甚至还没到下周呢。
Dialogue: 0,0:21:26.88,0:21:28.09,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,real case\N真实案例
Dialogue: 0,0:21:28.09,0:21:29.27,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,very real very real\N非常真实 非常真实
Dialogue: 0,0:21:29.27,0:21:30.35,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,I couldn't help but laugh when I heard it\N听到这话，我忍不住笑了。
Dialogue: 0,0:21:30.35,0:21:31.27,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,so real\N太真实了
Dialogue: 0,0:21:31.27,0:21:32.85,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,very real and hard\N非常真实且艰难
Dialogue: 0,0:21:32.85,0:21:36.01,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Because what we have now is this kind of\N因为我们现在面临的是这种
Dialogue: 0,0:21:36.01,0:21:40.36,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,There's this trend of natural, eco-friendly, and health-conscious thinking nowadays, right?\N现在流行一种天然、环保、注重健康的理念，对吧？
Dialogue: 0,0:21:40.36,0:21:42.36,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Just like the common overprescription of antibiotics\N就像抗生素的滥用一样
Dialogue: 0,0:21:42.36,0:21:45.35,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,I can't prescribe too much of this painkiller for you.\N我不能给你开太多这种止痛药。
Dialogue: 0,0:21:45.35,0:21:47.64,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Right, um, I'll give you one pill a day to start with\N好的，嗯，一开始我每天给你开一片药。
Dialogue: 0,0:21:47.64,0:21:49.31,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,I'll give you half a blister pack first\N我先给你半包药片。
Dialogue: 0,0:21:49.31,0:21:50.85,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,I'll prescribe you seven pills\N我会给你开七粒药。
Dialogue: 0,0:21:50.85,0:21:51.53,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,contraceptive pill\N避孕药
Dialogue: 0,0:21:51.53,0:21:53.33,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Let me give you seven pills first.\N我先给你七粒药。
Dialogue: 0,0:21:53.33,0:21:54.51,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,You go back and take it first\N你回去先拿走它。
Dialogue: 0,0:21:54.51,0:21:56.24,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Those seven pills can only be taken for seven days.\N这七粒药丸只能服用七天。
Dialogue: 0,0:21:56.24,0:21:57.24,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,That's for the next visit\N那是下次来访的事了。
Dialogue: 0,0:21:57.24,0:21:57.75,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,I'm sorry\N对不起
Dialogue: 0,0:21:57.75,0:21:58.88,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,approximately one month later\N大约一个月后
Dialogue: 0,0:21:58.88,0:22:00.11,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,What about the other 21 days?\N剩下的 21 天呢？
Dialogue: 0,0:22:00.11,0:22:00.72,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Hey, this is not my concern\N嘿，这不关我的事。
Dialogue: 0,0:22:00.72,0:22:02.55,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,This is not within my jurisdiction\N这不属于我的管辖范围。
Dialogue: 0,0:22:04.25,0:22:05.13,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Hehe, right?\N呵呵，对吧？
Dialogue: 0,0:22:05.13,0:22:08.28,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Later on, this friend said someone was in critical condition\N后来，这位朋友说有人情况危急。
Dialogue: 0,0:22:08.28,0:22:11.03,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,just came back and called me saying, 'Ah,\N刚回来就给我打电话说：“啊，
Dialogue: 0,0:22:11.03,0:22:13.16,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Xiao Zhang and Xiao Li\NXiao Zhang and Xiao Li
Dialogue: 0,0:22:13.16,0:22:15.64,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,I'm really in excruciating pain\N我真的痛得要命
Dialogue: 0,0:22:15.64,0:22:17.80,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,You see, I've earned so much money in my lifetime, right?\N你看，我这辈子赚了很多钱，对吧？
Dialogue: 0,0:22:17.80,0:22:18.80,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,also in my fifties or sixties\N我也到了五六十岁。
Dialogue: 0,0:22:18.80,0:22:19.93,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,how come, right\N为什么呢，对吧？
Dialogue: 0,0:22:19.93,0:22:21.47,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,This matter is stuck right in my face\N这件事就摆在我眼前。
Dialogue: 0,0:22:21.47,0:22:22.60,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,I said, I said, you wait a second\N我说，我说，你等一下
Dialogue: 0,0:22:22.60,0:22:23.23,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Is this the matter?\N是这件事吗？
Dialogue: 0,0:22:23.23,0:22:24.50,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Hey, you give me the report\N嘿，你把报告给我。
Dialogue: 0,0:22:24.50,0:22:27.63,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Come on, let me help you find a... what's it called... Huashan...\N来吧，我帮你找找……叫什么来着……华山……
Dialogue: 0,0:22:27.63,0:22:30.25,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,a chief physician from a top-tier hospital somewhere, right\N某家顶级医院的首席医师，对吧？
Dialogue: 0,0:22:30.25,0:22:32.33,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Then deputy chief physician or chief physician might not be available\N那么，副主任医师或主任医师可能就无法到岗。
Dialogue: 0,0:22:32.33,0:22:33.33,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Let me find you an associate chief physician\N让我帮你找一位副主任医师
Dialogue: 0,0:22:33.33,0:22:34.68,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,At least a chief physician, right?\N至少应该有个主治医师吧？
Dialogue: 0,0:22:34.68,0:22:35.51,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Look, hey\N嘿，看！
Dialogue: 0,0:22:35.51,0:22:37.00,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Isn't it just a simple surgery?\N不就是个小手术吗？
Dialogue: 0,0:22:37.00,0:22:39.88,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,What date is your flight booked for? Ah, September 24th, right?\N你订的是哪一天的航班？啊，9 月 24 日，对吧？
Dialogue: 0,0:22:39.88,0:22:41.68,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Will you arrive in the morning or afternoon on September 24th?\N9 月 24 日，您是上午到达还是下午到达？
Dialogue: 0,0:22:41.68,0:22:43.21,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Arrive in the morning, hey\N早上到，好吗？
Dialogue: 0,0:22:43.21,0:22:44.43,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,The flight might be delayed\N航班可能会延误
Dialogue: 0,0:22:44.43,0:22:44.91,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Here's the deal\N事情是这样的。
Dialogue: 0,0:22:44.91,0:22:46.28,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,If you can arrive in the morning\N如果你能早上到达的话
Dialogue: 0,0:22:46.28,0:22:47.08,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,I'll schedule it for you in the afternoon\N我下午会帮你安排。
Dialogue: 0,0:22:47.08,0:22:47.84,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,if you arrive in the afternoon\N如果你下午到达。
Dialogue: 0,0:22:47.84,0:22:49.84,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,How about I do it for you the next morning?\N不如我明天早上帮你做吧？
Dialogue: 0,0:22:49.84,0:22:50.36,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Sure\N当然
Dialogue: 0,0:22:50.36,0:22:51.71,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Okay then, let's go ahead.\N好的，那我们继续。
Dialogue: 0,0:22:51.71,0:22:53.28,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,late-stage bro bro\N后期兄弟兄弟
Dialogue: 0,0:22:53.28,0:22:56.47,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,What you're saying has no impact at all.\N你说的话根本没有任何影响。
Dialogue: 0,0:22:56.47,0:22:58.08,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:58.08,0:23:00.35,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,went to the hospital after work\N下班后去了医院
Dialogue: 0,0:23:00.35,0:23:02.40,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,and then had the surgery done in the early morning\N然后，他在清晨接受了手术。
Dialogue: 0,0:23:02.40,0:23:04.00,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,discharged the next day\N第二天出院
Dialogue: 0,0:23:04.00,0:23:05.85,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,This can be done so incredibly at Li Si's place\N在李思家，这简直太不可思议了。
Dialogue: 0,0:23:05.85,0:23:09.65,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,This is simply incomparable, right?\N这简直无法相提并论，对吧？
Dialogue: 0,0:23:09.65,0:23:11.13,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,So so so\N所以就这样
Dialogue: 0,0:23:11.13,0:23:15.04,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,So this thing is truly, truly evil.\N所以这东西真是邪恶至极。
Dialogue: 0,0:23:15.04,0:23:18.45,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,I I I can only say that I, as I as\N我只能说，我，作为我，作为
Dialogue: 0,0:23:18.45,0:23:20.46,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Actually, my stance isn't very neutral either.\N实际上，我的立场也并非十分中立。
Dialogue: 0,0:23:20.46,0:23:22.70,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,I think from my perspective\N我认为从我的角度来看
Dialogue: 0,0:23:22.70,0:23:24.01,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,To be fair,\N公平地说，
Dialogue: 0,0:23:24.01,0:23:28.44,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,The current medical system in Serica is beneficial for the poorest individuals\N塞里卡目前的医疗体系对最贫困的人群有利。
Dialogue: 0,0:23:28.44,0:23:30.57,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,it is definitely good\N绝对不错
Dialogue: 0,0:23:30.57,0:23:33.83,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,especially in fiscally affluent provinces, right\N尤其是在财政富裕的省份，对吧？
Dialogue: 0,0:23:33.83,0:23:35.74,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,You're fully covered by the medical insurance\N您的医疗保险涵盖所有费用。
Dialogue: 0,0:23:35.74,0:23:38.34,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Don't even think about those fancy ideas\N别想那些花里胡哨的想法了。
Dialogue: 0,0:23:38.34,0:23:39.41,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,then what's better\N那么，哪种更好呢？
Dialogue: 0,0:23:39.41,0:23:40.80,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Anyway, you just pay less\N总之，你只需要少付钱。
Dialogue: 0,0:23:40.80,0:23:45.02,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Basically, you just need to pay a few hundred or thousand dollars, right?\N基本上，你只需要支付几百或几千美元，对吧？
Dialogue: 0,0:23:45.02,0:23:50.99,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,That can provide you with a fairly modern standard\N这可以为您提供一个相当现代的标准。
Dialogue: 0,0:23:50.99,0:23:53.60,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,That's not just modern-level\N这不仅仅是现代水平
Dialogue: 0,0:23:53.60,0:23:55.43,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Let me add another mind-blowing example\N让我再举一个令人震惊的例子。
Dialogue: 0,0:23:55.43,0:23:56.52,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,I'm not in Guangzhou\N我不在广州
Dialogue: 0,0:23:56.52,0:24:00.68,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Bro, you should know there are quite a few famous doctors in Guangzhou, right?\N兄弟，你应该知道广州有不少名医吧？
Dialogue: 0,0:24:00.68,0:24:01.88,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,especially Sun Yat-sen Hospital\N特别是孙中山医院
Dialogue: 0,0:24:01.88,0:24:03.32,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,right?\N正确的？
Dialogue: 0,0:24:03.32,0:24:05.23,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,If you want to make an appointment with a specialist\N如果您想预约专科医生
Dialogue: 0,0:24:05.23,0:24:06.91,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,maybe you can get an appointment with Zhong Nanshan\N或许你可以预约钟南山医生。
Dialogue: 0,0:24:08.06,0:24:09.92,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Nanshan for 1500 bucks, hmm\N南山要 1500 块，嗯……
Dialogue: 0,0:24:09.92,0:24:11.48,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,They are indeed practicing.\N他们确实在练习。
Dialogue: 0,0:24:11.48,0:24:12.40,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,You're the one seeing patients, right?\N你就是负责接诊病人的那位，对吧？
Dialogue: 0,0:24:12.40,0:24:13.42,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Can you get an appointment?\N可以预约吗？
Dialogue: 0,0:24:13.42,0:24:15.50,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Right, just relying on 3000, right?\N对，就靠 3000 这个数，对吧？
Dialogue: 0,0:24:15.50,0:24:16.59,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,And then\N进而
Dialogue: 0,0:24:16.59,0:24:18.24,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Now moving on to the second part\N现在进入第二部分
Dialogue: 0,0:24:18.24,0:24:19.35,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,in Seres\N在生物中
Dialogue: 0,0:24:19.35,0:24:22.16,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,If you're truly wealthy, right\N如果你真的很有钱，对吧？
Dialogue: 0,0:24:22.16,0:24:24.50,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Because the entire system was not built for you\N因为整个系统并非为你而建。
Dialogue: 0,0:24:24.50,0:24:27.06,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,It has already been established for the general public with this free land\N它已经通过这块免费土地向公众开放。
Dialogue: 0,0:24:27.06,0:24:27.99,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,free hospitals\N免费医院
Dialogue: 0,0:24:27.99,0:24:28.98,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,doctors trained at no cost\N免费培训的医生
Dialogue: 0,0:24:28.98,0:24:30.77,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,patients receiving free treatment, right\N接受免费治疗的患者，右
Dialogue: 0,0:24:30.77,0:24:32.50,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,has already been established for you\N已经为您安排好了
Dialogue: 0,0:24:32.50,0:24:36.57,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,So, even Zhong Nanshan only costs you 1,500 yuan\N所以，即使是中南山也只需要 1500 元人民币。
Dialogue: 0,0:24:36.57,0:24:36.98,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,3000 yuan\N3000 元
Dialogue: 0,0:24:36.98,0:24:40.67,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,even if you can dig up the person I helped\N即使你能找到我帮助过的那个人。
Dialogue: 0,0:24:40.67,0:24:42.88,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,This is already an irregular method.\N这本身就是一种不规范的做法。
Dialogue: 0,0:24:42.88,0:24:46.11,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,The most expensive registration fee I've ever heard of\N我听过最贵的注册费
Dialogue: 0,0:24:46.11,0:24:47.79,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,I also don't know what this person was thinking\N我也不知道这个人当时在想什么。
Dialogue: 0,0:24:47.79,0:24:51.09,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,He insisted on seeing a 94-year-old cancer specialist.\N他坚持要见一位 94 岁的癌症专家。
Dialogue: 0,0:24:51.09,0:24:51.57,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Alright\N好吧
Dialogue: 0,0:24:51.57,0:24:52.38,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,you you you want\N你，你想
Dialogue: 0,0:24:52.38,0:24:54.00,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Then I'll help you get it done, okay?\N那我来帮你完成这件事，好吗？
Dialogue: 0,0:24:54.00,0:24:56.22,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,I I came up with a solution uh\N我想出了一个解决办法。
Dialogue: 0,0:24:56.22,0:24:58.71,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,anyway, found someone and gave him roughly\N总之，我找到一个人，然后大致给了他一些钱。
Dialogue: 0,0:24:58.71,0:24:59.78,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Then can I say this?\N那我能这么说吗？
Dialogue: 0,0:24:59.78,0:25:00.86,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,I don't know if I gave 10,000 yuan\N我不知道我是否给了 1 万元人民币。
Dialogue: 0,0:25:00.86,0:25:02.55,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Right?\N正确的？
Dialogue: 0,0:25:02.55,0:25:03.77,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,he just got on the list\N他刚被列入名单。
Dialogue: 0,0:25:03.77,0:25:04.61,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,It sounds like\N听起来像
Dialogue: 0,0:25:04.61,0:25:04.98,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Of course\N当然
Dialogue: 0,0:25:04.98,0:25:09.35,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Perhaps many people in the Live think this is worth a lot of money, a lot of money?\N或许很多现场观众都认为这价值连城，非常非常高？
Dialogue: 0,0:25:09.35,0:25:12.73,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Think about it again compared to the US, huh, right\N再想想跟美国比起来，对吧？
Dialogue: 0,0:25:12.73,0:25:13.85,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Uh, old buddies\N呃，老朋友
Dialogue: 0,0:25:13.85,0:25:14.77,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,I want to ask\N我想问
Dialogue: 0,0:25:14.77,0:25:15.93,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,that is if in the West ah\N也就是说，如果在西方……
Dialogue: 0,0:25:15.93,0:25:18.81,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,if you encounter a problem that a department can't solve\N如果你遇到某个部门无法解决的问题
Dialogue: 0,0:25:18.81,0:25:21.98,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,that is, under the premise that you do not need to pay any additional fees\N也就是说，前提是您无需支付任何额外费用。
Dialogue: 0,0:25:21.98,0:25:24.14,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Would anyone do it without preconditions like we do here\N有人会像我们这样不设前提条件就去做吗？
Dialogue: 0,0:25:24.14,0:25:30.11,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,There is no such premise, if it doesn't exist then it doesn't exist\N不存在这样的前提，如果它不存在，那就是不存在。
Dialogue: 0,0:25:30.11,0:25:33.51,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,This hypothetical assumption is not an example, there is uh...\N这个假设并非示例，而是……
Dialogue: 0,0:25:33.51,0:25:37.88,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,At that time, uh, there was an accident\N当时，呃，发生了一起事故。
Dialogue: 0,0:25:37.88,0:25:41.50,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,was a fracture of a bone in the body\N是身体某处的骨折。
Dialogue: 0,0:25:41.50,0:25:44.57,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Brother Lan's medical reimbursement form in China\N兰哥在中国的医疗报销单
Dialogue: 0,0:25:44.57,0:25:46.15,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,it's the chest\N是箱子
Dialogue: 0,0:25:46.15,0:25:48.81,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,and then without any\N然后没有任何
Dialogue: 0,0:25:48.81,0:25:50.85,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,on the premise of paying other fees\N在支付其他费用的前提下
Dialogue: 0,0:25:50.85,0:25:53.22,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,directly triggered the alarm\N直接触发了警报
Dialogue: 0,0:25:53.22,0:25:54.98,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,the entire hospital was mobilized\N整个医院都动员起来了。
Dialogue: 0,0:25:54.98,0:25:58.75,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,It's terrifying, right?\N是不是很可怕？
Dialogue: 0,0:25:58.75,0:26:00.09,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Never mind that for now\N暂时先别管这件事。
Dialogue: 0,0:26:00.09,0:26:01.50,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Get everyone here first\N首先把所有人都叫到这里。
Dialogue: 0,0:26:01.50,0:26:05.38,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,joint consultation for severe and critical illnesses\N重症和危重症联合会诊
Dialogue: 0,0:26:05.38,0:26:10.24,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,What's needed is, for example, non-specialty departments like orthopedics\N例如，我们需要的是像骨科这样的非专科科室。
Dialogue: 0,0:26:10.24,0:26:10.94,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Internal Medicine\N内科
Dialogue: 0,0:26:10.94,0:26:11.78,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,surgery department\N外科
Dialogue: 0,0:26:11.78,0:26:17.82,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,to call in all departments that might be related to this condition\N召集所有可能与此情况相关的部门。
Dialogue: 0,0:26:17.82,0:26:21.68,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,combined joint rescue\N联合救援
Dialogue: 0,0:26:21.68,0:26:23.31,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,that thing\N那东西
Dialogue: 0,0:26:23.31,0:26:26.35,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,You'd better not wish for that day to come\N你最好别盼着那一天到来。
Dialogue: 0,0:26:26.35,0:26:29.05,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,You generally wouldn't trigger this mechanism\N通常情况下，你不会触发这种机制。
Dialogue: 0,0:26:29.05,0:26:30.83,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,usually not near death\N通常不会濒临死亡
Dialogue: 0,0:26:30.83,0:26:33.25,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,It's usually the very last moment\N通常是最后一刻
Dialogue: 0,0:26:33.25,0:26:36.13,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,snatching lives from the jaws of death\N从死神手中夺回生命
Dialogue: 0,0:26:36.13,0:26:37.83,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Because I, I lived\N因为我，我活着
Dialogue: 0,0:26:37.83,0:26:38.89,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,I've been hospitalized\N我住院了。
Dialogue: 0,0:26:38.89,0:26:40.61,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,It was because I was hospitalized at the time\N那是因为我当时住院了。
Dialogue: 0,0:26:40.61,0:26:41.31,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,I was bored\N我很闷
Dialogue: 0,0:26:41.31,0:26:44.40,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,I ran to the emergency room to watch the commotion.\N我跑到急诊室去看热闹。
Dialogue: 0,0:26:44.40,0:26:47.25,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,This is really, really not very ethical.\N这真的非常非常不道德。
Dialogue: 0,0:26:47.25,0:26:48.86,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,When I was hospitalized\N我住院期间
Dialogue: 0,0:26:48.86,0:26:50.78,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,I noticed that as soon as many people come in\N我注意到，一旦很多人进来，情况就会发生变化。
Dialogue: 0,0:26:50.78,0:26:55.06,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,that is, you, uh, even some reckless teenagers\N也就是说，你，呃，甚至一些鲁莽的青少年
Dialogue: 0,0:26:55.06,0:26:59.13,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,He came in without any explanation of the situation.\N他进来时没有对情况做任何解释。
Dialogue: 0,0:26:59.13,0:27:02.04,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,First, save the person's life and then talk about the rest.\N首先，救人一命，然后才能谈其他事。
Dialogue: 0,0:27:02.04,0:27:03.84,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Regardless of the situation\N无论情况如何
Dialogue: 0,0:27:03.84,0:27:07.13,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,First, just focus on saving the person, we'll deal with the rest later.\N首先，集中精力救人，其他的事情以后再说。
Dialogue: 0,0:27:07.13,0:27:09.65,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,We can discuss the rest later in detail\N其余部分我们可以稍后详细讨论。
Dialogue: 0,0:27:09.97,0:27:13.13,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Well, what I was trying to say earlier is\N我刚才想说的是……
Dialogue: 0,0:27:13.13,0:27:14.83,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,it's precisely because of this infrastructure\N正是因为有了这种基础设施。
Dialogue: 0,0:27:14.83,0:27:18.80,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,So even if you're considered upper-middle class in China\N所以即使你在中国被认为是中上阶层，也未必能成功。
Dialogue: 0,0:27:18.80,0:27:20.13,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,You don't even need to be that wealthy\N你甚至不需要很富有。
Dialogue: 0,0:27:20.13,0:27:21.49,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,mid-tier first-tier city middle class\N中等水平的一线城市中产阶级
Dialogue: 0,0:27:21.49,0:27:25.80,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,You can actually enjoy world-class services by spending a bit more money yourself.\N只要你多花一点钱，就能享受到世界一流的服务。
Dialogue: 0,0:27:25.80,0:27:28.45,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,That is to say, for these two groups of people\N也就是说，对于这两类人群而言
Dialogue: 0,0:27:28.45,0:27:29.47,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,actually now it's all\N实际上现在这一切都结束了
Dialogue: 0,0:27:29.47,0:27:32.17,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,I think this system is already the optimal one.\N我认为这个系统已经是最佳方案了。
Dialogue: 0,0:27:32.17,0:27:36.93,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,If you are just an ordinary person in China with a monthly income\N如果你只是中国一个普通的月收入者……
Dialogue: 0,0:27:36.93,0:27:38.34,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,may only be 4,5,6 thousand\N可能只有 4、5、6 千。
Dialogue: 0,0:27:38.34,0:27:40.36,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,I will go and see for myself\N我会亲自去看看。
Dialogue: 0,0:27:40.36,0:27:42.89,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Here, at the reinforced shipyard, this is Brother纳兰's domestic medical reimbursement bill\N这里，在加固的造船厂，这是纳兰兄弟的国内医疗报销账单。
Dialogue: 0,0:27:42.89,0:27:43.32,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,millions\N百万
Dialogue: 0,0:27:43.32,0:27:44.36,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,tens of millions to hundreds of millions\N数千万到数亿
Dialogue: 0,0:27:44.36,0:27:46.52,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,as long as you haven't reached the point of having more money than you can spend\N只要你还没到钱多到花不完的地步。
Dialogue: 0,0:27:46.52,0:27:47.60,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,the point where you could never spend it all\N你永远也花不完的点。
Dialogue: 0,0:27:47.60,0:27:48.70,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,before\N前
Dialogue: 0,0:27:48.70,0:27:51.38,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,This system is also good for you, yes\N是的，这套系统对你也有好处。
Dialogue: 0,0:27:51.38,0:27:52.75,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,I just don't allow people to feel liberated\N我就是不允许人们感到自由。
Dialogue: 0,0:27:52.75,0:27:57.65,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,All these people, they must all go abroad\N这些人，他们都必须出国。
Dialogue: 0,0:27:57.65,0:28:00.26,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Oh dear, this is really true, you just haven't encountered such a situation yet\N哎呀，这倒是真的，你只是还没遇到过这种情况而已。
Dialogue: 0,0:28:00.26,0:28:01.17,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Old brother, old brother\N老兄，老兄
Dialogue: 0,0:28:01.17,0:28:02.49,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,You should, you're in the industry\N你应该这么做，毕竟你身处这个行业。
Dialogue: 0,0:28:02.49,0:28:06.29,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,you should know that during those few years before\N你应该知道，在那之前的那几年里……
Dialogue: 0,0:28:06.29,0:28:08.72,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Some people just have minor illnesses\N有些人只是得了些小病。
Dialogue: 0,0:28:08.72,0:28:12.33,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,but just uh just don't believe in Ceres ah\N但是，呃，我就是不相信谷神星啊
Dialogue: 0,0:28:12.33,0:28:14.83,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,he had been receiving treatment in China for over a decade without any issues\N他在中国接受治疗十多年来一直没有出现任何问题。
Dialogue: 0,0:28:14.83,0:28:15.96,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,but went to Greece\N但去了希腊
Dialogue: 0,0:28:15.96,0:28:18.05,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Every year of treatment forces them to sell their house and car\N每过一年，治疗就迫使他们卖掉房子和车。
Dialogue: 0,0:28:18.05,0:28:20.40,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,I will go check it out myself\N我会亲自去看看。
Dialogue: 0,0:28:20.40,0:28:23.28,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Moreover, this is Brother Nalan's medical reimbursement form in China\N此外，这是纳兰哥在中国的医疗报销单。
Dialogue: 0,0:28:23.28,0:28:25.17,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,I will go and see for myself\N我会亲自去看看。
Dialogue: 0,0:28:25.17,0:28:27.56,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,But actually, I have many loves\N但实际上，我有很多爱。
Dialogue: 0,0:28:27.56,0:28:29.56,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Let me give you a very simple example\N我举个很简单的例子。
Dialogue: 0,0:28:29.56,0:28:32.20,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,I can even give a very minor illness as an example\N我甚至可以举一个轻微疾病的例子。
Dialogue: 0,0:28:32.20,0:28:35.01,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Shang, strengthen the shipyard\N尚，加强造船厂
Dialogue: 0,0:28:35.01,0:28:37.42,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Don't they all want to have an American baby?\N难道他们不都想生个美国宝宝吗？
Dialogue: 0,0:28:37.42,0:28:38.11,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Shanghai, Jiangnan Shipyard\NShanghai, Jiangnan Shipyard
Dialogue: 0,0:28:38.11,0:28:39.46,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,As everyone knows\N众所周知
Dialogue: 0,0:28:39.46,0:28:41.42,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,on, strengthening the shipyard\N继续加强造船厂
Dialogue: 0,0:28:41.42,0:28:43.29,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,because pregnancy is a personal choice\N因为怀孕是个人选择。
Dialogue: 0,0:28:43.29,0:28:44.01,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,right\N正确的
Dialogue: 0,0:28:44.01,0:28:47.85,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Except for those in the most typical large corporate\N除了那些在最典型的大型企业工作的人之外。
Dialogue: 0,0:28:47.85,0:28:50.00,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Group medical insurance personnel can cover personal liability beyond\N团体医疗保险人员可以承担超出个人责任范围的责任。
Dialogue: 0,0:28:50.00,0:28:52.82,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Here is Brother Nalan's domestic medical reimbursement form from the Jiangnan Shipyard\N这是纳兰哥在江南造船厂开具的国内医疗报销单。
Dialogue: 0,0:28:52.82,0:28:53.95,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,I will check it myself\N我会亲自核实一下。
Dialogue: 0,0:28:53.95,0:28:55.08,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,What about newborns?\N新生儿呢？
Dialogue: 0,0:28:55.08,0:28:57.51,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,For example, if a minor condition like jaundice occurs\N例如，如果出现像黄疸这样的轻微疾病
Dialogue: 0,0:28:57.51,0:29:00.48,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Here is Brother Nalan's medical reimbursement form in China from the shipyard.\N这是纳兰兄弟在中国造船厂开具的医疗报销单。
Dialogue: 0,0:29:00.48,0:29:01.74,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,You know\N你知道
Dialogue: 0,0:29:01.74,0:29:03.14,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,on, strengthen the shipyard\N继续加强造船厂建设
Dialogue: 0,0:29:03.14,0:29:03.96,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,That's very common\N这很常见。
Dialogue: 0,0:29:03.96,0:29:09.16,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Here, this is Brother纳兰's medical reimbursement form in China\N这是纳兰兄弟在中国的医疗报销单。
Dialogue: 0,0:29:09.16,0:29:10.72,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,He first, right\N他首先，没错
Dialogue: 0,0:29:10.72,0:29:13.18,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Then you have to stay in the ultraviolet room, right or wrong?\N那么你就得待在紫外线照射室里，对吧？
Dialogue: 0,0:29:13.18,0:29:14.90,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Then what about your UV box?\N那么你的紫外线杀菌箱呢？
Dialogue: 0,0:29:14.90,0:29:18.48,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Sigh, it has to be medically certified UV light.\N唉，必须是经过医疗认证的紫外线灯。
Dialogue: 0,0:29:18.48,0:29:18.83,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,elephant\N大象
Dialogue: 0,0:29:18.83,0:29:20.77,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,with medical certification\N附医疗证明
Dialogue: 0,0:29:20.77,0:29:24.26,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Here, strengthened shipyard, this is Brother Nalan's domestic medical reimbursement form\N这里是加固的船厂，这是纳兰兄弟的国内医疗报销单。
Dialogue: 0,0:29:24.26,0:29:25.04,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,right\N正确的
Dialogue: 0,0:29:25.04,0:29:25.43,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Hey\N嘿
Dialogue: 0,0:29:25.43,0:29:27.28,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,I know the number is $3000\N我知道这个数字是 3000 美元。
Dialogue: 0,0:29:27.28,0:29:28.54,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Bro, what does this mean\N兄弟，这是什么意思？
Dialogue: 0,0:29:28.54,0:29:30.41,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,There's a certified\N有认证
Dialogue: 0,0:29:30.41,0:29:36.67,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Is this so-called Smith specialist not supposed to make money?\N这位所谓的史密斯专家难道不应该赚钱吗？
Dialogue: 0,0:29:36.67,0:29:37.99,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,that certified professional\N那位认证专业人士
Dialogue: 0,0:29:37.99,0:29:41.02,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,So even using that equipment requires certification, right? Yeah, of course.\N所以即使使用那种设备也需要认证，对吧？是的，当然。
Dialogue: 0,0:29:41.02,0:29:42.25,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,He's the one using this equipment.\N他就是使用这套设备的人。
Dialogue: 0,0:29:42.25,0:29:43.25,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Of course\N当然
Dialogue: 0,0:29:43.25,0:29:44.71,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,a government hand\N政府官员
Dialogue: 0,0:29:44.71,0:29:46.90,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Oh, I'm doing my postgraduate studies\N哦，我正在攻读研究生学位。
Dialogue: 0,0:29:46.90,0:29:48.28,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Oh dear oh dear\N哦，天哪，哦，天哪
Dialogue: 0,0:29:48.28,0:29:48.92,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Too sweet\N太甜了
Dialogue: 0,0:29:48.92,0:29:50.14,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Listen carefully\N仔细听
Dialogue: 0,0:29:50.14,0:29:54.16,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Here's Brother纳兰's domestic medical reimbursement form from 加强造船厂\NHere's Brother 纳兰's domestic medical reimbursement form from 加强造船厂
Dialogue: 0,0:29:54.16,0:29:57.46,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,But don't forget, it's not up to you when you can get out of treatment\N但别忘了，何时结束治疗并非由你决定。
Dialogue: 0,0:29:57.46,0:29:58.98,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,It's not up to you to decide.\N这并非由你决定。
Dialogue: 0,0:29:58.98,0:30:00.25,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,For humanitarian purposes\N出于人道主义目的
Dialogue: 0,0:30:00.25,0:30:01.66,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Children lack the capacity to make decisions.\N儿童缺乏做决定的能力。
Dialogue: 0,0:30:01.66,0:30:04.33,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Isn't this something the doctor should decide?\N这难道不应该由医生来决定吗？
Dialogue: 0,0:30:04.33,0:30:06.84,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,on, strengthening the shipyard\N继续加强造船厂
Dialogue: 0,0:30:06.84,0:30:08.60,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Haha, right?\N哈哈，对吧？
Dialogue: 0,0:30:08.60,0:30:11.52,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Then staying for 90 days would be a completely normal thing, wouldn't it?\N那么待上 90 天就完全正常了，不是吗？
Dialogue: 0,0:30:11.52,0:30:13.40,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Okay, now take out your calculator\N好了，现在拿出你的计算器
Dialogue: 0,0:30:13.40,0:30:16.29,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,How much is $3,000 multiplied by 90 days in dollars?\N3000 美元乘以 90 天等于多少美元？
Dialogue: 0,0:30:16.29,0:30:21.27,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,How much is 270,000 dollars multiplied by seven?\N27 万美元乘以 7 等于多少？
Dialogue: 0,0:30:21.27,0:30:24.75,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Oh my god, haha\N我的天啊，哈哈
Dialogue: 0,0:30:24.75,0:30:25.63,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Then it's 100\N那么就是 100
Dialogue: 0,0:30:25.63,0:30:29.74,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Why do we need to multiply 270,000 dollars by seven to convert it to RMB?\N为什么我们需要将 27 万美元乘以 7 才能将其转换为人民币？
Dialogue: 0,0:30:29.74,0:30:31.53,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,100 yuan\N100 元
Dialogue: 0,0:30:31.53,0:30:33.44,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,on, strengthen the shipyard\N继续加强造船厂建设
Dialogue: 0,0:30:33.44,0:30:34.88,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,nearly 2 million\N近 200 万
Dialogue: 0,0:30:34.88,0:30:35.79,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,1.89 million\N189 万
Dialogue: 0,0:30:35.79,0:30:37.84,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,nearly 2 million, hmm\N将近 200 万，嗯。
Dialogue: 0,0:30:37.84,0:30:38.75,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Shanghai, strengthen the shipyard\N上海，加强造船厂建设
Dialogue: 0,0:30:38.75,0:30:39.65,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Let me read the SC\N让我读一下最高法院的判决。
Dialogue: 0,0:30:39.65,0:30:41.76,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Above, strengthen the shipyard\N上方，加强造船厂
Dialogue: 0,0:30:41.76,0:30:42.76,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,There's a joke in the medical industry\N医疗界有个笑话
Dialogue: 0,0:30:42.76,0:30:44.36,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,When the intern can't handle it,\N当实习生无法胜任时，
Dialogue: 0,0:30:44.36,0:30:46.02,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,might summon their grandmaster to save the day\N或许会召唤他们的宗师来力挽狂澜。
Dialogue: 0,0:30:46.02,0:30:48.83,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,There is also one more thing: thank you, Brother J, for the tip.\N还有一件事：谢谢 J 兄弟提供的建议。
Dialogue: 0,0:30:48.83,0:30:49.44,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Click on the damn image\N点击那张该死的图片
Dialogue: 0,0:30:49.44,0:30:51.07,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,I'll go check it out myself\N我亲自去看看。
Dialogue: 0,0:30:51.07,0:30:51.64,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,searched for a long time\N找了很久
Dialogue: 0,0:30:51.64,0:30:53.58,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,I'll go take a look myself\N我亲自去看看。
Dialogue: 0,0:30:53.58,0:30:54.08,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Yes\N是的
Dialogue: 0,0:30:54.08,0:30:55.80,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Is it the picture on the left?\N是左边那张图吗？
Dialogue: 0,0:30:55.80,0:31:02.59,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Well, because, because, because I've been hospitalized before.\N嗯，因为，因为，因为我以前住过院。
Dialogue: 0,0:31:02.59,0:31:06.83,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,I would check it myself\N我会亲自去查一下。
Dialogue: 0,0:31:06.83,0:31:08.83,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,And at that time, because it was a fracture\N当时，因为那是一次骨折。
Dialogue: 0,0:31:08.83,0:31:11.66,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,I will check it myself\N我会亲自核实一下。
Dialogue: 0,0:31:11.66,0:31:14.70,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Did the internal organs show any damage from the impact of the fracture?\N骨折冲击是否对内脏器官造成损伤？
Dialogue: 0,0:31:14.70,0:31:17.81,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,I don't even know why\N我甚至不知道为什么
Dialogue: 0,0:31:17.81,0:31:20.68,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,and then a whole bunch of doctors came in\N然后一大群医生进来了。
Dialogue: 0,0:31:20.68,0:31:22.35,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,and then this examination also checks\N然后，这项检查还会检查以下内容。
Dialogue: 0,0:31:22.35,0:31:23.18,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,that touching check\N那张触感检查
Dialogue: 0,0:31:23.18,0:31:27.57,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Only then, at the very end, did they finally feel assured enough to admit me.\N直到最后，他们才终于觉得足够放心，录取了我。
Dialogue: 0,0:31:27.57,0:31:28.44,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Hey hey hey, let me ask you something\N嘿嘿嘿，我问你个问题
Dialogue: 0,0:31:28.44,0:31:28.96,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,just bros\N只是兄弟
Dialogue: 0,0:31:28.96,0:31:30.61,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,If such a situation occurs\N如果出现这种情况
Dialogue: 0,0:31:30.61,0:31:34.18,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,on, strengthen the shipyard\N继续加强造船厂建设
Dialogue: 0,0:31:35.47,0:31:40.78,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Well first of all, there needs to be an authoritative institution\N首先，需要一个权威机构。
Dialogue: 0,0:31:40.78,0:31:44.50,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,This institution itself must have an adequate number of doctors\N该机构本身必须拥有足够数量的医生
Dialogue: 0,0:31:44.77,0:31:46.38,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,this premise\N这个前提
Dialogue: 0,0:31:46.38,0:31:49.46,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,on strengthening the shipyard, this is Brother纳兰's domestic medical reimbursement form\N关于加强船厂建设，这是纳兰兄弟的国内医疗报销单
Dialogue: 0,0:31:49.46,0:31:51.34,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,I will go and see for myself\N我会亲自去看看。
Dialogue: 0,0:31:51.34,0:31:53.54,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,I remember Mayo, I specialize in treating cancer.\N我记得梅奥诊所，我专攻癌症治疗。
Dialogue: 0,0:31:53.54,0:31:55.75,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,I'll go see it myself.\N我打算亲自去看一看。
Dialogue: 0,0:31:55.75,0:31:56.86,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,What is he specialized in treating?\N他擅长治疗什么疾病？
Dialogue: 0,0:31:56.86,0:31:58.53,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,His starting point is entirely different.\N他的出发点完全不同。
Dialogue: 0,0:31:58.53,0:32:00.61,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Your hospital might not necessarily have a general practice department\N您的医院可能没有全科医疗部门。
Dialogue: 0,0:32:00.61,0:32:01.81,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Oh\N哦
Dialogue: 0,0:32:01.81,0:32:04.02,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Oh, in his hospital, it's not like us\N哦，在他住的医院里，情况跟我们不一样。
Dialogue: 0,0:32:04.02,0:32:07.54,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Here is Brother纳兰's domestic medical reimbursement form from the shipyard\N这是纳兰兄弟从造船厂开具的国内医疗报销单。
Dialogue: 0,0:32:07.54,0:32:08.62,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,That is because what\N那是因为什么
Dialogue: 0,0:32:08.62,0:32:12.30,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Because this hospital was originally established by some wealthy individuals\N因为这家医院最初是由一些富裕人士创办的。
Dialogue: 0,0:32:12.30,0:32:14.73,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,something specifically invested in\N专门投资的东西
Dialogue: 0,0:32:15.08,0:32:19.24,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,because the hospital itself was custom-built\N因为医院本身是专门定制建造的。
Dialogue: 0,0:32:19.24,0:32:21.31,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,It does not serve the people\N它对人民没有好处。
Dialogue: 0,0:32:21.31,0:32:22.09,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,You know what I mean\N你知道我的意思
Dialogue: 0,0:32:22.09,0:32:23.64,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,it serves the people\N它服务于人民。
Dialogue: 0,0:32:23.64,0:32:28.29,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,And then the second point is that there needs to be an initiator, uh\N第二点是，需要有一个发起人，嗯。
Dialogue: 0,0:32:28.29,0:32:32.04,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Here is Brother纳兰's domestic medical reimbursement form from the shipyard.\N这是 Brother 纳兰从船厂获得的国内医疗报销单。
Dialogue: 0,0:32:32.04,0:32:34.65,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,But but I remember in our insurance service\N但是，我记得在我们的保险服务中
Dialogue: 0,0:32:34.65,0:32:41.72,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Above is Brother Nalan's medical reimbursement form in China from the strengthened shipyard.\N以上是纳兰兄弟在中国加固的造船厂开具的医疗报销单。
Dialogue: 0,0:32:41.72,0:32:44.22,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,You can initiate this thing.\N你可以启动这个程序。
Dialogue: 0,0:32:49.66,0:32:50.74,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,I will check it myself\N我会亲自核实一下。
Dialogue: 0,0:32:50.74,0:32:54.70,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,On the reinforcement shipyard, this is Brother纳兰's domestic medical reimbursement form\N在加固船厂，这是纳兰兄弟的国内医疗报销单
Dialogue: 0,0:32:54.70,0:32:56.33,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,36 days in the ICU\N在重症监护室住了 36 天
Dialogue: 0,0:32:56.33,0:32:59.26,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,two days in a row\N连续两天
Dialogue: 0,0:32:59.26,0:33:02.44,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,On, strengthen the shipyard\N继续加强造船厂建设
Dialogue: 0,0:33:02.44,0:33:04.72,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,It seems the report was completed with over 40.\N这份报告似乎已经完成了 40 多个人。
Dialogue: 0,0:33:04.72,0:33:06.70,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Shanghai, strengthen shipyard\N上海，加强造船厂建设
Dialogue: 0,0:33:06.70,0:33:08.40,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,I don't know the exact figure\N我不知道确切数字。
Dialogue: 0,0:33:08.40,0:33:11.78,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Anyway, my dad mentioned it was like over 40.\N总之，我爸说大概超过 40 了。
Dialogue: 0,0:33:11.78,0:33:13.47,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Let me show you all\N让我来给你们全部展示一下。
Dialogue: 0,0:33:13.47,0:33:15.38,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Is it still\N还是
Dialogue: 0,0:33:15.38,0:33:18.03,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Let me read it for you\N我来读给你听。
Dialogue: 0,0:33:18.03,0:33:19.61,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,American doctors\N美国医生
Dialogue: 0,0:33:19.61,0:33:22.79,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,I will go see for myself\N我会亲自去看看。
Dialogue: 0,0:33:22.79,0:33:26.72,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Every year, every year, every year, they receive patients\N每年，每年，每年，他们都会接收病人。
Dialogue: 0,0:33:26.72,0:33:28.55,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Ah, there's no data.\N啊，没有数据。
Dialogue: 0,0:33:28.55,0:33:33.75,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,That is, countless surgeons, 320 to 820 cases a year.\N也就是说，无数外科医生每年要进行 320 到 820 例手术。
Dialogue: 0,0:33:33.75,0:33:36.64,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Psychiatrists 50~170\N精神科医生 50~170
Dialogue: 0,0:33:36.64,0:33:46.52,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Here is Brother Nalan's domestic medical reimbursement slip at the strengthened shipyard\N这是纳兰兄弟在加固造船厂开具的国内医疗报销单。
Dialogue: 0,0:33:46.52,0:33:50.20,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,300 to 450 a year\N每年 300 至 450
Dialogue: 0,0:33:51.94,0:33:53.50,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Um, a year\N一年
Dialogue: 0,0:33:53.50,0:33:57.92,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,So if this shutdown incident happens\N所以如果这次停工事件发生
Dialogue: 0,0:33:57.92,0:34:05.43,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Here is Brother Nalan's medical reimbursement form from a domestic shipyard.\N这是纳兰兄弟从国内造船厂获得的医疗报销单。
Dialogue: 0,0:34:05.43,0:34:08.69,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Haha, fifty or sixty million people\N哈哈，五六千万人
Dialogue: 0,0:34:10.01,0:34:14.82,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,So now ACACA is now yes\N所以现在 ACACA 的答案是肯定的。
Dialogue: 0,0:34:14.82,0:34:17.23,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,And also, this is the AACA\N还有，这是 AACA
Dialogue: 0,0:34:17.23,0:34:19.78,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,I will go check it out myself\N我会亲自去看看。
Dialogue: 0,0:34:20.11,0:34:24.03,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Here is Brother Nalan's medical reimbursement form in China from the strengthened shipyard.\N这是纳兰兄弟在中国加固的造船厂开具的医疗报销单。
Dialogue: 0,0:34:24.03,0:34:25.96,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,I've seen some families of four\N我见过一些四口之家。
Dialogue: 0,0:34:25.96,0:34:31.17,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,The parents have to pay 42,100 yuan in annual insurance premiums for their two children.\N这对父母每年需要为他们的两个孩子缴纳 42100 元的保险费。
Dialogue: 0,0:34:31.92,0:34:37.15,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Shang, strengthen the shipyard\N尚，加强造船厂
Dialogue: 0,0:34:37.15,0:34:39.01,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Just think about this expense\N想想这笔开销。
Dialogue: 0,0:34:39.01,0:34:43.51,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,from 2000 a month to 42,000 a year\N从每月 2000 到每年 42000
Dialogue: 0,0:34:43.51,0:34:45.19,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Can he afford it?\N他买得起吗？
Dialogue: 0,0:34:45.19,0:34:46.92,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,He can't afford it, hmm\N他买不起，嗯。
Dialogue: 0,0:34:46.96,0:34:48.84,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,absolutely unaffordable\N完全负担不起
Dialogue: 0,0:34:48.84,0:34:51.01,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,It's a matter of life and death\N这是生死攸关的事。
Dialogue: 0,0:34:51.55,0:34:53.95,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Here, strengthening the shipyard. This is Brother Nalan's domestic medical reimbursement form.\N这里，正在加固船厂。这是纳兰兄弟的国内医疗报销单。
Dialogue: 0,0:34:53.95,0:34:55.96,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,That is not just 16 million\N那可不仅仅是 1600 万。
Dialogue: 0,0:34:55.96,0:34:57.44,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,he has 60 million\N他有 6000 万
Dialogue: 0,0:34:57.44,0:35:00.55,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,covered the costs for approximately over 70 million people\N涵盖了大约 7000 多万人的费用
Dialogue: 0,0:35:00.55,0:35:04.01,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,There are also nearly 10 million illegal immigrants among them.\N其中还有近 1000 万非法移民。
Dialogue: 0,0:35:04.01,0:35:05.96,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Illegal immigrants are purely consuming this money\N非法移民完全是在挥霍这些钱。
Dialogue: 0,0:35:05.96,0:35:08.51,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Additionally, strengthen the shipyard\N此外，加强造船厂建设
Dialogue: 0,0:35:09.94,0:35:10.65,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,you know what I mean\N你知道我的意思
Dialogue: 0,0:35:10.65,0:35:15.61,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Here, strengthening the shipyard is Brother纳兰’s domestic medical reimbursement form\N这里，加强造船厂建设是纳兰兄弟的国内医疗报销表格
Dialogue: 0,0:35:16.44,0:35:17.51,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,their housing\N他们的住房
Dialogue: 0,0:35:17.51,0:35:21.67,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,I'll go check it out myself\N我亲自去看看。
Dialogue: 0,0:35:22.76,0:35:25.46,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,It was Trump who abolished it\N是特朗普废除了它。
Dialogue: 0,0:35:25.46,0:35:28.55,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,It is regarded as a welfare benefit by the middle class.\N中产阶级将其视为一项福利。
Dialogue: 0,0:35:32.96,0:35:33.92,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Just think about it\N仔细想想
Dialogue: 0,0:35:33.92,0:35:36.44,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,In November, because of the renewal of health insurance in the United States\N11 月，由于美国医疗保险的续期
Dialogue: 0,0:35:36.44,0:35:39.38,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,roughly from October to the end of November\N大致从十月到十一月底
Dialogue: 0,0:35:39.38,0:35:41.17,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,I'm renewing my health insurance for the next year\N我正在续保下一年的健康保险。
Dialogue: 0,0:35:41.17,0:35:42.73,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,There are a few things in November\N十一月有几件事。
Dialogue: 0,0:35:42.73,0:35:46.07,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,The ACA is about to be terminated, right?\N《平价医疗法案》（ACA）即将终止，对吗？
Dialogue: 0,0:35:46.07,0:35:46.76,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,food stamps\N食品券
Dialogue: 0,0:35:46.76,0:35:49.57,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Here, strengthening the shipyard is Brother纳兰's medical reimbursement form in China.\N在这里，加强造船厂建设是 Brother 纳兰在中国的医疗报销表格。
Dialogue: 0,0:35:49.57,0:35:52.48,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,I will check it myself\N我会亲自核实一下。
Dialogue: 0,0:35:52.48,0:35:56.32,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Above, strengthening the shipyard, this is Brother Nalan's domestic medical reimbursement form\N以上是加固船厂的部分，这是纳兰兄弟的国内医疗报销单。
Dialogue: 0,0:35:56.32,0:35:58.30,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,basically consistent\N基本一致
Dialogue: 0,0:35:58.30,0:36:00.15,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,which is 42 million people\N也就是 4200 万人
Dialogue: 0,0:36:00.15,0:36:01.05,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,no food stamps\N没有食品券
Dialogue: 0,0:36:02.90,0:36:06.21,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,But the freight charges are definitely still being collected now.\N但目前运费肯定还在收取。
Dialogue: 0,0:36:06.21,0:36:06.67,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,right\N正确的
Dialogue: 0,0:36:06.67,0:36:08.84,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,So the shipping industry's national fortunes are in disorder.\N因此，航运业的命运岌岌可危。
Dialogue: 0,0:36:08.84,0:36:11.78,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,The port of Seattle has been completely devastated.\N西雅图港已彻底损毁。
Dialogue: 0,0:36:11.78,0:36:14.05,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,and strengthen the shipyard\N并加强造船厂
Dialogue: 0,0:36:14.05,0:36:16.81,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,and then uh because of deporting illegal immigrants\N然后，呃，因为遣返非法移民
Dialogue: 0,0:36:16.81,0:36:18.43,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,That Old A has talked about it many times before\N老 A 以前多次谈到过这件事。
Dialogue: 0,0:36:18.43,0:36:19.19,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,illegal immigrants\N非法移民
Dialogue: 0,0:36:19.19,0:36:20.23,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,many demanding jobs\N许多高要求的工作
Dialogue: 0,0:36:20.23,0:36:21.13,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,either in the catering industry\N无论是在餐饮业
Dialogue: 0,0:36:21.13,0:36:22.15,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,or slaughtering\N或屠宰
Dialogue: 0,0:36:22.15,0:36:23.30,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,or agriculture\N或农业
Dialogue: 0,0:36:23.30,0:36:25.59,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,I'll go check it out myself\N我亲自去看看。
Dialogue: 0,0:36:25.59,0:36:26.69,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,maintaining urban operations\N维持城市运转
Dialogue: 0,0:36:26.69,0:36:28.77,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,the urban underclass, um, okay\N城市底层阶级，嗯，好吧
Dialogue: 0,0:36:28.77,0:36:30.85,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,And then these things of yours\N然后还有你的这些东西
Dialogue: 0,0:36:30.85,0:36:34.19,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,If it happens to coincide with, as everyone knows, November being Thanksgiving\N如果恰好与 11 月感恩节重合，众所周知，11 月是感恩节。
Dialogue: 0,0:36:34.19,0:36:35.86,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,December is Christmas\N十二月是圣诞节
Dialogue: 0,0:36:35.86,0:36:37.59,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,on, strengthen the shipyard\N继续加强造船厂建设
Dialogue: 0,0:36:37.59,0:36:39.15,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,and Halloween\N以及万圣节
Dialogue: 0,0:36:39.15,0:36:39.94,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Has it passed?\N已经过去了吗？
Dialogue: 0,0:36:39.94,0:36:40.55,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,On, strengthen the shipyard\N继续加强造船厂建设
Dialogue: 0,0:36:40.55,0:36:41.80,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,It's almost over\N快结束了
Dialogue: 0,0:36:41.80,0:36:45.48,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,On, strengthen the shipyard\N继续加强造船厂建设
Dialogue: 0,0:36:45.48,0:36:46.00,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,in our neighborhood\N在我们社区
Dialogue: 0,0:36:46.00,0:36:48.03,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,It seems that this thing hasn't been prepared for the children yet\N看来这东西还没准备好给孩子们用。
Dialogue: 0,0:36:48.03,0:36:48.59,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,but anyway what\N不过话说回来，什么？
Dialogue: 0,0:36:48.59,0:36:53.82,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,That is to say, if these few things are stacked together\N也就是说，如果把这几样东西放在一起比较……
Dialogue: 0,0:36:53.82,0:36:56.94,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Then perhaps out of 300 million people, 160 million won't be affected.\N那么，在 3 亿人口中，或许有 1.6 亿人不会受到影响。
Dialogue: 0,0:36:56.94,0:36:57.42,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,No problem\N没问题
Dialogue: 0,0:36:57.42,0:36:59.82,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,it means there's that company\N这意味着有那家公司
Dialogue: 0,0:36:59.82,0:37:02.51,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Here is Brother Nalan's medical reimbursement form in China, let's strengthen the shipyard\N这是纳兰兄弟在中国的医疗报销单，让我们加强造船厂建设吧。
Dialogue: 0,0:37:02.51,0:37:05.00,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,The remaining bit is completely different\N剩下的部分则完全不同。
Dialogue: 0,0:37:07.96,0:37:09.63,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,on, strengthening the shipyard\N继续加强造船厂
Dialogue: 0,0:37:09.63,0:37:12.11,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Because there are still 20 million illegal immigrants.\N因为还有 2000 万非法移民。
Dialogue: 0,0:37:12.84,0:37:17.84,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Damn, it's really eating away at everything, absolutely nothing left\N该死，它真的把一切都吞噬殆尽，什么都没剩下。
Dialogue: 0,0:37:17.84,0:37:19.67,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,And just as Lao Yi mentioned earlier\N正如老毅之前提到的那样。
Dialogue: 0,0:37:19.67,0:37:20.55,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,This one is also not easy to cut off\N这个也不容易切掉。
Dialogue: 0,0:37:20.55,0:37:21.03,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,once it's cut off\N一旦被切断
Dialogue: 0,0:37:21.03,0:37:22.38,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,it will be troublesome later\N以后会很麻烦。
Dialogue: 0,0:37:22.90,0:37:26.78,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,I will go check it myself\N我本人会去查看。
Dialogue: 0,0:37:27.15,0:37:30.90,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Damn, someone's gonna go to extremes soon.\N糟了，看来有人很快就要走极端了。
Dialogue: 0,0:37:30.90,0:37:34.17,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,I've already collected many bodies these past two days.\N过去两天我已经收集了很多尸体。
Dialogue: 0,0:37:34.17,0:37:35.90,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,The temperature is getting lower and lower\N气温越来越低
Dialogue: 0,0:37:35.90,0:37:37.34,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,on, strengthen the shipyard\N继续加强造船厂建设
Dialogue: 0,0:37:37.34,0:37:38.65,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,The humidity is getting higher and higher\N湿度越来越高了。
Dialogue: 0,0:37:38.65,0:37:40.48,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,The rain is becoming more frequent\N雨越来越频繁了。
Dialogue: 0,0:37:40.48,0:37:43.48,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Someone is bound to crack first\N总会有人第一个崩溃的。
Dialogue: 0,0:37:43.73,0:37:45.61,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Fortunately, energy prices have been low these two days.\N幸运的是，这两天的能源价格一直很低。
Dialogue: 0,0:37:45.61,0:37:47.05,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,But then again\N但话又说回来……
Dialogue: 0,0:37:47.05,0:37:48.55,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Electricity prices in the US are rising again\N美国电价再次上涨
Dialogue: 0,0:37:48.55,0:37:50.59,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Electricity prices in the U.S. are now fluctuating between rising and falling.\N美国的电价目前呈现波动趋势，时而上涨，时而下跌。
Dialogue: 0,0:37:50.59,0:37:52.59,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Electricity prices in the U.S. are now rising outrageously.\N美国的电价现在正以惊人的速度上涨。
Dialogue: 0,0:37:52.59,0:37:54.13,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,I will check it myself\N我会亲自核实一下。
Dialogue: 0,0:37:54.13,0:37:55.28,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,My electricity bill has increased.\N我的电费账单上涨了。
Dialogue: 0,0:37:55.28,0:37:57.59,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Our average annual electricity bill now\N我们现在的平均年度电费
Dialogue: 0,0:37:57.59,0:38:00.40,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,The average increase is around fourteen to fourteen percent.\N平均增幅约为 14%至 14%。
Dialogue: 0,0:38:00.40,0:38:02.69,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,On average, that's not too bad, is it?\N平均而言，这还算不错，对吧？
Dialogue: 0,0:38:02.69,0:38:04.05,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,That's on average\N这是平均水平
Dialogue: 0,0:38:04.05,0:38:05.76,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,and it must be calculated based on 202\N而且必须根据 202 进行计算
Dialogue: 0,0:38:05.76,0:38:07.01,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Shanghai Jiangnan Shipyard\NShanghai Jiangnan Shipyard
Dialogue: 0,0:38:07.01,0:38:09.67,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,By last year, the average annual rate was 14%\N截至去年，平均年利率为 14%。
Dialogue: 0,0:38:09.67,0:38:12.67,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,But in fact, it increased by 22% last year.\N但事实上，去年增长了 22%。
Dialogue: 0,0:38:12.67,0:38:16.75,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,It's just an average, you know.\N这只是个平均值而已。
Dialogue: 0,0:38:16.75,0:38:18.36,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Last year it was 22%\N去年是 22%。
Dialogue: 0,0:38:18.36,0:38:21.94,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,This year it's basically heading for over 25%\N今年基本上要超过 25%了
Dialogue: 0,0:38:21.94,0:38:22.98,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Thanks to Xinfengzhitian\NThanks to Xinfengzhitian
Dialogue: 0,0:38:22.98,0:38:23.50,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Brother Da Gan\N达干哥
Dialogue: 0,0:38:23.50,0:38:25.46,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,I'll check it myself\N我会亲自检查一下。
Dialogue: 0,0:38:25.46,0:38:26.44,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Discharged in July\N七月出院
Dialogue: 0,0:38:26.44,0:38:27.36,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,47,000\N｛1001｝
Dialogue: 0,0:38:27.36,0:38:28.36,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,After reimbursement, it's 11,000\N报销后，是 11,000。
Dialogue: 0,0:38:28.36,0:38:29.84,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,My medical insurance card has 7,000\N我的医疗保险卡有 7000 元
Dialogue: 0,0:38:29.84,0:38:33.05,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,In the end, I only had to pay 3,000.\N最后，我只需要支付 3000 元。
Dialogue: 0,0:38:33.53,0:38:37.23,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,on, strengthen the shipyard\N继续加强造船厂建设
Dialogue: 0,0:38:37.23,0:38:39.94,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,That's why there's now an expectation saying\N这就是为什么现在人们期望说……
Dialogue: 0,0:38:39.94,0:38:43.59,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Perhaps Trump is about to immediately taco on apex\N或许特朗普马上就要在巅峰时期大展拳脚了。
Dialogue: 0,0:38:43.59,0:38:46.21,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Let me think about it, yeah yeah\N让我想想，嗯嗯
Dialogue: 0,0:38:46.21,0:38:49.19,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Actually, they don't care whether he collapses or not\N事实上，他们并不关心他是否会倒下。
Dialogue: 0,0:38:49.19,0:38:51.19,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,This matter is definitely beyond saving\N这件事已经无可挽回了。
Dialogue: 0,0:38:51.19,0:38:57.67,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Here, strengthening the shipyard, this is Brother Nalan's medical reimbursement form in China.\N这里，加强造船厂建设，这是纳兰兄弟在中国的医疗报销单。
Dialogue: 0,0:38:57.67,0:39:00.32,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,His food stamps and everything have all been restored to your logistics\N他的食品券和其他所有东西都已恢复到你们物流部门的记录中。
Dialogue: 0,0:39:00.32,0:39:02.82,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Go, strengthen the shipyard\N去，加强造船厂建设
Dialogue: 0,0:39:02.82,0:39:05.71,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,There's no way that would be in time.\N绝对来不及。
Dialogue: 0,0:39:06.61,0:39:07.92,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Thanks to Brother Zhen Dasha\N感谢甄达沙兄弟
Dialogue: 0,0:39:07.92,0:39:09.92,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Come on, strengthen the shipyard\N加油，加强造船厂建设！
Dialogue: 0,0:39:09.92,0:39:11.19,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,European and American health insurance is too shady\N欧美医疗保险太不透明了。
Dialogue: 0,0:39:11.19,0:39:12.40,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,leading to skyrocketing costs\N导致成本飙升
Dialogue: 0,0:39:12.40,0:39:14.34,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,On the other hand, strengthen the shipyard\N另一方面，加强造船厂建设
Dialogue: 0,0:39:14.34,0:39:15.23,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,cannot afford medical treatment\N负担不起医疗费用
Dialogue: 0,0:39:15.23,0:39:16.71,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,resulting in an increasing number of Gundams\N导致高达的数量不断增加
Dialogue: 0,0:39:16.71,0:39:18.94,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,while Gundam can still be recycled for more uses\N高达模型仍然可以回收利用，用于更多用途。
Dialogue: 0,0:39:18.94,0:39:20.17,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,using the damn thing\N用那玩意儿
Dialogue: 0,0:39:20.17,0:39:22.61,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Here, strengthening the shipyard is Brother纳兰's domestic medical reimbursement bill\N这里，加强造船厂建设就是纳兰兄弟的国内医疗报销账单。
Dialogue: 0,0:39:22.61,0:39:26.01,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,No wonder the U.S. population remains stagnant despite a continuous surge in immigration\N难怪尽管移民数量持续激增，美国人口却依然停滞不前。
Dialogue: 0,0:39:26.01,0:39:28.05,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,the overall population remains relatively stagnant\N总体人口数量保持相对稳定。
Dialogue: 0,0:39:28.05,0:39:29.67,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,It's completely inhumane\N这完全不人道。
Dialogue: 0,0:39:29.67,0:39:32.82,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,I'm still going to share this picture, um, yes, let me tell you\N我还是要分享这张照片，嗯，是的，让我告诉你。
Dialogue: 0,0:39:32.82,0:39:36.11,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,I'm really grateful today that Lao Wei allowed me to speak.\N今天我非常感激老伟允许我发言。
Dialogue: 0,0:39:36.11,0:39:39.19,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Today is my first time being a guest here, um\N今天是我第一次来这里做客人，嗯。
Dialogue: 0,0:39:39.19,0:39:41.17,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,There's actually a problem here that\N这里实际上存在一个问题：
Dialogue: 0,0:39:41.17,0:39:43.30,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Many of my American classmates told me at the time\N当时我的许多美国同学都告诉我这一点。
Dialogue: 0,0:39:43.30,0:39:46.38,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Now, but it was much later that I gradually came to understand.\N但过了很久我才逐渐明白。
Dialogue: 0,0:39:46.38,0:39:51.63,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Actually, for the vast majority of Americans\N事实上，对于绝大多数美国人来说
Dialogue: 0,0:39:51.63,0:39:54.28,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,I will go and see for myself\N我会亲自去看看。
Dialogue: 0,0:39:54.28,0:39:57.55,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,I think people back home probably haven't experienced much of this yet\N我觉得家乡的人们可能还没怎么经历过这些。
Dialogue: 0,0:39:57.55,0:39:59.30,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,but in first-tier cities\N但在一线城市
Dialogue: 0,0:39:59.30,0:40:00.53,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,especially in second-tier cities\N尤其是在二线城市
Dialogue: 0,0:40:00.53,0:40:03.23,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Perhaps it also includes the notion that everyone has\N或许它也包含了每个人都拥有的这种观念。
Dialogue: 0,0:40:03.23,0:40:05.55,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,like when grandparents pass away and leave behind a house\N比如祖父母去世后留下一栋房子
Dialogue: 0,0:40:05.55,0:40:06.92,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Does this kind of thought exist?\N这种想法真的存在吗？
Dialogue: 0,0:40:06.92,0:40:08.44,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Is it common\N常见吗？
Dialogue: 0,0:40:09.15,0:40:10.71,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,It should be quite common in the domestic market, right?\N这在国内市场应该很常见吧？
Dialogue: 0,0:40:10.71,0:40:11.96,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Ah, it's quite normal\N啊，这很正常。
Dialogue: 0,0:40:11.96,0:40:14.00,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Let me tell you all, I mean\N让我来告诉你们所有人，我的意思是
Dialogue: 0,0:40:14.00,0:40:14.78,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Go ahead and strengthen the shipyard, this is the N/A\N请继续加强造船厂建设，这是不适用的。
Dialogue: 0,0:40:14.78,0:40:17.86,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,many so-called second-generation rich kids in Guangzhou\N广州有很多所谓的富二代
Dialogue: 0,0:40:17.86,0:40:20.13,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,how come it's just so simple\N为什么就这么简单呢？
Dialogue: 0,0:40:20.13,0:40:21.23,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,can't do anything\N什么都做不了
Dialogue: 0,0:40:21.23,0:40:24.17,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,but they have a piece of land\N但他们拥有一块土地。
Dialogue: 0,0:40:24.17,0:40:25.61,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,There has been demolition\N已经进行了拆除
Dialogue: 0,0:40:25.61,0:40:26.73,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,let alone the rental income\N更别提租金收入了。
Dialogue: 0,0:40:26.73,0:40:30.44,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,In those situations, I would say even if the grandparents were workers\N在这种情况下，即使祖父母是劳动者，我也会说……
Dialogue: 0,0:40:30.44,0:40:32.38,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,at least they got a house\N至少他们得到了一套房子。
Dialogue: 0,0:40:32.38,0:40:35.03,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,A house can be sold for around 1 million yuan no matter what.\N无论如何，房子都能卖到 100 万元左右。
Dialogue: 0,0:40:35.03,0:40:36.03,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,right\N正确的
Dialogue: 0,0:40:36.03,0:40:38.07,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Oh no no no, it depends on the location\N哦不不不，这取决于地点。
Dialogue: 0,0:40:38.07,0:40:40.15,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Ah\N啊
Dialogue: 0,0:40:40.15,0:40:41.84,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,No no no no, that's not the case\N不不不不，不是这样的。
Dialogue: 0,0:40:41.84,0:40:45.34,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Bro, if you understand his grandparents\N兄弟，如果你了解他的祖父母……
Dialogue: 0,0:40:45.34,0:40:48.61,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,If they were former frontline state-owned enterprise workers\N如果他们是以前国有企业一线员工。
Dialogue: 0,0:40:48.61,0:40:50.48,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,The location of his house would definitely not be bad\N他家的位置肯定不错。
Dialogue: 0,0:40:50.48,0:40:51.71,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,and might even possibly\N甚至有可能
Dialogue: 0,0:40:51.71,0:40:54.13,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,and often more than one property\N而且通常不止一处房产
Dialogue: 0,0:40:54.13,0:40:55.25,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Yeah yeah yeah\N对对对对
Dialogue: 0,0:40:55.25,0:40:56.13,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,even if it's just one house\N即使只是一栋房子
Dialogue: 0,0:40:56.13,0:40:58.05,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,the best-case scenario\N最佳情况
Dialogue: 0,0:40:58.05,0:41:00.71,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,We ordinary people also need to consider that China has many second-tier cities, right?\N我们普通人也需要考虑到，中国有很多二线城市，对吧？
Dialogue: 0,0:41:00.71,0:41:02.19,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,People often call me an appendage in the group chat.\N在群聊里，人们经常叫我“附属物”。
Dialogue: 0,0:41:02.19,0:41:03.48,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,It's because I don't take these situations into account\N这是因为我没有考虑到这些情况。
Dialogue: 0,0:41:03.48,0:41:05.17,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,I am considering these situations\N我正在考虑这些情况。
Dialogue: 0,0:41:05.17,0:41:10.19,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,But why doesn't the United States have it?\N但为什么美国没有呢？
Dialogue: 0,0:41:11.67,0:41:13.76,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,The inheritance tax is terrifying.\N遗产税太可怕了。
Dialogue: 0,0:41:13.76,0:41:16.80,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,The estate tax is just one aspect\N遗产税只是其中一个方面。
Dialogue: 0,0:41:16.80,0:41:18.94,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,First of all, right\N首先，没错
Dialogue: 0,0:41:18.94,0:41:21.80,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Back when grandparents were in their prime\N想当年祖父母正值壮年的时候
Dialogue: 0,0:41:21.80,0:41:23.46,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,bought that house\N买下了那栋房子
Dialogue: 0,0:41:23.46,0:41:25.61,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,have to pay property taxes for the house\N必须缴纳房屋房产税
Dialogue: 0,0:41:25.61,0:41:26.44,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,right\N正确的
Dialogue: 0,0:41:26.44,0:41:27.76,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,have to pay property taxes for the house\N必须缴纳房屋房产税
Dialogue: 0,0:41:27.76,0:41:30.21,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Then you have to send your child to the school district, right?\N那么你就得把孩子送到学区去上学，对吧？
Dialogue: 0,0:41:30.21,0:41:32.09,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,All these should help pay for the children's college tuition\N这些钱应该都能帮助支付孩子们的大学学费。
Dialogue: 0,0:41:32.09,0:41:34.40,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,All these things should be taken care of, right?\N这些事情都应该得到妥善处理，对吧？
Dialogue: 0,0:41:34.40,0:41:35.82,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Then what happens\N然后会发生什么？
Dialogue: 0,0:41:35.82,0:41:37.92,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Then the children all go to college\N然后孩子们都上大学。
Dialogue: 0,0:41:37.92,0:41:40.28,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Would he feel that the house is a bit empty like an empty nest\N他会不会觉得房子有点空荡荡的，像个空巢一样？
Dialogue: 0,0:41:40.28,0:41:41.44,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,the elderly feel empty and lonely\N老年人感到空虚和孤独
Dialogue: 0,0:41:41.44,0:41:42.90,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,It's too big to live in now, right?\N现在住起来太大了，对吧？
Dialogue: 0,0:41:42.90,0:41:44.42,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,living in a two or three hundred square meter house\N住在两三百平方米的房子里
Dialogue: 0,0:41:44.42,0:41:45.48,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,can't live in two\N不能住在两个地方
Dialogue: 0,0:41:45.48,0:41:47.71,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Why should I pay so much property tax for no reason?\N我为什么要无缘无故缴纳这么多房产税？
Dialogue: 0,0:41:47.71,0:41:50.80,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,A large portion of the property tax goes towards education, right?\N房产税的大部分都用于教育，对吧？
Dialogue: 0,0:41:50.80,0:41:53.00,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Then I'll just downsize a bit more\N那我再缩小一下规模吧。
Dialogue: 0,0:41:53.00,0:41:54.96,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Then I'll downsize a bit more\N那我再缩小一下规模吧。
Dialogue: 0,0:41:54.96,0:41:56.00,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Alas, my old partner is gone\N唉，我的老搭档已经不在了。
Dialogue: 0,0:41:56.00,0:41:57.36,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Let me switch to a smaller one\N我换个小点的。
Dialogue: 0,0:41:57.36,0:41:59.21,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,In the end, in the end, they had to move into a nursing home\N最后，最后，他们不得不搬进养老院。
Dialogue: 0,0:41:59.21,0:42:01.25,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,In the end, I'll just live in a nursing home.\N最终，我可能只能住在养老院了。
Dialogue: 0,0:42:01.25,0:42:02.98,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,There will still be blind spots in the front and back.\N前方和后方仍然会存在盲区。
Dialogue: 0,0:42:02.98,0:42:06.21,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,1shit and die, right\N1shit and die，对吧
Dialogue: 0,0:42:06.21,0:42:08.05,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,This term is definitely heard in the United States\N这个词在美国肯定有人听过。
Dialogue: 0,0:42:08.05,0:42:09.80,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,called eating and die\N被称为吃和死
Dialogue: 0,0:42:09.80,0:42:11.96,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,And then it's not, hey\N然后就不是这样了，嘿
Dialogue: 0,0:42:11.96,0:42:13.03,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Let me interject\N让我插一句
Dialogue: 0,0:42:13.03,0:42:14.07,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,what does this mean\N这是什么意思？
Dialogue: 0,0:42:14.07,0:42:14.84,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,I don't understand\N我不明白
Dialogue: 0,0:42:14.84,0:42:16.36,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Go eat shit\N去吃屎吧
Dialogue: 0,0:42:16.36,0:42:18.76,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Then you just die there, you old geezer, right?\N然后你就死在那儿了，你这老家伙，对吧？
Dialogue: 0,0:42:18.76,0:42:21.61,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,That's right, being blocked and spamming coins, spamming coins, huh?\N没错，被封号然后疯狂刷金币，疯狂刷金币，是吗？
Dialogue: 0,0:42:21.61,0:42:22.65,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Isn't this just landing\N这不就是着陆吗？
Dialogue: 0,0:42:22.65,0:42:24.15,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,just eat, shit, and wait to die\N吃喝拉撒，等死就完了
Dialogue: 0,0:42:24.15,0:42:25.42,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,just these three things\N仅此三件事
Dialogue: 0,0:42:25.42,0:42:27.11,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Eat, shit, and wait to die, hmm\N吃喝拉撒，等死，嗯。
Dialogue: 0,0:42:27.11,0:42:28.80,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,You have nothing else to do\N你无事可做
Dialogue: 0,0:42:28.80,0:42:32.73,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,And then all the money, you think how expensive labor is in the U.S.\N然后还有所有的钱，想想美国的劳动力成本有多高。
Dialogue: 0,0:42:32.73,0:42:34.28,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,How expensive is the land rent in the United States?\N美国的土地租金有多贵？
Dialogue: 0,0:42:34.28,0:42:39.51,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Do you think nursing homes in the U.S. are cheap, right?\N你觉得美国的养老院很便宜，对吗？
Dialogue: 0,0:42:39.51,0:42:41.82,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,You end up arriving naked and leaving naked\N你最终赤身裸体地来，也赤身裸体地离开。
Dialogue: 0,0:42:41.82,0:42:42.92,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,leave with nothing\N空手而归
Dialogue: 0,0:42:42.92,0:42:46.86,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,being completely exploited by society leaves nothing behind\N被社会彻底剥削，最终一无所有。
Dialogue: 0,0:42:46.86,0:42:48.78,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Your grandchildren won't inherit anything from you\N你的孙辈不会继承你的任何东西。
Dialogue: 0,0:42:48.78,0:42:50.38,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Yes\N是的
Dialogue: 0,0:42:51.42,0:42:54.46,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,those so-called Chuanbei Y, right\N那些所谓的川北 Y，对吧
Dialogue: 0,0:42:54.46,0:42:57.23,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,is that the family really has a considerable amount of property\N这个家庭确实拥有相当数量的财产。
Dialogue: 0,0:42:57.23,0:42:59.07,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,can be passed down from generation to generation\N可以代代相传
Dialogue: 0,0:42:59.07,0:43:00.07,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,and often have already\N而且通常已经有了
Dialogue: 0,0:43:00.07,0:43:02.92,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Now it is commonly passed down through trust forms.\N现在通常通过信托形式传承。
Dialogue: 0,0:43:02.92,0:43:05.55,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,That is indeed a minority, but it does exist.\N这确实是少数情况，但确实存在。
Dialogue: 0,0:43:05.55,0:43:07.40,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Many of my former classmates were like this\N我以前的很多同学都是这样的。
Dialogue: 0,0:43:07.40,0:43:09.73,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,But such cases are a minority in society as a whole\N但就整个社会而言，这类案例只占少数。
Dialogue: 0,0:43:09.73,0:43:12.30,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,the vast majority of people are\N绝大多数人
Dialogue: 0,0:43:13.51,0:43:18.48,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,will be completely, utterly, and thoroughly abandoned by the entire market economy society\N将被整个市场经济社会彻底、完全、彻底地抛弃。
Dialogue: 0,0:43:18.48,0:43:20.30,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,won't be burned to ashes\N不会被烧成灰烬
Dialogue: 0,0:43:24.46,0:43:27.09,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,In China, even if you're extremely poor, right?\N在中国，即使你非常贫穷，对吧？
Dialogue: 0,0:43:27.09,0:43:28.78,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,If your grandparents are from the countryside\N如果你的祖父母来自农村
Dialogue: 0,0:43:28.78,0:43:30.09,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,has a homestead\N拥有一处宅基地
Dialogue: 0,0:43:30.09,0:43:34.13,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Well, well, there are also guests outside who say you can go back home and farm.\N嗯，嗯，外面也有客人说你可以回家务农。
Dialogue: 0,0:43:34.13,0:43:35.28,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,You can really go back to farming\N你真的可以重操旧业了。
Dialogue: 0,0:43:35.28,0:43:36.73,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,That's right\N这是正确的
Dialogue: 0,0:43:36.73,0:43:38.26,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,And if you're a worker,\N如果你是一名工人，
Dialogue: 0,0:43:38.26,0:43:39.34,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,you were assigned a house back then\N当时你被分配了一套房子。
Dialogue: 0,0:43:39.34,0:43:40.18,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,WeChat payment\N微信支付
Dialogue: 0,0:43:40.18,0:43:42.44,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Many people think I'm already very poor in China.\N很多人认为我在中国已经很穷了。
Dialogue: 0,0:43:42.44,0:43:44.42,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,I only have a few thousand yuan in salary\N我只有几千元工资。
Dialogue: 0,0:43:44.42,0:43:46.63,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,My grandparents are just ordinary people.\N我的祖父母只是普通人。
Dialogue: 0,0:43:46.98,0:43:48.67,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Oh my\N哦，我的
Dialogue: 0,0:43:48.67,0:43:50.59,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Look at America\N看看美国
Dialogue: 0,0:43:50.59,0:43:52.61,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,nothing at all\N什么都没有
Dialogue: 0,0:43:52.61,0:43:54.88,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Let me read the SC\N让我读一下最高法院的判决。
Dialogue: 0,0:43:54.88,0:43:55.76,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Thank you Puppet\N谢谢你，木偶
Dialogue: 0,0:43:55.76,0:43:56.48,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Nothingness, my grand prize\N虚无，我的终极大奖
Dialogue: 0,0:43:56.48,0:43:57.48,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Will Lao Yi go back for the New Year?\N老义会回去过年吗？
Dialogue: 0,0:43:57.48,0:43:58.57,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Enjoy delicious food to your heart's content\N尽情享用美味佳肴
Dialogue: 0,0:43:58.57,0:43:59.57,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,I can't go back for the New Year.\N我回不去了，过不了新年。
Dialogue: 0,0:43:59.57,0:44:00.63,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,I have to finish my studies\N我必须完成学业
Dialogue: 0,0:44:00.63,0:44:02.32,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Thanks to Brother Finny for the reward\N感谢芬尼兄弟的奖励
Dialogue: 0,0:44:02.32,0:44:04.80,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Here in Serica, they keep talking about cutting medical insurance costs\N在塞里卡，他们一直在讨论削减医疗保险费用。
Dialogue: 0,0:44:04.80,0:44:05.78,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,divert patients\N分流病人
Dialogue: 0,0:44:05.78,0:44:08.22,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,alleviate the outpatient pressure on top-tier hospitals\N缓解顶级医院的门诊压力
Dialogue: 0,0:44:08.22,0:44:09.84,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,So what is the solution?\N那么解决方案是什么？
Dialogue: 0,0:44:09.84,0:44:12.86,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Strengthen the construction of primary medical institutions and infrastructure\N加强基层医疗机构和基础设施建设
Dialogue: 0,0:44:12.86,0:44:14.21,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,I'm not sure about other places\N我不确定其他地方的情况。
Dialogue: 0,0:44:14.21,0:44:15.26,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Jiangsu must also achieve\N江苏省也必须实现
Dialogue: 0,0:44:15.26,0:44:18.03,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,every township health center and community health service center is fully equipped with\N每个乡镇卫生中心和社区卫生服务中心都配备了齐全的……
Dialogue: 0,0:44:18.03,0:44:20.48,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,CT, DR, color ultrasound, and electrocardiogram\NCT、DR、彩色超声和心电图
Dialogue: 0,0:44:20.48,0:44:21.76,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,blood tests\N血液检查
Dialogue: 0,0:44:21.76,0:44:22.48,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,blood tests and such\N血液检查等等
Dialogue: 0,0:44:22.48,0:44:24.38,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Basic biochemistry tests are all done in-house\N基础生化检测均在院内完成。
Dialogue: 0,0:44:24.38,0:44:26.28,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Unable to perform, sent to external laboratory\N无法进行检测，已送至外部实验室。
Dialogue: 0,0:44:26.28,0:44:27.51,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,and then comprehensively reduce prices\N然后全面降低价格
Dialogue: 0,0:44:27.51,0:44:29.84,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,From examinations to lab tests to medications, complete localization of production\N从体检、实验室检测到药物治疗，生产完全本地化。
Dialogue: 0,0:44:29.84,0:44:30.36,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,slashed prices\N价格大幅下降
Dialogue: 0,0:44:30.36,0:44:31.48,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,When I first started working\N我刚开始工作的时候
Dialogue: 0,0:44:31.48,0:44:32.80,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,In 2017, a CT scan cost over 200\N2017 年，一次 CT 扫描的费用超过 200 美元。
Dialogue: 0,0:44:32.80,0:44:33.75,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,close to 300\N接近 300
Dialogue: 0,0:44:33.75,0:44:35.19,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Now the price has been slashed\N现在价格已经大幅下调。
Dialogue: 0,0:44:35.19,0:44:36.38,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,halved to 150\N减半至 150
Dialogue: 0,0:44:36.38,0:44:38.25,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,still a tier-3 hospital's remotely prescribed medication\N仍然是三级医院远程开具的处方药
Dialogue: 0,0:44:38.25,0:44:41.69,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,The chronic disease medication costs just a few cents per pill.\N这种慢性病药物每片只需几美分。
Dialogue: 0,0:44:41.69,0:44:44.13,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,So cheap that ordinary people doubt its effectiveness\N价格如此低廉，以至于普通人都怀疑它的有效性。
Dialogue: 0,0:44:44.13,0:44:47.69,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Thank you to Xiaofeng Han and Brother Lao for the reward, let me show you all\N感谢韩晓峰和老哥的奖励，让我来给大家展示一下。
Dialogue: 0,0:44:47.69,0:44:50.26,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,My father was treated for cancer in Guangzhou in 2024.\N2024 年，我父亲在广州接受了癌症治疗。
Dialogue: 0,0:44:50.26,0:44:51.57,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,the largest expense among them\N其中最大的一笔开支
Dialogue: 0,0:44:51.57,0:44:55.11,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,clearly reflects the extent of the government's investment and support in critical illness medical coverage\N这清楚地反映了政府在重大疾病医疗保险方面的投入和支持力度。
Dialogue: 0,0:44:55.14,0:44:57.26,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Except for some examinations and special personnel services\N除某些考试和特殊人事服务外
Dialogue: 0,0:44:57.26,0:44:59.14,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,It really tries to minimize costs for ordinary people.\N它确实努力为普通民众降低成本。
Dialogue: 0,0:45:00.38,0:45:04.11,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Because currently in China, the main focus is actually on examinations\N因为目前在中国，主要的关注点实际上是考试。
Dialogue: 0,0:45:04.11,0:45:08.59,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Well, actually, once the examination is done, everything will be easier to handle.\N其实，一旦考试结束，一切都会更容易处理。
Dialogue: 0,0:45:08.59,0:45:11.48,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,After the examination, you will find that once it is clearly identified\N检查之后，你会发现一旦它被明确识别出来。
Dialogue: 0,0:45:14.50,0:45:15.07,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,is a problem\N这是一个问题
Dialogue: 0,0:45:15.07,0:45:17.81,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Right now it's because the cost control has gone too far\N目前的问题在于成本控制过度了。
Dialogue: 0,0:45:17.81,0:45:21.21,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,so there's a bit of overcorrection uh\N所以有点矫枉过正了。
Dialogue: 0,0:45:21.21,0:45:24.00,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,I might have heard of something called DRG-based healthcare reform.\N我可能听说过一种叫做基于 DRG 的医疗改革。
Dialogue: 0,0:45:24.00,0:45:26.48,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,This is a policy imported from the United States\N这是从美国引进的一项政策。
Dialogue: 0,0:45:26.48,0:45:29.09,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,It makes doctors oh\N它让医生们哦
Dialogue: 0,0:45:29.09,0:45:30.69,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,I don't know what can be said about this\N我不知道对此还能说什么。
Dialogue: 0,0:45:30.69,0:45:31.88,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Can't say, can't say\N不能说，不能说
Dialogue: 0,0:45:31.88,0:45:34.86,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Anyway, the result is that sometimes there are certain choices\N总之，结果是，有时确实存在某些选择。
Dialogue: 0,0:45:34.86,0:45:36.03,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,some treatment options\N一些治疗方案
Dialogue: 0,0:45:36.03,0:45:39.03,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,the doctor will tell you\N医生会告诉你
Dialogue: 0,0:45:39.03,0:45:41.65,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,unless you go to those self-pay places\N除非你去那些自费的地方。
Dialogue: 0,0:45:41.65,0:45:43.76,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,those places and so on\N那些地方等等
Dialogue: 0,0:45:43.76,0:45:45.76,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,This comes back to you again\N这又回到了你身上。
Dialogue: 0,0:45:45.76,0:45:47.59,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,So this is why middle-class and above individuals\N所以这就是为什么中产阶级及以上人士
Dialogue: 0,0:45:47.59,0:45:48.67,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,You should damn well pay out of pocket\N你理应自掏腰包。
Dialogue: 0,0:45:48.67,0:45:50.98,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Please go for the self-paid special consultation\N请前往自费专项咨询处咨询。
Dialogue: 0,0:45:50.98,0:45:51.75,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,only 400 yuan\N仅需 400 元
Dialogue: 0,0:45:51.75,0:45:52.15,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,800 yuan\N800 元
Dialogue: 0,0:45:52.15,0:45:53.63,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,1500 yuan is enough to get an appointment with Zhong Nanshan\N花 1500 元就能约到钟南山医生。
Dialogue: 0,0:45:53.63,0:45:54.88,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,what else do you want\N你还想要什么？
Dialogue: 0,0:45:54.88,0:45:56.73,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Then let's take a look at\N那么我们来看看……
Dialogue: 0,0:45:56.73,0:45:59.84,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,You should not, you should not compete with the poor for money\N你不应该，你不应该和穷人争夺金钱。
Dialogue: 0,0:45:59.84,0:46:01.61,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Let me show you\N让我来给你展示一下。
Dialogue: 0,0:46:01.61,0:46:04.90,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,How many people went missing in the US this year?\N今年美国有多少人失踪？
Dialogue: 0,0:46:04.90,0:46:09.44,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Ah, this year in the US, no fewer than 530,000 people have gone missing.\N啊，今年美国已有不少于 53 万人失踪。
Dialogue: 0,0:46:09.44,0:46:10.21,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Great\N伟大的
Dialogue: 0,0:46:10.21,0:46:12.55,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,530,000 people are missing in the United States\N美国有 53 万人失踪
Dialogue: 0,0:46:12.55,0:46:14.92,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,53 legal residents\N53 名合法居民
Dialogue: 0,0:46:14.92,0:46:17.26,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,530,000 missing legal residents\N53 万失踪的合法居民
Dialogue: 0,0:46:17.26,0:46:18.40,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Not bad\N不错
Dialogue: 0,0:46:18.40,0:46:19.17,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Ah\N啊
Dialogue: 0,0:46:19.17,0:46:20.84,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,at its peak\N在其巅峰时期
Dialogue: 0,0:46:20.84,0:46:24.37,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,In 1997 alone, 980,000 people went missing.\N仅在 1997 年，就有 98 万人失踪。
Dialogue: 0,0:46:24.37,0:46:26.09,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Yes, it's the legal population\N是的，这是法定人口。
Dialogue: 0,0:46:26.09,0:46:27.81,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,excluding the illegal ones, bros\N兄弟们，非法的除外。
Dialogue: 0,0:46:27.81,0:46:30.90,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Although I think the decline in missing persons\N虽然我认为失踪人口数量的下降是原因之一
Dialogue: 0,0:46:30.90,0:46:35.21,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,It's because the statistical capability has declined.\N这是因为统计能力下降了。
Dialogue: 0,0:46:36.86,0:46:38.28,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,This is in the Yellow Register\N这在黄皮书登记册里。
Dialogue: 0,0:46:38.28,0:46:40.05,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,the registered population\N登记人口
Dialogue: 0,0:46:40.05,0:46:45.82,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,First of all, the missing person must be a legal resident\N首先，失踪人员必须是合法居民。
Dialogue: 0,0:46:45.82,0:46:48.44,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,and someone has to report him missing\N必须有人报告他失踪。
Dialogue: 0,0:46:48.44,0:46:49.96,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,on record\N有记录
Dialogue: 0,0:46:49.96,0:46:53.53,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Only then can he be considered a legitimate missing person\N只有这样，他才能被认定为合法失踪人员。
Dialogue: 0,0:46:55.61,0:46:58.80,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,How many illegal immigrants go missing each year?\N每年有多少非法移民失踪？
Dialogue: 0,0:46:58.80,0:47:02.67,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,That stuff isn't properly counted anyway\N那些东西本来就没被正确统计过。
Dialogue: 0,0:47:02.67,0:47:05.63,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,WeChat payment received 30 yuan\N微信支付收到 30 元
Dialogue: 0,0:47:05.63,0:47:07.05,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Someone said it's that scary\N有人说它很可怕。
Dialogue: 0,0:47:07.05,0:47:09.67,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Yeah, it's really that scary\N是啊，真的太可怕了。
Dialogue: 0,0:47:09.67,0:47:10.84,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Thanks to NEOK\N感谢 NEOK
Dialogue: 0,0:47:10.84,0:47:11.48,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Brother Hua tipped\N华哥小费
Dialogue: 0,0:47:11.48,0:47:13.86,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Let me take a look\N让我看看
Dialogue: 0,0:47:14.03,0:47:15.59,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Anchor, I have quite a bit to say\N安克尔，我有很多话要说。
Dialogue: 0,0:47:15.59,0:47:16.46,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Let me explain bit by bit\N让我一点一点地解释。
Dialogue: 0,0:47:16.46,0:47:17.23,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,First and foremost\N首先，也是最重要的
Dialogue: 0,0:47:17.23,0:47:19.06,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,This afternoon my younger brother told me\N今天下午，我弟弟告诉我
Dialogue: 0,0:47:19.06,0:47:20.50,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,He saw something online\N他在网上看到了一些东西。
Dialogue: 0,0:47:20.50,0:47:22.06,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,It's an article from Beijing Daily\N这是《北京日报》的一篇文章。
Dialogue: 0,0:47:22.06,0:47:24.66,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,The general idea is that we don't need to envy winning Nobel Prizes or the like.\N总的来说，我们不必羡慕获得诺贝尔奖之类的奖项。
Dialogue: 0,0:47:24.66,0:47:26.90,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Then some creatures appeared in the Douyin comment section\N然后抖音评论区出现了一些生物。
Dialogue: 0,0:47:26.90,0:47:29.63,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Then you say Serica can't see the grapes and calls them sour\N然后你说塞丽卡看不见葡萄，就说它们是酸的。
Dialogue: 0,0:47:29.63,0:47:30.55,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,sour grapes\N酸葡萄
Dialogue: 0,0:47:30.55,0:47:32.98,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,My brother's thinking was somewhat swayed by some comments.\N我哥哥的想法受到了一些评论的影响。
Dialogue: 0,0:47:32.98,0:47:34.11,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,I scolded my brother at that time\N那时我责骂了我哥哥
