Dialogue: 0,0:52:42.71,0:52:45.26,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Everyone finds it not difficult to produce after discovering this, right?\N发现这一点后，大家都觉得生产并不难，对吧？
Dialogue: 0,0:52:45.26,0:52:49.53,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,However, the purity and impurities of the active ingredients\N然而，活性成分的纯度和杂质
Dialogue: 0,0:52:49.53,0:52:53.94,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,The effect of your sustained-release agent is too poor.\N你的缓释剂效果太差。
Dialogue: 0,0:52:53.94,0:52:57.25,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Because you have different prices\N因为你们的价格不同
Dialogue: 0,0:52:57.25,0:53:00.17,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,It might be different, right?\N或许情况会有所不同，对吧？
Dialogue: 0,0:53:00.17,0:53:02.69,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,so I I I can't simply say\N所以，我不能简单地说
Dialogue: 0,0:53:02.69,0:53:04.80,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,is this one better or that one\N这个好还是那个好？
Dialogue: 0,0:53:04.80,0:53:08.89,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,But generally speaking, the more choices you have, the better, which is certainly fine.\N但总的来说，选择越多越好，这当然无可厚非。
Dialogue: 0,0:53:08.89,0:53:12.13,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,For me, the ideal situation is the ideal situation is\N对我来说，理想的情况就是……
Dialogue: 0,0:53:12.13,0:53:14.98,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,you can go to the best in the country\N你可以去全国最好的学校。
Dialogue: 0,0:53:14.98,0:53:18.84,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,when you can see a doctor and buy all the medicines worldwide\N当你可以看医生并购买全世界所有的药品时
Dialogue: 0,0:53:18.84,0:53:21.51,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,This is theoretically the most perfect.\N理论上这是最完美的。
Dialogue: 0,0:53:21.78,0:53:24.80,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,and when necessary, you can even go to the United States for something\N必要时，你甚至可以去美国做某事。
Dialogue: 0,0:53:24.80,0:53:26.61,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,those so-called online\N那些所谓的网络用户
Dialogue: 0,0:53:26.61,0:53:28.86,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,online multidisciplinary consultation, right\N在线多学科会诊，没错
Dialogue: 0,0:53:28.86,0:53:30.40,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,So this is theoretically the most perfect\N所以，从理论上讲，这是最完美的。
Dialogue: 0,0:53:30.40,0:53:32.86,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,But it requires money.\N但这需要钱。
Dialogue: 0,0:53:33.46,0:53:34.67,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,This healthcare in Greece\N希腊的医疗保健
Dialogue: 0,0:53:34.67,0:53:37.90,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Because here in Serica before in our place ah\N因为之前在塞里卡，在我们这里啊
Dialogue: 0,0:53:37.90,0:53:41.82,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Some people really went there but didn't get proper treatment\N有些人确实去了那里，但没有得到妥善治疗。
Dialogue: 0,0:53:41.82,0:53:43.30,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,not necessarily not cured\N不一定没治好。
Dialogue: 0,0:53:43.30,0:53:45.46,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,but they must return\N但他们必须返回
Dialogue: 0,0:53:45.46,0:53:47.17,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,the entire family\N全家
Dialogue: 0,0:53:47.17,0:53:49.32,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,the entire family has already collapsed because of this, right?\N整个家庭都因此而崩溃了，对吗？
Dialogue: 0,0:53:49.32,0:53:51.69,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Then it brings up another issue\N然后，它又引出了另一个问题。
Dialogue: 0,0:53:51.69,0:53:52.76,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Well, uh\N嗯，呃
Dialogue: 0,0:53:52.76,0:53:53.69,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,so it talks about\N所以它谈到了
Dialogue: 0,0:53:53.69,0:53:55.96,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Everyone's basic understanding of economics\N每个人都应该对经济学有基本的了解
Dialogue: 0,0:53:55.96,0:53:58.92,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,often overlook something called marginal cases\N常常忽略所谓的边缘情况
Dialogue: 0,0:53:58.92,0:53:59.48,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,that is to say\N也就是说
Dialogue: 0,0:53:59.48,0:54:03.30,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,It's about human needs\N这关乎人类的需求
Dialogue: 0,0:54:03.30,0:54:05.65,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Well, generally speaking, it's flexible.\N总的来说，它很灵活。
Dialogue: 0,0:54:05.65,0:54:09.30,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,but in some aspects, it is rigid\N但在某些方面，它又很僵硬。
Dialogue: 0,0:54:09.30,0:54:11.30,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,and extremely rigid\N非常刚硬
Dialogue: 0,0:54:11.30,0:54:13.36,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,So what is the most rigid thing?\N那么，最僵化的是什么？
Dialogue: 0,0:54:13.36,0:54:15.92,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,The most rigid things are survival and reproduction\N最根本的法则莫过于生存和繁衍。
Dialogue: 0,0:54:15.92,0:54:16.56,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,right?\N正确的？
Dialogue: 0,0:54:16.56,0:54:17.68,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,This is a human need\N这是人类的需求
Dialogue: 0,0:54:17.68,0:54:18.40,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,This is rigidity\N这是刚性
Dialogue: 0,0:54:18.40,0:54:19.04,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,That is to say\N也就是说
Dialogue: 0,0:54:19.04,0:54:23.39,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,If you push the possibility of this thing toward zero\N如果你把这件事发生的可能性降到零以下
Dialogue: 0,0:54:23.39,0:54:25.53,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,At this point, the party involved is willing to pay\N此时，相关方愿意支付费用。
Dialogue: 0,0:54:25.53,0:54:27.29,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,he can pay the highest price\N他可以付出最高的代价
Dialogue: 0,0:54:27.29,0:54:28.63,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,sell off three generations of the family\N卖掉三代家族财产
Dialogue: 0,0:54:28.63,0:54:29.39,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,he is willing\N他愿意
Dialogue: 0,0:54:29.39,0:54:30.23,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,You get it, right?\N你明白我的意思吧？
Dialogue: 0,0:54:30.23,0:54:32.73,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,It's this so-called highest salary demand, right?\N这就是所谓的最高薪资要求，对吧？
Dialogue: 0,0:54:32.73,0:54:33.80,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,This is why\N这就是原因
Dialogue: 0,0:54:33.80,0:54:35.94,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,anything involving these rigid medical needs\N任何涉及这些严格医疗需求的事情
Dialogue: 0,0:54:35.94,0:54:38.42,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,This has been proven by the practice of human society\N人类社会的实践已经证明了这一点。
Dialogue: 0,0:54:38.42,0:54:39.69,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,must be regulated by the government\N必须由政府监管
Dialogue: 0,0:54:39.69,0:54:41.17,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,For example, let me give an extreme example\N例如，让我举一个极端的例子。
Dialogue: 0,0:54:41.17,0:54:43.63,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,There is no such demand in itself\N本身并不存在这样的需求。
Dialogue: 0,0:54:43.63,0:54:45.19,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,but the person who proposed it was very happy\N但求婚的那个人非常高兴
Dialogue: 0,0:54:45.19,0:54:48.44,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,booster booster, right\N增压器，右边
Dialogue: 0,0:54:48.44,0:54:49.96,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,So the state has to use\N所以国家必须使用
Dialogue: 0,0:54:52.30,0:54:54.65,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,I won't allow this thing to become a rigid demand, right?\N我不会让这件事变成硬性要求，对吧？
Dialogue: 0,0:54:54.65,0:54:56.01,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,No matter what Naxida says, ah\N不管纳克西达说什么，啊
Dialogue: 0,0:54:56.01,0:54:58.21,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Is it everyone's own willpower that makes the choice?\N每个人做出选择都是依靠自己的意志力吗？
Dialogue: 0,0:54:58.21,0:54:59.53,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Bullshit, right?\N胡说八道，对吧？
Dialogue: 0,0:54:59.53,0:55:01.19,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Then then then this is is\N然后，然后，这就是了。
Dialogue: 0,0:55:01.19,0:55:02.55,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Does this violate the fundamental principles of economics?\N这是否违反了经济学的基本原理？
Dialogue: 0,0:55:02.55,0:55:03.34,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Actually, it's\N实际上，是
Dialogue: 0,0:55:03.34,0:55:04.30,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,And then\N进而
Dialogue: 0,0:55:04.30,0:55:07.61,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,For example, let's talk about something that might be more relatable to everyone.\N例如，我们来谈谈一些大家更容易产生共鸣的话题。
Dialogue: 0,0:55:07.61,0:55:09.50,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Why monogamy, right?\N为什么是一夫一妻制呢？
Dialogue: 0,0:55:09.50,0:55:10.17,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,because of monogamy\N因为一夫一妻制
Dialogue: 0,0:55:10.17,0:55:13.53,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,This is also a rigid human need for reproduction\N这也是人类繁衍后代的根本需求。
Dialogue: 0,0:55:13.53,0:55:14.76,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,is a fundamental human need\N这是人类的基本需求
Dialogue: 0,0:55:14.76,0:55:17.30,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,You're not even giving him this little bit of hope\N你连这点希望都不给他。
Dialogue: 0,0:55:17.30,0:55:19.61,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,History has proven that this will lead to trouble.\N历史已经证明，这样做会招致麻烦。
Dialogue: 0,0:55:19.61,0:55:22.61,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Therefore, the vast majority of civilized societies throughout history and across the world have made this choice.\N因此，纵观历史，世界各地绝大多数文明社会都做出了这样的选择。
Dialogue: 0,0:55:22.61,0:55:23.90,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,So if neither of these can be done\N所以如果这两种方法都行不通的话
Dialogue: 0,0:55:23.90,0:55:25.90,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,So where else can we\N那么我们还能去哪里呢？
Dialogue: 0,0:55:25.90,0:55:27.63,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,squeeze every last drop of profit out of a person\N榨干一个人身上最后一滴利润
Dialogue: 0,0:55:27.63,0:55:28.63,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Hmph, ah\N哼，啊
Dialogue: 0,0:55:28.63,0:55:31.04,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,That would definitely be education\N那绝对算是教育。
Dialogue: 0,0:55:31.04,0:55:34.16,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Because education is essentially the reproduction of social class, right?\N因为教育本质上是社会阶级的再生产，对吧？
Dialogue: 0,0:55:34.16,0:55:35.73,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,for example, um, buying a house\N例如，嗯，买房
Dialogue: 0,0:55:35.73,0:55:37.63,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Because buying a house is also related to reproduction, right?\N因为买房也与繁衍后代有关，对吧？
Dialogue: 0,0:55:37.63,0:55:39.59,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,However, these two matters are not entirely without solutions.\N然而，这两个问题并非完全没有解决办法。
Dialogue: 0,0:55:39.59,0:55:42.30,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Because after all, you might indeed have a privileged child, right?\N毕竟，你的孩子很可能确实过着优渥的生活，对吧？
Dialogue: 0,0:55:42.30,0:55:43.05,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,no education required\N无需学历
Dialogue: 0,0:55:43.05,0:55:44.61,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,you can graduate from Tsinghua or Peking University\N你可以从清华大学或北京大学毕业。
Dialogue: 0,0:55:44.61,0:55:48.30,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,that that that uh what's it called house\N那，那，呃，它叫什么来着，房子
Dialogue: 0,0:55:48.30,0:55:49.42,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,That's not necessarily the case.\N情况未必如此。
Dialogue: 0,0:55:49.42,0:55:51.86,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Actually, renting a house isn't that unlivable, right?\N其实租房住并没有那么糟糕，对吧？
Dialogue: 0,0:55:51.86,0:55:54.92,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Then then then what's left, what's the matter\N然后，然后，还剩下什么？到底出了什么问题？
Dialogue: 0,0:55:54.92,0:55:58.40,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,is the situation where a person is pushed to their absolute limit when facing death\N是指一个人在面临死亡时被推向极限的情况。
Dialogue: 0,0:55:58.40,0:55:59.59,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,It's best not to die instantly\N最好不要立刻死去。
Dialogue: 0,0:55:59.59,0:56:00.48,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,preferably chronic\N最好是慢性
Dialogue: 0,0:56:00.48,0:56:03.44,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,It can also repeatedly extract every last drop from you, right?\N它还能反复榨干你身上的每一滴水，对吧？
Dialogue: 0,0:56:03.44,0:56:04.63,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Think about it, so hard to figure out\N想想看，这太难搞清楚了。
Dialogue: 0,0:56:04.63,0:56:05.75,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,What could this possibly be?\N这究竟是什么？
Dialogue: 0,0:56:05.75,0:56:06.55,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Ah, right\N啊，对
Dialogue: 0,0:56:06.55,0:56:11.03,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Then then then whether this thing is regulated or unregulated\N然后，还要考虑这件事是否受到监管。
Dialogue: 0,0:56:11.03,0:56:13.51,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,This is completely two different things.\N这是两码事。
Dialogue: 0,0:56:13.51,0:56:19.15,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Absolutely, it just can't be, you can't let him think things through successfully\N绝对不行，绝对不能让他把事情想清楚。
Dialogue: 0,0:56:19.71,0:56:22.40,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,At the very least, its foundation cannot be based on a market economy.\N至少，它的基础不能建立在市场经济之上。
Dialogue: 0,0:56:23.40,0:56:25.00,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,If you follow Xi Da's approach like this\N如果你像这样遵循席达的方法
Dialogue: 0,0:56:25.00,0:56:27.07,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,You even leave the basics to the market economy\N你甚至把最基本的要素都交给了市场经济。
Dialogue: 0,0:56:27.07,0:56:27.98,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Let me tell you\N让我告诉你
Dialogue: 0,0:56:27.98,0:56:29.11,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Why am I telling you\N我为什么要告诉你这些？
Dialogue: 0,0:56:29.11,0:56:31.71,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Why was the CEO of United Health executed\N联合健康集团首席执行官为何被处决
Dialogue: 0,0:56:31.71,0:56:33.31,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Everyone applauded and cheered\N众人鼓掌欢呼。
Dialogue: 0,0:56:33.31,0:56:35.87,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Because his claim denial rate is the highest in the United States\N因为他的理赔拒赔率是全美最高的。
Dialogue: 0,0:56:35.87,0:56:37.97,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,I looked it up, it's 55% uh\N我查了一下，是 55%。
Dialogue: 0,0:56:37.97,0:56:39.81,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,It has now reached 60%.\N目前已达到 60%。
Dialogue: 0,0:56:39.81,0:56:41.52,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,It has increased, hasn't it\N确实增加了，不是吗？
Dialogue: 0,0:56:41.52,0:56:42.78,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Holy shit\N我的天啊
Dialogue: 0,0:56:42.78,0:56:44.94,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Because because because because they want to withdraw\N因为因为他们想退出
Dialogue: 0,0:56:44.94,0:56:48.73,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Because more people are canceling their insurance policies.\N因为越来越多的人取消了他们的保险单。
Dialogue: 0,0:56:48.73,0:56:51.55,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,So they have to squeeze more from a limited number of people, right?\N所以他们必须从有限的人身上榨取更多价值，对吧？
Dialogue: 0,0:56:51.55,0:56:53.76,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,More people are canceling their insurance, haha\N越来越多的人取消了保险，哈哈
Dialogue: 0,0:56:53.76,0:56:56.17,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Aren't they afraid of getting shot?\N他们难道不怕被枪击吗？
Dialogue: 0,0:56:56.17,0:56:57.07,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,I'm curious\N我很好奇
Dialogue: 0,0:56:57.07,0:56:58.88,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,So I say again\N所以我再说一遍
Dialogue: 0,0:56:58.88,0:57:00.23,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,I don't understand American politics.\N我不了解美国政治。
Dialogue: 0,0:57:00.23,0:57:02.00,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,This still requires more input from people knowledgeable about US politics.\N这仍然需要更多了解美国政治的人士提供意见。
Dialogue: 0,0:57:02.00,0:57:03.32,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,But then again\N但话又说回来……
Dialogue: 0,0:57:03.32,0:57:05.90,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,the abolition of the ACA\N废除《平价医疗法案》
Dialogue: 0,0:57:05.90,0:57:13.57,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,It must just be the fantasy of some radical conservatives.\N这一定是某些极端保守派的幻想。
Dialogue: 0,0:57:13.57,0:57:17.80,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,or even including many fans themselves unwilling to do it\N甚至包括许多不愿这样做的粉丝在内
Dialogue: 0,0:57:17.80,0:57:21.09,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Then the boss, the owner is the one who most doesn't want to do it\N然后，老板，也就是所有者，是最不愿意做这件事的人。
Dialogue: 0,0:57:21.09,0:57:22.67,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,They have the greatest parallel willingness\N他们拥有最强的平行意愿
Dialogue: 0,0:57:22.67,0:57:24.15,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Really? Oh, is that so?\N真的吗？哦，是这样吗？
Dialogue: 0,0:57:24.15,0:57:26.73,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,ACA is a classic case of A4\NACA 是 A4 的一个典型案例。
Dialogue: 0,0:57:26.73,0:57:29.57,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,AC is a typical case of doing more but earning less\NAC 是一个典型的付出更多却收入更少的例子。
Dialogue: 0,0:57:30.29,0:57:32.71,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,And then the members inside are all acting wildly.\N然后，里面的成员们都开始疯狂行事。
Dialogue: 0,0:57:32.71,0:57:33.76,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Just imagine\N试想一下
Dialogue: 0,0:57:33.76,0:57:35.23,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,ACE has illegal immigrants\NACE 有非法移民
Dialogue: 0,0:57:35.23,0:57:36.36,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,LGBT\NLGBT
Dialogue: 0,0:57:36.36,0:57:37.15,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,with DEI\N具有多元化、公平和包容性
Dialogue: 0,0:57:37.15,0:57:41.19,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,There are all sorts of demons and monsters mixed in there\N里面混杂着各种各样的恶魔和怪物。
Dialogue: 0,0:57:41.67,0:57:45.86,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Even you capitalists don't want to deal with these people\N就连你们这些资本家都不想跟这些人打交道。
Dialogue: 0,0:57:45.86,0:57:46.84,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,You know what\N你知道吗
Dialogue: 0,0:57:46.84,0:57:49.38,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,That's enough then\N那就足够了。
Dialogue: 0,0:57:50.44,0:57:53.19,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,So, this perfect storm in the coming months\N所以，未来几个月可能会出现这种完美风暴。
Dialogue: 0,0:57:53.19,0:57:54.71,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,I I really don't know why\N我真的不知道为什么
Dialogue: 0,0:57:54.71,0:57:55.15,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Of course\N当然
Dialogue: 0,0:57:55.15,0:57:57.11,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,I hope we're being alarmist\N我希望我们是在危言耸听。
Dialogue: 0,0:57:57.11,0:57:57.92,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Hopefully it's just alarmist talk\N希望这只是危言耸听。
Dialogue: 0,0:57:57.92,0:58:00.86,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,But I think among these few things\N但我认为，在这几件事中，最重要的是……
Dialogue: 0,0:58:00.86,0:58:04.78,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Based on my understanding of the previous abundance of food under Xi's leadership\N根据我对习近平领导时期粮食供应充足的了解，
Dialogue: 0,0:58:04.78,0:58:07.34,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,I think it should be fine\N我觉得应该没问题。
Dialogue: 0,0:58:07.34,0:58:09.51,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,on the basis of milk being so cheap elsewhere\N鉴于其他地方的牛奶价格如此低廉。
Dialogue: 0,0:58:09.51,0:58:12.63,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,It's not like they can't get anything to eat at all.\N他们并非完全没有东西吃。
Dialogue: 0,0:58:12.63,0:58:15.83,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Well, electricity isn't exactly doubling in price, right?\N嗯，电价总不至于翻倍吧？
Dialogue: 0,0:58:15.83,0:58:17.76,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,But when it comes to healthcare\N但就医疗保健而言，
Dialogue: 0,0:58:17.76,0:58:20.84,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,talking about the ACA today for the middle and lower class\N今天我们来谈谈《平价医疗法案》（ACA）对中低收入阶层的影响。
Dialogue: 0,0:58:20.84,0:58:23.80,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,If it's eight or ten times higher\N如果高出八倍或十倍
Dialogue: 0,0:58:23.80,0:58:25.30,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,This has really caused quite a few incidents, hasn't it?\N这确实引发了不少事件，不是吗？
Dialogue: 0,0:58:25.30,0:58:27.57,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,I don't know what kind of things would happen\N我不知道会发生什么事。
Dialogue: 0,0:58:27.57,0:58:32.76,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,But this really makes you imagine if you were in a situation where\N但这真的会让你想象，如果你身处这样的境地：
Dialogue: 0,0:58:32.76,0:58:36.59,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,that is to say, because of this treasure gathering producing that uh\N也就是说，因为这次宝藏的收集产生了那个呃
Dialogue: 0,0:58:36.59,0:58:39.44,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,the practice of occupying certain institutions\N占领某些机构的做法
Dialogue: 0,0:58:39.44,0:58:40.57,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,I don't know, I don't know\N我不知道，我不知道
Dialogue: 0,0:58:40.57,0:58:41.69,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Let me correct a term\N让我纠正一个术语
Dialogue: 0,0:58:41.69,0:58:44.78,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Denial of coverage means the insurance company refuses to insure you.\N拒保是指保险公司拒绝为你提供保险。
Dialogue: 0,0:58:44.78,0:58:46.26,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,which means unable to claim money\N这意味着无法领取赔偿金
Dialogue: 0,0:58:46.26,0:58:47.34,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Unable to receive treatment, right?\N无法接受治疗，对吗？
Dialogue: 0,0:58:47.34,0:58:51.18,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Claim denial, claim denial!\N索赔被拒，索赔被拒！
Dialogue: 0,0:58:51.54,0:58:53.38,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Well, I don't know about this.\N嗯，我对此并不了解。
Dialogue: 0,0:58:53.38,0:58:54.90,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,I can hardly imagine what kind of situation it is\N我简直无法想象那会是什么样的情况。
Dialogue: 0,0:58:54.90,0:58:56.10,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,As far as I know\N据我所知
Dialogue: 0,0:58:56.10,0:58:56.98,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,in this regard\N在这方面
Dialogue: 0,0:58:56.98,0:58:58.92,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Americans have always been very submissive.\N美国人一直都很顺从。
Dialogue: 0,0:58:58.92,0:59:00.30,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,they have a specific term\N他们有一个特定的术语
Dialogue: 0,0:59:00.30,0:59:03.26,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,that is to say, it's like saying\N也就是说，这就像说
Dialogue: 0,0:59:03.26,0:59:06.01,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,If you can't even afford your own dr.bill\N如果你连自己的医生账单都付不起的话。
Dialogue: 0,0:59:06.01,0:59:08.17,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,it's a very shameful thing\N这是一件非常可耻的事情。
Dialogue: 0,0:59:08.17,0:59:10.30,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,It's something that can't even be mentioned openly.\N这是连公开提及都不能说的事情。
Dialogue: 0,0:59:10.30,0:59:13.11,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,It's like I've never even been out there, hey\N感觉就像我从未去过那里一样，嘿
Dialogue: 0,0:59:13.11,0:59:14.76,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,China's first case due to medical expenses\N中国首例因医疗费用导致的病例
Dialogue: 0,0:59:14.76,0:59:16.55,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Who was that person who caused a big stir?\N那个引起轩然大波的人是谁？
Dialogue: 0,0:59:16.55,0:59:17.28,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Let me think about it\N让我想想。
Dialogue: 0,0:59:17.28,0:59:18.68,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,It seems to be the late Eastern Han Dynasty, right?\N看起来像是东汉晚期，对吗？
Dialogue: 0,0:59:18.68,0:59:21.24,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,What was that person's name again?\N那个人叫什么名字来着？
Dialogue: 0,0:59:21.24,0:59:22.84,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,No, I really forgot, it's like writer's block.\N不，我真的忘了，就像写作遇到瓶颈一样。
Dialogue: 0,0:59:22.84,0:59:25.05,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Like the S3 brothers, right?\N就像 S3 兄弟那样，对吧？
Dialogue: 0,0:59:25.05,0:59:26.84,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Was it Zhang Jiao and those guys?\N是张娇他们那帮人吗？
Dialogue: 0,0:59:27.92,0:59:30.25,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Yeah, they can cure diseases, right?\N是的，它们可以治愈疾病，对吧？
Dialogue: 0,0:59:30.25,0:59:31.53,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,They can actually treat ascites\N他们实际上可以治疗腹水。
Dialogue: 0,0:59:31.53,0:59:35.71,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,In the history of Europe and America, there has never been such a person.\N在欧洲和美国的历史上，从来没有过这样的人。
Dialogue: 0,0:59:35.71,0:59:38.46,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Not even one.\N一个也没有。
Dialogue: 0,0:59:38.86,0:59:40.30,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Not a single one to my knowledge\N据我所知，一个也没有。
Dialogue: 0,0:59:40.30,0:59:44.92,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Not a single one, not even Zhang Jiao, ah\N一个也没有，连张娇也没有，啊
Dialogue: 0,0:59:45.88,0:59:47.59,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,I really\N我真的
Dialogue: 0,0:59:47.59,0:59:50.44,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Sometimes I think the title of that film is\N有时我觉得那部电影的片名是
Dialogue: 0,0:59:50.44,0:59:51.23,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,increasingly simple and unadorned\N越来越简单朴素
Dialogue: 0,0:59:51.23,0:59:52.67,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,The Silence of the Lambs\N沉默的羔羊
Dialogue: 0,0:59:52.67,0:59:55.42,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Just you putting this kind of stuff out there\N你竟然把这种东西公之于众
Dialogue: 0,0:59:55.42,0:59:57.98,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,This would be intolerable in Serica, haha\N这在塞里卡是绝对无法容忍的，哈哈
Dialogue: 0,0:59:57.98,1:00:00.25,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,There's this meme called, uh,\N有个梗叫做，呃，
Dialogue: 0,1:00:00.25,1:00:01.76,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,just raise both hands\N举起双手
Dialogue: 0,1:00:01.76,1:00:02.84,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Can't take it anymore\N我再也受不了了
Dialogue: 0,1:00:02.84,1:00:03.80,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Blow them up\N把它们炸掉
Dialogue: 0,1:00:07.57,1:00:08.61,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Ah, I can't take it anymore\N啊，我再也受不了了。
Dialogue: 0,1:00:08.61,1:00:09.86,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,punch the Earth into smithereens\N把地球打成碎片
Dialogue: 0,1:00:10.53,1:00:14.30,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,So I find myself in this position of, uh, selflessly saving all humanity\N所以我发现自己身处这样的境地，呃，要无私地拯救全人类。
Dialogue: 0,1:00:14.30,1:00:16.19,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,as well as for selfish purposes\N以及出于自私的目的
Dialogue: 0,1:00:16.19,1:00:20.61,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Still, I would suggest Alex to, uh, get to know more female classmates, right?\N不过，我还是建议 Alex 多认识一些女同学，对吧？
Dialogue: 0,1:00:20.61,1:00:22.42,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Ah, more development, no, oh dear\N啊，又有新进展了，不，哦，天哪
Dialogue: 0,1:00:22.42,1:00:23.46,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Don't you dare act wild\N你敢胡闹试试
Dialogue: 0,1:00:23.46,1:00:25.34,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,You're serious, right, right?\N你是认真的，对吧？
Dialogue: 0,1:00:25.34,1:00:27.42,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,They are facing financial difficulties\N他们面临财务困难
Dialogue: 0,1:00:27.42,1:00:30.83,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,They don't know much about the University of Tokyo, right?\N他们对东京大学了解不多，对吧？
Dialogue: 0,1:00:30.83,1:00:32.23,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Now there's also visa-free entry\N现在也实行免签入境了。
Dialogue: 0,1:00:32.23,1:00:33.39,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,that advises you\N给你的建议
Dialogue: 0,1:00:33.39,1:00:35.27,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,You should also consider your future career development\N你也应该考虑一下未来的职业发展。
Dialogue: 0,1:00:35.27,1:00:36.93,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,this path to wealth\N这条致富之路
Dialogue: 0,1:00:36.93,1:00:37.57,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,right\N正确的
Dialogue: 0,1:00:37.57,1:00:40.96,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,a new path to wealth, lying down\N一条通往财富的新途径，躺下
Dialogue: 0,1:00:40.96,1:00:44.23,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Or maybe his father is called, uh\N或许他父亲的名字叫……呃
Dialogue: 0,1:00:44.23,1:00:45.03,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,a gambling-addicted father\N一个沉迷赌博的父亲
Dialogue: 0,1:00:45.03,1:00:46.44,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,sick mother, right?\N母亲生病了，对吗？
Dialogue: 0,1:00:46.44,1:00:48.26,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Uh, whatever, right\N呃，随便吧，对吧
Dialogue: 0,1:00:48.26,1:00:51.15,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Perhaps they have urgent needs\N或许他们有紧急需求
Dialogue: 0,1:00:51.15,1:00:52.71,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,needs rescue\N需要救援
Dialogue: 0,1:00:52.71,1:00:53.80,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,That's right\N这是正确的
Dialogue: 0,1:00:53.80,1:00:56.53,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,You can't possibly pay out of your own pocket to save everyone, right?\N你不可能自掏腰包去拯救所有人，对吧？
Dialogue: 0,1:00:56.53,1:00:59.17,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,You, you, you could develop a business in this area, right?\N你，你，你可以在这个领域发展事业，对吧？
Dialogue: 0,1:00:59.17,1:00:59.48,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Right?\N正确的？
Dialogue: 0,1:01:04.13,1:01:04.55,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Thank you\N谢谢
Dialogue: 0,1:01:04.55,1:01:05.28,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Sorry up\N抱歉
Dialogue: 0,1:01:05.28,1:01:05.90,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,act like a fool\N像个傻瓜一样
Dialogue: 0,1:01:05.90,1:01:07.53,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Because they believe in Jesus.\N因为他们信奉耶稣。
Dialogue: 0,1:01:07.53,1:01:09.78,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,What kind of person are you\N你是什​​么样的人？
Dialogue: 0,1:01:09.78,1:01:10.40,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,You are\N你是
Dialogue: 0,1:01:10.40,1:01:11.55,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,So you're a Protestant\N所以你是新教徒
Dialogue: 0,1:01:11.55,1:01:14.44,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,At that time, I understood.\N那时我明白了。
Dialogue: 0,1:01:14.44,1:01:17.61,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,That's fine then, hmm\N那没问题，嗯。
Dialogue: 0,1:01:19.46,1:01:20.69,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Ah yes\N啊，是的
Dialogue: 0,1:01:20.69,1:01:23.46,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,And also, speaking of this treasure trove\N还有，说到这个宝库……
Dialogue: 0,1:01:23.46,1:01:26.82,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,This is about another terrifying aspect of American insurance.\N这是美国保险业另一个令人恐惧的方面。
Dialogue: 0,1:01:26.82,1:01:29.36,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Do you think claim denial is already terrifying enough?\N你觉得被拒赔已经够可怕的了吗？
Dialogue: 0,1:01:29.36,1:01:31.11,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Many times, the insurance simply denies coverage.\N很多时候，保险公司会直接拒绝赔付。
Dialogue: 0,1:01:31.11,1:01:34.19,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,When does rejection usually occur?\N拒绝通常发生在什么情况下？
Dialogue: 0,1:01:34.19,1:01:37.55,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,It happens in certain professions, you know.\N你知道，这种情况在某些行业会发生。
Dialogue: 0,1:01:37.55,1:01:39.48,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Why do they deny coverage?\N他们为什么拒绝承保？
Dialogue: 0,1:01:39.48,1:01:40.46,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Simply put\N简而言之
Dialogue: 0,1:01:41.46,1:01:46.17,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,that is, certain technical jobs\N也就是说，某些技术性工作
Dialogue: 0,1:01:46.17,1:01:49.11,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,upon reaching a certain age or under certain circumstances\N达到一定年龄或在特定情况下
Dialogue: 0,1:01:49.11,1:01:51.63,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,they won't cover you anymore\N他们不会再为你提供保险了。
Dialogue: 0,1:01:51.96,1:01:55.58,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Some say isn't this something the company provides insurance for?\N有人说，这难道不是公司会提供保险的吗？
Dialogue: 0,1:01:55.58,1:01:59.73,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,But what does the company base its insurance coverage on?\N但该公司的保险范围是基于什么呢？
Dialogue: 0,1:01:59.73,1:02:01.90,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,For example, electricians\N例如，电工
Dialogue: 0,1:02:01.90,1:02:02.80,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,climbing utility poles\N爬电线杆
Dialogue: 0,1:02:02.80,1:02:03.80,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Everyone has seen it, right?\N大家都看过了吧？
Dialogue: 0,1:02:03.80,1:02:05.84,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,electricians\N电工
Dialogue: 0,1:02:05.84,1:02:08.67,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,He needs an electrician's license.\N他需要一张电工执照。
Dialogue: 0,1:02:08.67,1:02:13.07,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Those power companies base their decisions on the electrician's certification.\N这些电力公司会根据电工的资格证书来做决定。
Dialogue: 0,1:02:13.07,1:02:17.06,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,with this certificate in hand can you go to the insurance company\N凭这份证明，你可以去保险公司。
Dialogue: 0,1:02:17.06,1:02:21.28,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,purchase his industry-specific insurance\N购买他所在行业的保险
Dialogue: 0,1:02:21.28,1:02:22.63,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,one license\N一张许可证
Dialogue: 0,1:02:22.63,1:02:23.50,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,an insurance policy\N保险单
Dialogue: 0,1:02:23.50,1:02:25.48,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,No license, no insurance\N无驾照，无保险
Dialogue: 0,1:02:26.92,1:02:28.48,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Some people say isn't this quite good\N有人说，这难道不是相当不错吗？
Dialogue: 0,1:02:28.48,1:02:31.50,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Well, here comes the problem.\N问题就在这里。
Dialogue: 0,1:02:31.50,1:02:36.13,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,The insurance for professionals is many times that of ordinary individuals.\N专业人士的保险费用是普通人的数倍。
Dialogue: 0,1:02:36.13,1:02:36.78,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Some people say\N有人说
Dialogue: 0,1:02:36.78,1:02:39.01,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,So how much can one actually receive?\N那么一个人实际能收到多少钱呢？
Dialogue: 0,1:02:39.01,1:02:40.07,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Let me put it this way\N让我这样说吧
Dialogue: 0,1:02:40.07,1:02:44.82,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,If an ordinary person's accident insurance costs $100 per month\N如果普通人的意外保险每月费用为 100 美元。
Dialogue: 0,1:02:44.82,1:02:46.63,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,if you're an electrician\N如果你是一名电工
Dialogue: 0,1:02:46.63,1:02:49.36,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,The cost can even reach $500\N费用甚至可能高达 500 美元。
Dialogue: 0,1:02:49.36,1:02:50.15,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,600 dollars\N600 美元
Dialogue: 0,1:02:50.15,1:02:51.30,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,$700\N700 美元
Dialogue: 0,1:02:51.30,1:02:52.98,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Do you understand my concept?\N你理解我的意思吗？
Dialogue: 0,1:02:52.98,1:02:53.94,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Do you understand this concept?\N你理解这个概念吗？
Dialogue: 0,1:02:53.94,1:02:56.26,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,That is, if you are an electrician\N也就是说，如果你是一名电工
Dialogue: 0,1:02:56.26,1:02:58.55,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Primary, intermediate, advanced, or specialized, no matter what?\N无论是初级、中级、高级还是专业，都一样？
Dialogue: 0,1:02:58.55,1:03:01.03,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,your premiums are skyrocketing\N你的保费飙升了
Dialogue: 0,1:03:01.03,1:03:02.98,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,exponentially increasing\N指数级增长
Dialogue: 0,1:03:02.98,1:03:05.73,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,perhaps an ordinary young person your age\N或许你只是一个和你同龄的普通年轻人。
Dialogue: 0,1:03:05.73,1:03:07.73,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,his premium would be eighty to one hundred\N他的保费大概是八十到一百。
Dialogue: 0,1:03:07.73,1:03:11.34,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,you might have to pay five or six hundred, even seven or eight hundred\N你可能要付五六百，甚至七八百。
Dialogue: 0,1:03:11.76,1:03:14.21,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,This amount of money, right?\N就是这个数额的钱，对吧？
Dialogue: 0,1:03:14.21,1:03:15.94,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Basically, it's all covered by the company.\N基本上，所有费用都由公司承担。
Dialogue: 0,1:03:15.94,1:03:18.61,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,If you are a full-time employee\N如果您是全职员工
Dialogue: 0,1:03:20.09,1:03:23.27,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Some people say then part-time workers don't need to buy it, right?\N有人说，兼职员工就不需要购买了，对吗？
Dialogue: 0,1:03:23.27,1:03:25.53,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Part-time workers don't need to buy it\N兼职员工无需购买。
Dialogue: 0,1:03:25.53,1:03:26.71,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,but there will be penalties\N但会有处罚。
Dialogue: 0,1:03:26.71,1:03:31.36,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,because if there's an issue with this kind of specialized technical operation\N因为如果这种专业技术操作出现问题……
Dialogue: 0,1:03:31.36,1:03:33.44,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,found that insurance was not purchased\N发现并未购买保险。
Dialogue: 0,1:03:33.44,1:03:34.94,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,will be fined severely\N将受到严厉罚款
Dialogue: 0,1:03:34.94,1:03:39.30,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,So he actually doesn't dare to mess around too much\N所以他其实不敢太过放肆。
Dialogue: 0,1:03:39.30,1:03:41.65,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,However, there is racial discrimination involved.\N然而，其中涉及种族歧视。
Dialogue: 0,1:03:42.84,1:03:44.82,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,What is racial discrimination?\N什么是种族歧视？
Dialogue: 0,1:03:44.82,1:03:48.98,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,The electrician license in the U.S. is for electricians\N美国的电工执照是颁发给电工的。
Dialogue: 0,1:03:48.98,1:03:52.61,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,A Mexican electrician's license is also an electrician's license.\N墨西哥的电工执照也是电工执照。
Dialogue: 0,1:03:53.65,1:03:59.32,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,The North American economic and trade integration has brought about many aspects\N北美经济和贸易一体化带来了诸多方面的影响。
Dialogue: 0,1:03:59.32,1:04:01.38,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,including academic credential recognition\N包括学历证书认可
Dialogue: 0,1:04:01.38,1:04:03.57,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,including certification authentication\N包括证书认证
Dialogue: 0,1:04:03.57,1:04:05.98,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Do you know what I mean?\N你明白我的意思吗？
Dialogue: 0,1:04:06.26,1:04:10.05,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Why should I hire an American electrician?\N我为什么要聘请美国电工？
Dialogue: 0,1:04:11.26,1:04:15.75,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Are Mexican electricians not good enough? Ah\N墨西哥的电工技术不够好吗？啊
Dialogue: 0,1:04:15.75,1:04:19.75,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Hey, old A, I wanted to ask about the work-related injury insurance at Western University\N嘿，老 A，我想问问西安大略大学的工伤保险。
Dialogue: 0,1:04:19.75,1:04:22.25,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Can work-related injury insurance usually be claimed, ah?\N通常情况下，工伤保险可以理赔吗？
Dialogue: 0,1:04:22.25,1:04:24.46,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Work injury insurance is almost the most difficult to claim.\N工伤保险几乎是最难索赔的。
Dialogue: 0,1:04:24.46,1:04:26.82,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,that is, you almost as if\N也就是说，你几乎就像
Dialogue: 0,1:04:26.82,1:04:29.07,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,even if you have surveillance footage\N即使你有监控录像
Dialogue: 0,1:04:29.07,1:04:33.48,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,it's also difficult to prove whether it was due to your own operational error\N而且也很难证明这是否是由于你自身的操作失误造成的。
Dialogue: 0,1:04:33.48,1:04:35.28,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,resulting in an accidental incident\N导致意外事故
Dialogue: 0,1:04:37.36,1:04:40.61,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Oh no no no no, not to the commerce bureau\N哦不不不不，千万别去商务局
Dialogue: 0,1:04:40.61,1:04:42.44,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,You say yes to all these first\N你首先对所有这些都说“是”。
Dialogue: 0,1:04:42.44,1:04:44.46,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Because here in our place\N因为在这里，在我们这里
Dialogue: 0,1:04:44.46,1:04:48.17,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,In our line of work, as long as you can say it happened\N在我们这行，只要你能说这件事发生过就行。
Dialogue: 0,1:04:48.17,1:04:50.63,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,is the problem that occurred during work\N这是工作中出现的问题。
Dialogue: 0,1:04:50.63,1:04:51.73,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,most can be reimbursed\N大部分费用都可以报销。
Dialogue: 0,1:04:51.73,1:04:55.63,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,It's not like the vast majority can absolutely get reimbursed.\N绝大多数人并非都能获得全额赔偿。
Dialogue: 0,1:04:55.63,1:04:56.84,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Absolutely not\N绝对不是
Dialogue: 0,1:04:56.84,1:05:01.51,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Well, anyway, as for industrial and commercial insurance, I know how it works in China.\N总之，至于工商业保险，我知道它在中国是如何运作的。
Dialogue: 0,1:05:01.51,1:05:03.48,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,but in China, accident insurance\N但在中国，意外保险
Dialogue: 0,1:05:03.48,1:05:06.25,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,It's the relationship between the insurance company and the individual, right?\N这是保险公司和个人之间的关系，对吧？
Dialogue: 0,1:05:06.25,1:05:07.36,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,because of industry and commerce\N因为工商业
Dialogue: 0,1:05:07.36,1:05:09.61,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,especially when it involves special categories of occupations such as Class 3 or Class 4 jobs\N尤其当涉及特殊类别的职业，例如三级或四级工作时更是如此。
Dialogue: 0,1:05:09.61,1:05:10.36,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,like electricians\N比如电工
Dialogue: 0,1:05:10.36,1:05:11.92,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,things like working at heights\N比如高空作业
Dialogue: 0,1:05:11.92,1:05:14.82,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,the claims for these things require\N这些要求需要
Dialogue: 0,1:05:14.82,1:05:19.57,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,First, it needs to be assessed by the local human resources and social security department\N首先，需要由当地人力资源和社会保障部门进行评估。
Dialogue: 0,1:05:20.23,1:05:21.32,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,then it will be covered\N然后它就会被覆盖。
Dialogue: 0,1:05:21.32,1:05:26.88,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,That is to say, the first step is to report the case to the human resources and social security department, um, ah.\N也就是说，第一步是向人力资源和社会保障部门报告此案，嗯，啊。
Dialogue: 0,1:05:26.88,1:05:29.04,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,so uh further compensation\N所以，呃，进一步的补偿
Dialogue: 0,1:05:29.04,1:05:29.96,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,it is definitely there\N它肯定在那里。
Dialogue: 0,1:05:29.96,1:05:32.89,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,This is not something the insurance company can decide, okay?\N这并非保险公司可以决定的事情，明白吗？
Dialogue: 0,1:05:32.89,1:05:36.25,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,It is intervened by the higher-level authorities.\N此事由上级部门介入。
Dialogue: 0,1:05:38.33,1:05:41.03,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Um, uh, sir\N嗯，呃，先生
Dialogue: 0,1:05:41.03,1:05:41.55,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,I would like to ask\N我想问
Dialogue: 0,1:05:41.55,1:05:45.36,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Does this Workers' Compensation Insurance from Xida have\N西达提供的这份工伤赔偿保险有吗？
Dialogue: 0,1:05:45.36,1:05:47.73,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,that is to say, there is a time limit\N也就是说，是有时间限制的。
Dialogue: 0,1:05:47.73,1:05:52.57,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,That is to say, how long after the injury can you report it to be considered valid?\N也就是说，受伤后多久才能报案才算有效？
Dialogue: 0,1:05:52.57,1:05:54.82,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,There is usually a time limit for that\N通常会有时间限制。
Dialogue: 0,1:05:54.82,1:05:57.76,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Each industry is different\N每个行业的情况都不尽相同。
Dialogue: 0,1:05:57.76,1:05:59.90,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,But there is a time limit for it.\N但这样做是有时间限制的。
Dialogue: 0,1:05:59.90,1:06:00.92,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Let me finish speaking\N让我说完。
Dialogue: 0,1:06:00.92,1:06:05.86,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Someone said that, uh, uh, uh, uh, that certification is from me, let me read the SC\N有人说，呃，呃，呃，呃，那份证明是我出的，让我看看 SC（最高法院）的记录。
Dialogue: 0,1:06:05.86,1:06:07.11,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Thanks to Brother Zhen for the generous reward\N感谢甄哥的慷慨赏赐
Dialogue: 0,1:06:07.11,1:06:07.82,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Add more damn pictures\N多加点该死的图片
Dialogue: 0,1:06:07.82,1:06:09.42,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,It feels like we've covered tonight's topic pretty thoroughly.\N感觉我们今晚的话题已经讨论得相当透彻了。
Dialogue: 0,1:06:09.42,1:06:10.46,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Yesterday I came across something\N昨天我偶然发现了一些东西
Dialogue: 0,1:06:10.46,1:06:12.98,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,This cover really gave me a huge shock.\N这个封面真的让我大吃一惊。
Dialogue: 0,1:06:12.98,1:06:17.90,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,What Old A called the 'American fake smile' is probably this kind, huh?\N老 A 所说的“美国式假笑”大概就是这种吧？
Dialogue: 0,1:06:17.90,1:06:19.88,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Let me show you guys, alright\N让我给你们演示一下，好吗？
Dialogue: 0,1:06:19.88,1:06:24.57,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,It's even more terrifying compared to this\N比这更可怕
Dialogue: 0,1:06:24.57,1:06:25.50,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,He lacks sunshine\N他缺乏阳光
Dialogue: 0,1:06:25.50,1:06:29.63,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,It's just not that kind of California-style rare three-fan illusion\N这并非加州那种罕见的三扇扇幻觉
Dialogue: 0,1:06:29.63,1:06:31.19,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,This fake smile is pretty average.\N这种假笑很普通。
Dialogue: 0,1:06:31.19,1:06:34.32,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,It doesn't look that creepy.\N看起来没那么吓人。
Dialogue: 0,1:06:34.32,1:06:37.13,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,There are much more terrifying fake smiles than this, right?\N还有比这更可怕的假笑呢，对吧？
Dialogue: 0,1:06:37.13,1:06:38.86,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Let me show you, okay\N让我来给你演示一下，好吗？
Dialogue: 0,1:06:38.86,1:06:41.05,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,How fake can his illusions be\N他的幻觉究竟有多么虚假？
Dialogue: 0,1:06:45.73,1:06:48.38,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,In the U.S., insurance doesn't pay out like this.\N在美国，保险赔付并非如此。
Dialogue: 0,1:06:48.38,1:06:53.19,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Sigh, some people say the probability of such claim denials is high\N唉，有人说这种索赔被拒的概率很高。
Dialogue: 0,1:06:53.19,1:06:54.92,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Then do you still have to buy it?\N那你还一定要买吗？
Dialogue: 0,1:06:54.92,1:06:56.05,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Mandatory purchase\N强制购买
Dialogue: 0,1:06:56.05,1:06:57.46,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,not allowed to join the union\N不允许加入工会
Dialogue: 0,1:06:57.46,1:07:01.17,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,They are in cahoots with the unions.\N他们与工会勾结。
Dialogue: 0,1:07:01.17,1:07:04.26,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Someone said, 'Can I buy a cheaper one?' No, you can't.\N有人问：“我可以买个便宜点的吗？” 不，你不能。
Dialogue: 0,1:07:04.26,1:07:06.67,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Because the union has already set the rules\N因为工会已经制定了规则。
Dialogue: 0,1:07:06.67,1:07:09.67,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,what kind of insurance you can buy from which company\N你可以从哪家公司购买哪种保险
Dialogue: 0,1:07:09.67,1:07:11.71,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,You have no freedom of choice\N你没有选择的自由。
Dialogue: 0,1:07:11.71,1:07:13.30,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Do you know what I mean?\N你明白我的意思吗？
Dialogue: 0,1:07:13.30,1:07:15.78,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,that is, you cannot choose\N也就是说，你不能选择
Dialogue: 0,1:07:15.78,1:07:17.15,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,What insurance did you buy\N你买了什么保险？
Dialogue: 0,1:07:17.15,1:07:19.01,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,you're in this industry\N你身处这个行业
Dialogue: 0,1:07:19.01,1:07:20.67,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,the union in this industry\N该行业的工会
Dialogue: 0,1:07:20.67,1:07:24.89,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,has already completed a purchasing agreement with a certain health insurance company\N已与某健康保险公司签订采购协议
Dialogue: 0,1:07:24.89,1:07:26.89,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,they had already made a deal\N他们已经达成协议了。
Dialogue: 0,1:07:26.89,1:07:27.85,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,sold you out\N出卖了你
Dialogue: 0,1:07:27.85,1:07:30.81,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,You simply have no choice\N你别无选择
Dialogue: 0,1:07:34.55,1:07:41.26,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Got it\N知道了
Dialogue: 0,1:07:41.26,1:07:42.65,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,you simply can't choose\N你根本无法选择
Dialogue: 0,1:07:43.73,1:07:46.01,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,You want to freely choose an insurance plan\N你想自由选择保险计划
Dialogue: 0,1:07:46.01,1:07:46.67,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Sorry\N对不起
Dialogue: 0,1:07:46.67,1:07:48.26,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,The union doesn't recognize it\N工会不承认它
Dialogue: 0,1:07:51.15,1:07:53.26,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Yes, that's his freedom\N是的，那是他的自由
Dialogue: 0,1:07:53.26,1:07:55.88,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,You need to consider those local Putian-style hospitals\N你需要考虑一下莆田式的本地医院。
Dialogue: 0,1:07:55.88,1:07:58.69,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Which insurance companies are good, right?\N哪些保险公司比较好？
Dialogue: 0,1:07:58.69,1:08:00.96,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Don't say that you're covered for something on the East Coast\N别说你在东海岸有保险。
Dialogue: 0,1:08:00.96,1:08:02.69,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,you're on the West Coast\N你现在在西海岸
Dialogue: 0,1:08:03.46,1:08:06.90,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Well, uh, oh my, this is extremely fragmented\N呃，我的天，这太零散了。
Dialogue: 0,1:08:06.90,1:08:08.59,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Everyone has their own means of making a living.\N每个人都有自己的谋生手段。
Dialogue: 0,1:08:08.59,1:08:10.56,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,And everyone must not forget\N每个人都不能忘记
Dialogue: 0,1:08:10.56,1:08:16.78,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Everything we're discussing today is just the damn healthcare line.\N我们今天讨论的一切都只是该死的医保线。
Dialogue: 0,1:08:16.78,1:08:20.02,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,You should know that in the East\N你应该知道，在东方
Dialogue: 0,1:08:20.02,1:08:23.97,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Medical insurance is the cheapest among all types of insurance.\N在所有保险类型中，医疗保险是最便宜的。
Dialogue: 0,1:08:23.97,1:08:25.63,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,critical illness insurance\N重大疾病保险
Dialogue: 0,1:08:25.63,1:08:26.81,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,life insurance\N人寿保险
Dialogue: 0,1:08:26.81,1:08:28.19,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,annuity insurance\N年金保险
Dialogue: 0,1:08:28.19,1:08:29.13,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,dividend insurance\N分红保险
Dialogue: 0,1:08:29.13,1:08:31.14,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,We haven't even mentioned a single word yet\N我们甚至连一个字都没提过。
Dialogue: 0,1:08:31.14,1:08:34.38,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Well, the problem for the American people is\N嗯，美国人民面临的问题是……
Dialogue: 0,1:08:34.38,1:08:35.94,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,just for health insurance alone\N仅仅为了医疗保险
Dialogue: 0,1:08:35.94,1:08:37.50,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,he can already barely afford it\N他本来就几乎负担不起。
Dialogue: 0,1:08:37.50,1:08:43.18,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,So for us Easterners, the middle class is struggling with\N所以对我们东方人来说，中产阶级正面临着……
Dialogue: 0,1:08:43.18,1:08:44.06,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,should buy or not\N买还是不买
Dialogue: 0,1:08:44.06,1:08:45.80,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,which one is cost-effective or not\N哪种更划算？
Dialogue: 0,1:08:45.80,1:08:47.74,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,This is not a luxury they can afford\N这是他们负担不起的奢侈品。
Dialogue: 0,1:08:47.74,1:08:49.44,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,can afford the luxury to consider\N有能力承担考虑这种奢侈的后果
Dialogue: 0,1:08:49.44,1:08:55.77,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,The problem is that's something only decent people can talk about, right?\N问题是，只有正派的人才能谈论这种话题，对吧？
Dialogue: 0,1:08:55.77,1:08:58.57,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,It's something only decent people can talk about.\N只有正派的人才能谈论这种话题。
Dialogue: 0,1:08:59.39,1:09:01.23,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Hey boss, I have another question\N老板，我还有个问题
Dialogue: 0,1:09:01.23,1:09:03.71,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,I used to read that before\N我以前读过那篇文章。
Dialogue: 0,1:09:03.71,1:09:05.21,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,also read those Yi Lin\N也读了那些易林的文章
Dialogue: 0,1:09:05.21,1:09:06.59,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,I also saw that before\N我之前也看到过。
Dialogue: 0,1:09:06.59,1:09:08.17,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Those books say things like uh\N那些书里会说一些类似“呃……”之类的话。
Dialogue: 0,1:09:08.17,1:09:10.43,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,The Greeks are particularly good at donating money.\N希腊人特别擅长捐款。
Dialogue: 0,1:09:10.43,1:09:11.68,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,What is this issue\N这是什么问题？
Dialogue: 0,1:09:11.68,1:09:12.82,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Is this still happening now?\N现在这种情况还在发生吗？
Dialogue: 0,1:09:12.82,1:09:14.18,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,that is to say, they donated to show me\N也就是说，他们捐款是为了让我看到
Dialogue: 0,1:09:14.18,1:09:16.47,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,What are they saying? Oh right, the injured ones.\N他们在说什么？哦，对了，是受伤的人。
Dialogue: 0,1:09:16.47,1:09:18.64,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,that is, the so-called donation to the injured\N也就是说，就是所谓的向伤者捐款
Dialogue: 0,1:09:18.64,1:09:22.82,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,it's just that, how should I put it\N就是这样，该怎么说呢？
Dialogue: 0,1:09:22.82,1:09:26.82,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,This is a form of mutual assistance within the community.\N这是社区内的一种互助形式。
Dialogue: 0,1:09:26.82,1:09:30.03,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,In essence, it is the entire society\N从本质上讲，它就是整个社会
Dialogue: 0,1:09:30.03,1:09:32.57,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,a manifestation of the complete failure of the government\N这是政府彻底失败的体现。
Dialogue: 0,1:09:32.57,1:09:34.46,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,self-regulation\N自我调节
Dialogue: 0,1:09:34.46,1:09:35.69,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Do you know what I mean?\N你明白我的意思吗？
Dialogue: 0,1:09:35.69,1:09:37.38,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Uh-huh, got it\N嗯，明白了。
Dialogue: 0,1:09:37.38,1:09:40.26,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Well, well, no one can help anymore\N唉，唉，已经没人能帮上忙了。
Dialogue: 0,1:09:40.26,1:09:44.18,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Simply put, the government is ineffective.\N简而言之，政府效率低下。
Dialogue: 0,1:09:44.18,1:09:45.73,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Companies show no humanity\N企业毫无人性可言。
Dialogue: 0,1:09:45.73,1:09:48.10,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,The insurance companies are predatory\N保险公司是掠夺性的。
Dialogue: 0,1:09:48.10,1:09:50.18,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Let's help each other out\N让我们互相帮助吧
Dialogue: 0,1:09:51.18,1:09:52.96,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Do you know what I mean?\N你明白我的意思吗？
Dialogue: 0,1:09:52.96,1:09:57.51,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,This is clearly a manifestation of government dysfunction.\N这显然是政府失职的表现。
Dialogue: 0,1:09:58.88,1:10:03.71,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,They shamelessly hype it up as some kind of mutual aid among people\N他们厚颜无耻地将其吹捧为人们之间的一种互助行为。
Dialogue: 0,1:10:03.71,1:10:05.97,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,There is true love among people\N人与人之间存在着真爱。
Dialogue: 0,1:10:05.97,1:10:07.22,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,I'm so awesome\N我太棒了
Dialogue: 0,1:10:07.22,1:10:08.51,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,think these people are awesome\N我觉得这些人太棒了
Dialogue: 0,1:10:08.51,1:10:09.02,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,You know what\N你知道吗
Dialogue: 0,1:10:09.02,1:10:10.65,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,boasting about this kind of thing\N吹嘘这种事
Dialogue: 0,1:10:11.02,1:10:13.06,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Because what did they eat back then?\N他们那时候都吃什么呢？
Dialogue: 0,1:10:13.06,1:10:17.67,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Look at how Greece does it, you see, once someone gets injured,\N你看看希腊是怎么做的，一旦有人受伤，
Dialogue: 0,1:10:17.67,1:10:19.88,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,so everyone helps each other, right\N所以大家都会互相帮助，对吧？
Dialogue: 0,1:10:19.88,1:10:21.15,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Look at how others are doing\N看看其他人是怎么做的。
Dialogue: 0,1:10:21.15,1:10:23.35,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,I have also participated in such mutual aid meetings\N我也曾参加过类似的互助会议。
Dialogue: 0,1:10:23.35,1:10:25.56,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,I went to help a redneck brother\N我去帮一个乡巴佬兄弟。
Dialogue: 0,1:10:25.56,1:10:27.35,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,His son was also in this situation\N他的儿子也面临同样的情况。
Dialogue: 0,1:10:27.35,1:10:28.56,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,You know\N你知道
Dialogue: 0,1:10:33.02,1:10:34.42,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Everyone gathers together\N大家聚集在一起
Dialogue: 0,1:10:34.42,1:10:38.01,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,People in a community participate in mutual aid meetings\N社区居民参加互助会议
Dialogue: 0,1:10:38.01,1:10:40.32,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Whose child has encountered what kind of misfortune\N谁的孩子遭遇了什么样的不幸
Dialogue: 0,1:10:40.32,1:10:41.97,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,what kind of disaster has befallen them\N他们遭遇了什么样的灾难？
Dialogue: 0,1:10:41.97,1:10:42.75,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,How is the situation now\N现在情况如何？
Dialogue: 0,1:10:42.75,1:10:43.88,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,How much money is needed\N需要多少钱
Dialogue: 0,1:10:43.88,1:10:45.10,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,what supplies are needed\N需要哪些物资
Dialogue: 0,1:10:45.10,1:10:49.35,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Everyone pitching in already brings us very close to the state of primitive humans.\N大家齐心协力已经使我们非常接近原始人类的状态。
Dialogue: 0,1:10:49.35,1:10:50.26,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,You know what\N你知道吗
Dialogue: 0,1:10:50.26,1:10:52.52,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,That's not about food, right\N那跟食物无关，对吧？
Dialogue: 0,1:10:52.52,1:10:54.93,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,It's when someone has that, no, not an undercover agent\N就是当有人拥有那种能力的时候，不，不是卧底特工。
Dialogue: 0,1:10:54.93,1:10:56.14,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Everyone come out and lend a hand\N大家都出来帮忙吧！
Dialogue: 0,1:10:56.14,1:10:59.09,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,No more, wow, okay\N好了，没事了。
Dialogue: 0,1:10:59.09,1:11:01.69,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,It's just that primitive.\N它就是这么原始。
Dialogue: 0,1:11:01.69,1:11:03.10,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Thanks to Haoyue's Dream\N感谢昊岳之梦
Dialogue: 0,1:11:03.10,1:11:03.77,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Red Brother's big reward\N红兄弟的大奖励
Dialogue: 0,1:11:03.77,1:11:04.73,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Chinese-style sweet girl\N中国风甜美女孩
Dialogue: 0,1:11:04.73,1:11:07.30,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,American-style modern production girls\N美式现代制作女孩
Dialogue: 0,1:11:09.00,1:11:14.11,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Oh wow, this is just too classic, isn't it?\N哇，这简直太经典了，不是吗？
Dialogue: 0,1:11:14.68,1:11:15.31,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Come on\N快点
Dialogue: 0,1:11:15.31,1:11:17.26,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Some say sunshine fake yang yang\N有人说阳光是假阳阳
Dialogue: 0,1:11:17.26,1:11:18.11,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,sunny and cheerful\N阳光明媚，心情愉快
Dialogue: 0,1:11:18.11,1:11:19.56,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,What does a fake smile girl look like\N一个笑容虚假的女孩长什么样？
Dialogue: 0,1:11:19.56,1:11:22.59,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Let me show you a more classic example of the 'Dream of the Bright Moon'.\N让我给你展示一个更经典的“明月之梦”的例子。
Dialogue: 0,1:11:22.59,1:11:24.02,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,This picture from the Hongbao Pavilion is fucking\N这张红包阁的照片真是太他妈棒了
Dialogue: 0,1:11:24.02,1:11:24.75,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,I'm not\N我不是
Dialogue: 0,1:11:24.75,1:11:28.93,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,China's Five-Year Economic Plan The China Show\N中国五年经济计划 中国展
Dialogue: 0,1:11:32.38,1:11:33.38,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Take a look\N看看
Dialogue: 0,1:11:35.53,1:11:36.65,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Ah\N啊
Dialogue: 0,1:11:42.61,1:11:44.34,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,planning\N规划
Dialogue: 0,1:11:49.11,1:11:51.96,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Oh, sometimes even sages and great men\N哦，有时就连圣贤和伟人也会如此。
Dialogue: 0,1:11:51.96,1:11:53.47,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Yes\N是的
Dialogue: 0,1:11:55.68,1:11:59.88,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Well, is this kind of mutual aid association effective sometimes?\N那么，这种互助组织有时真的有效吗？
Dialogue: 0,1:11:59.88,1:12:01.00,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,not very good\N不太好
Dialogue: 0,1:12:01.00,1:12:02.73,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,If it weren't for my penicillin\N如果不是因为我用了青霉素
Dialogue: 0,1:12:02.73,1:12:05.06,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,And if it weren't for my antibiotics, right\N如果不是因为抗生素，对吧？
Dialogue: 0,1:12:05.06,1:12:06.11,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,redneck buddy\N乡巴佬哥们
Dialogue: 0,1:12:06.11,1:12:07.68,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,his son wouldn't have survived either\N他的儿子也活不下来。
Dialogue: 0,1:12:07.68,1:12:10.00,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,I provided a lot of meat, right?\N我提供了很多肉，对吧？
Dialogue: 0,1:12:10.00,1:12:11.72,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Those are all secondary.\N这些都是次要的。
Dialogue: 0,1:12:11.72,1:12:14.26,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,The most important thing is penicillin, right?\N最重要的是青霉素，对吧？
Dialogue: 0,1:12:14.26,1:12:18.53,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Taking antibiotics made me feel much better.\N服用抗生素后我感觉好多了。
Dialogue: 0,1:12:20.14,1:12:22.43,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,This doesn't even look human anymore.\N这看起来完全不像人类了。
Dialogue: 0,1:12:22.43,1:12:25.97,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Then you think it just doesn't look human, alright\N那你就会觉得它看起来不像人类，好吧。
Dialogue: 0,1:12:30.06,1:12:32.69,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Someone said this is talking so much about the boss, hmm\N有人说这话里有很多关于老板的意味，嗯。
Dialogue: 0,1:12:32.69,1:12:35.65,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,20 I noticed they really like tanning.\N20 我注意到他们真的很喜欢晒日光浴。
Dialogue: 0,1:12:35.65,1:12:38.03,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Because for white people, it's about being wealthy\N因为对白人来说，一切都关乎财富。
Dialogue: 0,1:12:38.03,1:12:41.68,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,A sign of being a middle-class white person is getting a tan.\N晒黑是中产阶级白人的标志之一。
Dialogue: 0,1:12:42.89,1:12:47.72,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,If you don't get a tan, it makes you look poor.\N如果你没晒黑，会显得你很穷。
Dialogue: 0,1:12:47.72,1:12:50.28,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Thanks to Cool Old Goose for the reward\N感谢 Cool Old Goose 的奖励
Dialogue: 0,1:12:50.28,1:12:51.78,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Their system\N他们的系统
Dialogue: 0,1:12:51.78,1:12:54.56,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Why does it feel like the situation in Region A is much more severe than in our country?\N为什么感觉 A 区的情况比我们国家严重得多？
Dialogue: 0,1:12:54.56,1:12:55.60,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,What do you think?\N你怎么认为？
Dialogue: 0,1:12:55.60,1:12:58.93,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,I'm from Henan. In the early years, people from other places often called me a manhole cover thief.\N我来自河南。早年间，外地人常叫我“井盖小偷”。
Dialogue: 0,1:12:58.93,1:13:01.63,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,But in recent years, I feel they just tease like this\N但近年来，我觉得他们只是这样戏弄人。
Dialogue: 0,1:13:01.63,1:13:02.98,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,even when introducing themselves\N即使在自我介绍时也是如此
Dialogue: 0,1:13:02.98,1:13:05.22,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,they would also say I'm from the place where manhole covers are stolen\N他们还会说我来自一个井盖经常被偷的地方。
Dialogue: 0,1:13:05.22,1:13:08.39,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Because regional discrimination in China is relatively mild.\N因为中国的地域歧视现象相对较轻。
Dialogue: 0,1:13:08.39,1:13:11.76,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Your American regional discrimination is the most terrifying.\N你们美国人对美国地域的歧视是最可怕的。
Dialogue: 0,1:13:12.11,1:13:15.30,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Someone asked how terrifying it could be\N有人问这到底有多可怕。
Dialogue: 0,1:13:15.89,1:13:19.46,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,American consortiums are all named after regions\N美国所有财团都以地区命名。
Dialogue: 0,1:13:24.26,1:13:24.93,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,You know what I mean\N你知道我的意思
Dialogue: 0,1:13:24.93,1:13:27.80,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,even if some consortiums don't have the name on them\N即使有些财团没有署名
Dialogue: 0,1:13:27.80,1:13:31.92,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,but essentially they are also initiated based on regions\N但本质上，它们也是根据地区而发起的。
Dialogue: 0,1:13:31.92,1:13:35.42,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,They are everywhere, just like those 'transportation brigade leaders', you know?\N他们无处不在，就像那些“运输队队长”一样，你知道吗？
Dialogue: 0,1:13:35.42,1:13:37.15,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Ah, right, right\N啊，对，对
Dialogue: 0,1:13:37.15,1:13:38.39,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Let me say it again\N让我再说一遍
Dialogue: 0,1:13:38.39,1:13:40.18,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Right, speaking of hell\N对了，说到地狱
Dialogue: 0,1:13:40.18,1:13:41.57,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,You should know that\N你应该知道这一点
Dialogue: 0,1:13:41.57,1:13:44.93,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,For example, if you work in different professions across different states\N例如，如果你在不同州从事不同的职业。
Dialogue: 0,1:13:44.93,1:13:48.46,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,For example, if you work as an electrician in Washington State\N例如，如果你在华盛顿州从事电工工作。
Dialogue: 0,1:13:48.46,1:13:49.88,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,to California\N到加利福尼亚
Dialogue: 0,1:13:49.88,1:13:51.74,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,your insurance has to be changed\N你的保险需要更改。
Dialogue: 0,1:13:51.74,1:13:57.85,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,because the local unions in California and the insurance companies in California\N因为加州的当地工会和加州的保险公司
Dialogue: 0,1:13:57.85,1:13:58.71,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,colluded\N串通
Dialogue: 0,1:13:58.71,1:14:00.60,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,you change jobs\N你换工作了
Dialogue: 0,1:14:00.60,1:14:04.21,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,you have to change your insurance\N你必须更换你的保险
Dialogue: 0,1:14:04.21,1:14:05.40,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,If you can\N如果可以的话
Dialogue: 0,1:14:05.40,1:14:08.27,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,If you can still stay within the coverage area of your original insurance company\N如果你还能继续留在原保险公司的承保范围内的话
Dialogue: 0,1:14:08.27,1:14:09.55,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,within the coverage area\N在覆盖范围内
Dialogue: 0,1:14:09.55,1:14:13.84,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,You don't need to once you're out of their coverage area\N一旦你离开他们的服务范围，就不需要了。
Dialogue: 0,1:14:13.84,1:14:17.52,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,You'd better switch to another one.\N你最好换一个。
Dialogue: 0,1:14:17.52,1:14:20.35,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,I would like to ask, in this particular situation\N我想问，在这种特殊情况下
Dialogue: 0,1:14:20.35,1:14:24.02,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,If it's just an internal company transfer to another region\N如果只是公司内部调动到其他地区
Dialogue: 0,1:14:24.02,1:14:25.02,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Is this also necessary\N这也有必要吗？
Dialogue: 0,1:14:25.02,1:14:28.08,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Yeah, ah, yes, yes, there is\N是的，啊，是的，是的，有
Dialogue: 0,1:14:28.08,1:14:29.10,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,And let me tell you all\N让我来告诉你们这一切
Dialogue: 0,1:14:29.10,1:14:32.60,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,1:14:32.60,1:14:34.97,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Why would anyone still buy it?\N为什么还会有人买它？
Dialogue: 0,1:14:34.97,1:14:36.73,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,It's forcibly bundled\N它是被强制捆绑的
Dialogue: 0,1:14:36.73,1:14:38.06,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,You know what\N你知道吗
Dialogue: 0,1:14:38.06,1:14:40.21,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,your company in this state\N贵公司在该州
Dialogue: 0,1:14:40.21,1:14:43.32,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,In reality, most of the time you have no choice.\N事实上，大多数时候你别无选择。
Dialogue: 0,1:14:43.32,1:14:45.44,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,you don't provide this for your employees\N你没有为你的员工提供这项服务。
Dialogue: 0,1:14:45.44,1:14:46.68,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,he has no other choice\N他别无选择
Dialogue: 0,1:14:46.68,1:14:48.42,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Do you know what I mean?\N你明白我的意思吗？
Dialogue: 0,1:14:48.42,1:14:51.47,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,it's like you're right\N你说的没错。
Dialogue: 0,1:14:51.47,1:14:54.46,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,It seems like you have choices\N看来你有很多选择。
Dialogue: 0,1:14:54.46,1:14:58.06,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,In fact, you don't have different industries\N事实上，你们并没有不同的行业。
Dialogue: 0,1:14:58.06,1:15:01.32,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,has already been carved up by different insurance companies\N已被不同的保险公司瓜分。
Dialogue: 0,1:15:01.32,1:15:03.38,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Do you understand what I mean?\N你明白我的意思吗？
Dialogue: 0,1:15:03.38,1:15:06.18,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,You actually have no choice but to buy\N你实际上别无选择，只能购买。
Dialogue: 0,1:15:08.76,1:15:09.84,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Do you know what I mean?\N你明白我的意思吗？
Dialogue: 0,1:15:11.39,1:15:13.76,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,It's possible that you may be within this company's\N你有可能就在这家公司里
Dialogue: 0,1:15:13.76,1:15:17.93,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,you may have issues with a specific business of this company\N您可能与该公司的某个特定业务存在问题。
Dialogue: 0,1:15:17.93,1:15:19.72,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,some certain insurance\N某些保险
Dialogue: 0,1:15:19.72,1:15:22.07,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Differences may exist regarding specific items\N具体项目可能存在差异
Dialogue: 0,1:15:22.07,1:15:25.50,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,But only this company understands it, right?\N但只有这家公司明白这一点，对吧？
Dialogue: 0,1:15:25.81,1:15:27.14,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,This is United Healthcare\N这是联合健康保险公司
Dialogue: 0,1:15:27.14,1:15:29.22,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,The rejection rate is almost fucking 60%\N拒绝率几乎高达 60%。
Dialogue: 0,1:15:29.22,1:15:30.81,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Why are people still buying it\N为什么还有人买它？
Dialogue: 0,1:15:31.18,1:15:36.43,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,You can't escape it. In certain states and industries, that's the only option available.\N你无法逃避。在某些州和某些行业，这是唯一的选择。
Dialogue: 0,1:15:36.63,1:15:37.98,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,unless you move\N除非你搬家
Dialogue: 0,1:15:37.98,1:15:39.39,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,unless you change jobs\N除非你换工作
Dialogue: 0,1:15:39.39,1:15:41.43,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,otherwise you can't escape\N否则你就无法逃脱
Dialogue: 0,1:15:42.01,1:15:43.27,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Do you understand what I mean?\N你明白我的意思吗？
Dialogue: 0,1:15:43.27,1:15:47.10,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,If you are among those 160 million people with formal jobs\N如果你是那 1.6 亿拥有正式工作的人之一
Dialogue: 0,1:15:47.10,1:15:49.82,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Your health insurance plan is no longer your decision.\N你的健康保险计划不再由你决定。
Dialogue: 0,1:15:49.82,1:15:51.06,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Your employer has already decided\N你的雇主已经决定了
Dialogue: 0,1:15:51.06,1:15:52.31,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,The entire company is on this plan\N整个公司都在执行这项计划。
Dialogue: 0,1:15:52.31,1:15:53.22,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,You want to add coverage\N您想增加保险范围
Dialogue: 0,1:15:53.22,1:15:54.25,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,you have to pay extra\N你需要额外付费。
Dialogue: 0,1:15:54.25,1:15:57.05,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,If the company's boss or HR decides to use United Healthcare\N如果公司老板或人力资源部门决定使用联合健康保险
Dialogue: 0,1:15:57.05,1:15:58.72,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,you can only use United Healthcare\N您只能使用联合健康保险
Dialogue: 0,1:15:58.72,1:15:59.94,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,you can get insured\N你可以投保
Dialogue: 0,1:15:59.94,1:16:03.13,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,you already belong to that top 160 million people\N你已经属于那前 1.6 亿人之中了。
Dialogue: 0,1:16:03.13,1:16:05.44,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Yes, your so-called choice is to choose ACC\N是的，你所谓的选择就是选择 ACC。
Dialogue: 0,1:16:05.44,1:16:06.44,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,you can't get in line\N你没法排队
Dialogue: 0,1:16:06.44,1:16:07.88,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,not in the top 1.61\N未进入前 1.61 名
Dialogue: 0,1:16:07.88,1:16:11.52,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,only then can you resort to turning to the ACA\N只有到那时，你才能求助于《平价医疗法案》（ACA）。
Dialogue: 0,1:16:11.52,1:16:13.44,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,It seems like there are some choices\N似乎有一些选择。
Dialogue: 0,1:16:13.44,1:16:14.97,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Well, essentially there's no real choice.\N其实，基本上没有真正的选择。
Dialogue: 0,1:16:14.97,1:16:18.03,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Actually, these are all just the same few big corporations.\N实际上，这些都是同一批大型企业。
Dialogue: 0,1:16:24.39,1:16:26.27,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Some say this is so not capitalist, right?\N有人说这完全不符合资本主义精神，对吧？
Dialogue: 0,1:16:26.27,1:16:28.19,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,This is the ultimate form of capitalism\N这是资本主义的终极形式。
Dialogue: 0,1:16:28.19,1:16:29.80,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,monopoly capital\N垄断资本
Dialogue: 0,1:16:30.50,1:16:33.65,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Trust monopoly\N信托垄断
Dialogue: 0,1:16:39.57,1:16:42.27,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Some might say, can't you just buy cheaper options?\N有人可能会问，难道不能买更便宜的替代品吗？
Dialogue: 0,1:16:42.27,1:16:44.89,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,but it's just a matter of whether this company's prices are expensive or cheap\N但问题就在于这家公司的价格是贵还是便宜。
Dialogue: 0,1:16:44.89,1:16:48.60,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,You still can't escape the grasp of his palm, the Five Finger Mountain.\N你仍然无法逃脱他那只手掌——五指山——的掌控。
Dialogue: 0,1:16:48.60,1:16:53.19,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,It's merely a difference of which finger you're being pressed under.\N区别仅仅在于按压你的是哪根手指而已。
Dialogue: 0,1:17:01.63,1:17:03.63,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,It's convenient to play a video at this moment.\N现在播放视频很方便。
Dialogue: 0,1:17:03.63,1:17:04.43,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,saw a few days ago\N几天前看到的
Dialogue: 0,1:17:04.43,1:17:05.55,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Always feel like remembering something\N总感觉应该想起什么事。
Dialogue: 0,1:17:05.55,1:17:06.63,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,It took me all night to find it again\N我花了一整夜才再次找到它。
Dialogue: 0,1:17:06.63,1:17:07.67,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,The level of hell is quite high\N地狱的等级相当高。
Dialogue: 0,1:17:07.67,1:17:09.22,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,See if it can be played\N看看能不能玩。
Dialogue: 0,1:17:13.72,1:17:16.93,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Ah, the cold father has turned into warm numbers.\N啊，冷酷的父亲变成了温暖的数字。
Dialogue: 0,1:17:16.93,1:17:20.06,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,This is quite common, you know\N这种情况很常见，你知道的。
Dialogue: 0,1:17:20.06,1:17:21.81,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Come on, let's take a look\N来吧，我们一起来看看。
Dialogue: 0,1:17:23.05,1:17:28.65,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,The cold father has turned into warm numbers\N冷漠的父亲变成了温暖的数字
Dialogue: 0,1:17:33.02,1:17:34.34,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Congratulations\N恭喜！
Dialogue: 0,1:17:35.42,1:17:36.61,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,He is the one millionth deceased since the hospital's opening.\N他是这家医院开业以来第一百万名逝者。
Dialogue: 0,1:17:36.61,1:17:39.53,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,One million death\N一百万人死亡
Dialogue: 0,1:17:41.76,1:17:43.64,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,How do the previous two generations feel, may I ask?\N请问前两代人有何感想？
Dialogue: 0,1:17:45.39,1:17:47.18,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,What is wrong with you people\N你们这些人到底怎么了？
Dialogue: 0,1:17:47.18,1:17:49.26,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,I was devastated, he was my father\N我悲痛欲绝，他是我父亲。
Dialogue: 0,1:17:49.26,1:17:51.26,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,This is a difficult time for our family\N这对我们家来说是一个艰难的时期。
Dialogue: 0,1:17:51.26,1:17:52.82,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Why would we want to celebrate this\N我们为什么要庆祝这件事？
Dialogue: 0,1:17:52.82,1:17:55.71,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,His final act in life was a monumental achievement\N他生前的最后举动是一项意义非凡的成就。
Dialogue: 0,1:17:55.71,1:17:58.40,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Congratulations\N恭喜！
Dialogue: 0,1:17:58.85,1:18:00.52,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,You are a one million customer\N您是百万级客户
Dialogue: 0,1:18:00.52,1:18:01.81,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,This year\N今年
Dialogue: 0,1:18:02.73,1:18:04.21,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,We are mourning the loss of my father.\N我们正在哀悼我父亲的去世。
Dialogue: 0,1:18:04.21,1:18:07.01,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Can't this wait a hundred and seventy five thousand\N难道不能等十七万五千美元吗？
Dialogue: 0,1:18:07.01,1:18:08.40,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,We can't afford that\N我们负担不起。
Dialogue: 0,1:18:08.40,1:18:10.10,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,We we gave you a discount on the aspirin\N我们给了你阿司匹林的折扣。
Dialogue: 0,1:18:10.10,1:18:11.32,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,So forty dollars\N所以四十美元
Dialogue: 0,1:18:11.32,1:18:13.48,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,A pillars of discount sry that that should be sixty\N折扣支柱，抱歉，应该是六十
Dialogue: 0,1:18:13.48,1:18:15.30,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,It's half off\N半价
Dialogue: 0,1:18:17.19,1:18:18.23,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Congratulations\N恭喜！
Dialogue: 0,1:18:19.72,1:18:21.71,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,You're the one million parking violations\N你是那第一百万张违章停车罚单。
Dialogue: 0,1:18:21.71,1:18:23.19,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,You toed our car\N你撞了我们的车
Dialogue: 0,1:18:23.19,1:18:24.47,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Our kids were in there\N我们的孩子当时也在里面。
Dialogue: 0,1:18:24.47,1:18:26.43,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,What you left the kids in the car\N你把孩子留在车里了
Dialogue: 0,1:18:26.43,1:18:27.43,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Then tell me what to do? Let him witness his grandfather's death with his own eyes?\N那你告诉我该怎么办？让他亲眼目睹祖父的死亡吗？
Dialogue: 0,1:18:27.43,1:18:30.60,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Let them see grandpa die death\N让他们亲眼目睹爷爷的死亡
Dialogue: 0,1:18:31.60,1:18:34.84,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Uh human is a natural part of life\N人类是生命自然的一部分
Dialogue: 0,1:18:34.84,1:18:35.72,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,As for abandonment and letting a child be kidnapped, that's certainly not.\N至于遗弃和放任儿童被绑架，那肯定不是。
Dialogue: 0,1:18:35.72,1:18:37.38,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,And abducted is not\N而绑架并非如此。
Dialogue: 0,1:18:37.38,1:18:37.81,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Okay\N好的
Dialogue: 0,1:18:37.81,1:18:38.11,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Sir\N先生
Dialogue: 0,1:18:38.11,1:18:39.03,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Oh! Doctor, we didn't abandon our child, he was taken away by a tow truck!\N哦！医生，我们没有遗弃孩子，他是被拖车拉走了！
Dialogue: 0,1:18:39.03,1:18:39.60,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Our children\N我们的孩子
Dialogue: 0,1:18:39.60,1:18:40.92,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,They were toed away in a car\N他们被车开走了
Dialogue: 0,1:18:40.92,1:18:42.10,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Congratulations\N恭喜！
Dialogue: 0,1:18:42.10,1:18:43.63,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Hh\N嗯
Dialogue: 0,1:18:43.99,1:18:45.75,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,You two are the one millionth pair to neglect your parents\N你们俩是第一百万个不孝顺父母的孩子了。
Dialogue: 0,1:18:45.75,1:18:46.27,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Megalyour\N巨型
Dialogue: 0,1:18:46.27,1:18:46.75,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Parents\N父母
Dialogue: 0,1:18:46.75,1:18:51.07,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Ha ha ha ha ha ha where are our children\N哈哈哈哈哈哈，我们的孩子在哪里？
Dialogue: 0,1:18:51.07,1:18:54.03,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,They're going in foster care\N他们将被送去寄养家庭。
Dialogue: 0,1:18:57.88,1:18:59.69,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Please no I just want my kids back\N求求你们不要，我只想我的孩子回来。
Dialogue: 0,1:18:59.69,1:19:00.03,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,No\N不
Dialogue: 0,1:19:00.03,1:19:04.18,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,I just want my honey to come back, congratulations\N我只希望我的爱人回来，恭喜你。
Dialogue: 0,1:19:04.18,1:19:07.82,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Ah you just won ten million dollars from your father's life\N啊，你刚刚从你父亲的遗产中赢得了 1000 万美元。
Dialogue: 0,1:19:07.82,1:19:10.00,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Insurance policy\N保单
Dialogue: 0,1:19:27.28,1:19:29.52,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,This is absolutely an American hell joke.\N这绝对是个美国式的地狱笑话。
Dialogue: 0,1:19:29.52,1:19:32.23,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Oh my god\N我的天啊
Dialogue: 0,1:19:32.32,1:19:35.27,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,The concentration is a bit too low or too high\N浓度有点低或有点高
Dialogue: 0,1:19:36.52,1:19:37.64,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Sigh\N叹
Dialogue: 0,1:19:39.53,1:19:41.53,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Ah, thank you Brother Digongzhiquan for the tip.\N啊，谢谢地宫之泉兄弟的指点。
Dialogue: 0,1:19:41.53,1:19:42.51,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Let me take a look\N让我看看
Dialogue: 0,1:19:42.51,1:19:44.60,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,I used to work in the insurance industry.\N我以前在保险行业工作。
Dialogue: 0,1:19:44.60,1:19:45.56,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,and other insurance\N以及其他保险
Dialogue: 0,1:19:45.56,1:19:46.63,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,collaboration with Europe and America\N与欧洲和美国合作
Dialogue: 0,1:19:46.63,1:19:51.39,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,I feel like domestic insurance and foreign insurance, uh, wait a second\N我觉得国内保险和国外保险，呃，等等
Dialogue: 0,1:19:51.39,1:19:53.64,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,are entirely two different concepts under the same term\N这是同一个术语下的两个完全不同的概念。
Dialogue: 0,1:19:53.64,1:19:55.11,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,So I haven't heard the whole story about this matter today\N所以今天我还没有听到关于这件事的全部经过。
Dialogue: 0,1:19:55.11,1:19:56.15,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,but want to share some insights\N但我想分享一些见解
Dialogue: 0,1:19:56.15,1:19:58.03,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Just as an additional perspective\N仅作为一种补充视角
Dialogue: 0,1:19:58.03,1:19:59.03,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,To be fair\N公平地说
Dialogue: 0,1:19:59.03,1:20:01.35,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,During my years working in the field\N在我从事该领域工作的这些年里
Dialogue: 0,1:20:01.35,1:20:03.80,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,The gemstones from XiDa almost completely outshine domestic ones in every aspect\N西大宝石在各个方面几乎都完胜国产宝石。
Dialogue: 0,1:20:03.80,1:20:06.31,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Their solutions and technologies do have remarkable advantages\N他们的解决方案和技术确实具有显著优势。
Dialogue: 0,1:20:06.31,1:20:07.43,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,but the path is wrong\N但这条路错了。
Dialogue: 0,1:20:08.98,1:20:10.36,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,is never an empty phrase\N这绝非一句空话。
Dialogue: 0,1:20:10.36,1:20:13.60,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,In recent years, the trend of the West declining while the East rises has become increasingly evident.\N近年来，西方衰落而东方崛起的趋势越来越明显。
Dialogue: 0,1:20:13.60,1:20:14.67,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,To elaborate\N详细说明
Dialogue: 0,1:20:14.67,1:20:16.86,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,First, domestic gemstones are looked down upon by the financial industry\N首先，国产宝石受到金融行业的轻视。
Dialogue: 0,1:20:16.86,1:20:18.18,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,There is a reason why it's at the bottom of the chain\N它之所以位于产业链的最底端，是有原因的。
Dialogue: 0,1:20:20.35,1:20:20.94,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,money bag\N钱袋
Dialogue: 0,1:20:20.94,1:20:22.73,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,even acting as a black-and-white glove\N甚至可以充当黑白手套
Dialogue: 0,1:20:22.73,1:20:25.94,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Overall, it serves as a tool and leverage for governance.\N总的来说，它可作为治理的工具和杠杆。
Dialogue: 0,1:20:25.94,1:20:27.27,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,the four major domestic treasures\N国内四大瑰宝
Dialogue: 0,1:20:27.27,1:20:28.98,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,three are wholly state-owned central enterprises\N三家均为国有中央企业
Dialogue: 0,1:20:28.98,1:20:30.40,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,must resolutely obey the leadership\N必须坚决服从领导
Dialogue: 0,1:20:30.40,1:20:31.75,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,even if it is purely privately owned\N即使它是完全私有的
Dialogue: 0,1:20:31.75,1:20:32.89,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,must also obey orders\N还必须服从命令
Dialogue: 0,1:20:32.89,1:20:34.43,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Keep social responsibility in mind\N牢记社会责任。
Dialogue: 0,1:20:34.43,1:20:35.85,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,the most basic hope lies with the salt merchants\N最基本的希望寄托在盐商身上。
Dialogue: 0,1:20:35.85,1:20:37.38,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,The salt merchants refuse to pay when they really should not pay\N盐商们明明不应该付钱，却拒绝付款。
Dialogue: 0,1:20:37.38,1:20:38.46,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Even if it should be covered, they still won't pay\N即使本应由保险公司承担，他们仍然不会支付。
Dialogue: 0,1:20:38.46,1:20:39.50,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,have no choice\N别无选择
Dialogue: 0,1:20:39.50,1:20:41.71,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,would rather settle out of court\N宁愿庭外和解。
Dialogue: 0,1:20:41.71,1:20:44.11,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,The Dongda Insurance Company has to pay even if they say they won't.\N即使东大保险公司声称不会赔付，他们也必须赔付。
Dialogue: 0,1:20:44.11,1:20:46.65,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,The insurance regulatory court compels payment despite claim rejection\N即使索赔被拒，保险监管法院仍强制支付。
Dialogue: 0,1:20:46.65,1:20:50.44,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Similarly, it doesn't matter if you involve relevant leaders from the insurance regulatory or private insurance sectors.\N同样，邀请保险监管机构或私人保险部门的相关领导人参与也无关紧要。
Dialogue: 0,1:20:50.44,1:20:52.09,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Having a court judgment is enough to settle the matter\N有了法院判决就足以解决问题。
Dialogue: 0,1:20:52.09,1:20:55.35,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,But foreign insurance companies are effectively part of the ruling class\N但外国保险公司实际上是统治阶级的一部分。
Dialogue: 0,1:20:55.35,1:20:55.94,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,itself\N本身
Dialogue: 0,1:20:55.94,1:20:56.90,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Specifically\N具体来说
Dialogue: 0,1:20:56.90,1:20:58.35,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,capitalist lawyers\N资本主义律师
Dialogue: 0,1:20:58.35,1:20:59.10,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,guild doctors\N行会医生
Dialogue: 0,1:20:59.10,1:21:00.06,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,guild actuaries\N行会精算师
Dialogue: 0,1:21:00.06,1:21:00.98,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Accounting Guild\N会计协会
Dialogue: 0,1:21:00.98,1:21:03.40,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,wealthy individuals with tax avoidance needs\N有避税需求的富裕人士
Dialogue: 0,1:21:03.40,1:21:05.64,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,a platform for weaving networks, colluding, and sharing interests\N一个用于构建网络、串通和分享利益的平台
Dialogue: 0,1:21:05.64,1:21:08.81,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,This is why bail deduction authority in the U.S. is even higher than that of banks\N这就是为什么美国的保释金扣除权限甚至比银行的权限还要高。
Dialogue: 0,1:21:08.81,1:21:11.34,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,the reason, okay\N原因，好的
Dialogue: 0,1:21:11.34,1:21:15.11,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,And there's also the aspect of premium investment, reinsurance, and double insurance design.\N此外，还有保费投资、再保险和双重保险设计等方面的问题。
Dialogue: 0,1:21:15.11,1:21:17.68,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Why do insurance companies have higher deduction authority than banks?\N为什么保险公司的扣款权限比银行高？
Dialogue: 0,1:21:17.68,1:21:20.56,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,You big gemstones play way too many tricks in the investment market\N你们这些大宝石在投资市场玩弄了太多花招。
Dialogue: 0,1:21:20.56,1:21:21.39,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,too aggressive\N过于激进
Dialogue: 0,1:21:21.39,1:21:24.43,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Although there are explicit restrictions on the proportion of insurance funds entering the market\N尽管对进入市场的保险基金比例有明确的限制
Dialogue: 0,1:21:24.43,1:21:27.64,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,but various credit guarantees, asset packages, and equity products\N但包括各种信用担保、资产组合和股权产品。
Dialogue: 0,1:21:27.64,1:21:29.47,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,The result is high risk and high return\N结果就是高风险高回报。
Dialogue: 0,1:21:29.47,1:21:30.65,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,too big to fail when things go wrong\N规模太大，出问题时不会倒闭
Dialogue: 0,1:21:32.04,1:21:32.88,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,renowned\N著名
Dialogue: 0,1:21:32.88,1:21:33.56,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,subprime mortgage crisis\N次贷危机
Dialogue: 0,1:21:33.56,1:21:35.52,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,the renowned American International Insurance Group\N著名的美国国际保险集团
Dialogue: 0,1:21:35.52,1:21:36.84,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,was also a key behind-the-scenes player\N他也是一位重要的幕后人物。
Dialogue: 0,1:21:36.84,1:21:37.74,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,credit insurance\N信用保险
Dialogue: 0,1:21:37.74,1:21:41.13,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,The result was that the federal government had to massively bail out with public funds.\N结果是联邦政府不得不动用公共资金进行大规模救助。
Dialogue: 0,1:21:41.13,1:21:43.42,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,while Lehman Brothers went straight into bankruptcy\N而雷曼兄弟则直接破产了。
Dialogue: 0,1:21:43.42,1:21:45.97,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,a Naya-led diagram of major healthcare reforms under the Schina administration\N纳亚主导绘制的席娜政府时期重大医疗改革示意图
Dialogue: 0,1:21:45.97,1:21:49.62,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,The sudden association feels somewhat similar to the fallen hostels of the Soviet Union.\N这种突如其来的联想，让人感觉有点像苏联时期那些倒塌的青年旅舍。
Dialogue: 0,1:21:49.62,1:21:50.98,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,nominally serving the entire population\N名义上服务于全体人口
Dialogue: 0,1:21:50.98,1:21:52.86,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,In practice, it can only take from those who have little\N实际上，它只能从那些贫穷的人身上掠夺。
Dialogue: 0,1:21:52.86,1:21:53.50,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,to give to those who already have more than enough\N给予那些已经拥有足够多资源的人
Dialogue: 0,1:21:53.50,1:21:55.18,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,To put it bluntly, it's about treating people differently based on their status.\N说得直白些，这就是根据人们的地位区别对待他们。
Dialogue: 0,1:21:55.18,1:21:58.02,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,robbing Peter to pay Paul with resources meant to serve ordinary people\N拆东墙补西墙，用原本服务于普通民众的资源来支付保罗的薪水。
Dialogue: 0,1:21:58.02,1:21:58.97,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,to the upper class\N对上层阶级而言
Dialogue: 0,1:21:59.97,1:22:01.81,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,That's how it is\N就是这样。
Dialogue: 0,1:22:04.69,1:22:09.57,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Sigh, someone said that's industry insurance\N唉，有人说那是行业保险。
Dialogue: 0,1:22:10.18,1:22:12.80,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Well, what else is there in industry insurance?\N那么，工业保险领域还有哪些其他方面呢？
Dialogue: 0,1:22:12.80,1:22:18.75,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Home insurance is the most terrifying thing\N房屋保险是最可怕的事情
Dialogue: 0,1:22:19.02,1:22:19.75,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Some people say\N有人说
Dialogue: 0,1:22:19.75,1:22:23.68,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Is property tax the scariest aspect of owning a home in the US?\N在美国，房产税是拥有房产最令人担忧的方面吗？
Dialogue: 0,1:22:23.68,1:22:24.32,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,No\N不
Dialogue: 0,1:22:24.32,1:22:26.47,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,it's the homeowner's insurance\N这是房主保险
Dialogue: 0,1:22:27.55,1:22:31.18,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Property tax typically charges around 2%.\N房产税通常约为 2%。
Dialogue: 0,1:22:31.18,1:22:33.14,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,on average, a house\N平均而言，一栋房子
Dialogue: 0,1:22:33.14,1:22:34.57,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,For example, your house is worth 1 million\N例如，你的房子价值 100 万美元。
Dialogue: 0,1:22:34.57,1:22:38.51,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,You pay $20,000 in property taxes per year.\N你每年缴纳 2 万美元的房产税。
Dialogue: 0,1:22:38.51,1:22:40.51,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,There are also property fees\N此外还有房产费
Dialogue: 0,1:22:41.55,1:22:45.27,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,property fees and that home insurance\N房产费和房屋保险
Dialogue: 0,1:22:45.27,1:22:46.98,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Oh\N哦
Dialogue: 0,1:22:48.22,1:22:51.53,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Both of them are also charged based on the property value\N两者的费用均按房产价值计算。
Dialogue: 0,1:22:51.53,1:22:52.85,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,You know what I mean\N你知道我的意思
Dialogue: 0,1:22:53.15,1:22:56.85,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,For example, if you bought a house at the age of 20\N例如，如果你在 20 岁时买了一套房子
Dialogue: 0,1:22:56.85,1:22:58.27,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,worth 1 million\N价值 100 万美元
Dialogue: 0,1:22:58.27,1:23:02.03,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,This house is now worth 5 million when you're 70 years old.\N当你 70 岁时，这栋房子价值 500 万美元。
Dialogue: 0,1:23:02.31,1:23:04.42,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,it has increased fivefold in 50 years\N50 年来，它增长了五倍。
Dialogue: 0,1:23:04.42,1:23:06.67,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Then don't be happy\N那就别高兴。
Dialogue: 0,1:23:06.67,1:23:08.67,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Insurance premiums will increase\N保险费将会上涨
Dialogue: 0,1:23:08.67,1:23:11.28,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,property fees and taxes will increase\N房产费用和税费将会增加
Dialogue: 0,1:23:11.28,1:23:12.72,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Property taxes will also rise\N房产税也将上涨
Dialogue: 0,1:23:12.72,1:23:15.06,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,And they are all proportional, you get it?\N它们都是成比例的，你明白吗？
Dialogue: 0,1:23:15.06,1:23:17.92,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,The high cost is proportional damage, you get it?\N高昂的代价与造成的损失成正比，你明白吗？
Dialogue: 0,1:23:17.92,1:23:21.03,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Do you understand his Vayne passive three-ring effect?\N你了解薇恩被动技能的三环效果吗？
Dialogue: 0,1:23:21.60,1:23:25.07,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,It deducts a percentage of the max health.\N它会扣除最大生命值的一定比例。
Dialogue: 0,1:23:25.07,1:23:26.38,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Some people mention insurance\N有些人提到了保险。
Dialogue: 0,1:23:26.38,1:23:29.05,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,How expensive can the insurance be?\N保险费用能有多高？
Dialogue: 0,1:23:29.05,1:23:32.25,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Well, it depends on how decent your house is, okay?\N那得看你的房子条件怎么样了，好吗？
Dialogue: 0,1:23:32.25,1:23:35.71,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,The more upscale the house, the more expensive it is.\N房子越高档，价格就越贵。
Dialogue: 0,1:23:35.98,1:23:36.59,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Some people say\N有人说
Dialogue: 0,1:23:36.59,1:23:41.63,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Generally speaking, it's roughly a bit cheaper than property taxes, but not by much.\N总的来说，它比房产税略便宜一些，但差别不大。
Dialogue: 0,1:23:41.63,1:23:45.35,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,So don't assume that property taxes are the end of it.\N所以不要以为房产税就万事大吉了。
Dialogue: 0,1:23:45.35,1:23:46.34,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,No, that's not the case\N不，并非如此。
Dialogue: 0,1:23:46.34,1:23:48.92,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,home insurance property tax\N房屋保险房产税
Dialogue: 0,1:23:48.92,1:23:51.93,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,property fees must also be paid\N还必须支付物业费。
Dialogue: 0,1:24:02.80,1:24:04.77,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Some say the proportion paid is uh\N有人说支付的比例是呃
Dialogue: 0,1:24:04.77,1:24:08.85,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,approximately one-third to one-half of the property tax\N大约占房产税的三分之一到二分之一
Dialogue: 0,1:24:08.85,1:24:14.12,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,if the property tax is 2% of the total home price\N如果房产税为房屋总价的 2%
Dialogue: 0,1:24:14.12,1:24:17.58,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,then the home insurance is basically 0.66%\N那么房屋保险基本上就是 0.66%。
Dialogue: 0,1:24:17.58,1:24:20.32,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,around 1%\N约 1%
Dialogue: 0,1:24:20.32,1:24:21.94,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,if it's not a luxury home\N如果不是豪华住宅的话
Dialogue: 0,1:24:21.94,1:24:23.06,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,just an ordinary house\N只是一栋普通的房子
Dialogue: 0,1:24:25.35,1:24:27.10,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Ah, and there's also the property management fee.\N啊，还有物业管理费呢。
Dialogue: 0,1:24:27.10,1:24:29.10,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Some say can property management fees even be considered?\N有人说，物业管理费是否可以考虑？
Dialogue: 0,1:24:29.10,1:24:29.67,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Right\N正确的
Dialogue: 0,1:24:29.67,1:24:32.59,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,The property management fee is 0.2% of the total house price\N物业管理费为房屋总价的 0.2%。
Dialogue: 0,1:24:32.59,1:24:35.10,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,ranging from 0.5%\N范围从 0.5%起
Dialogue: 0,1:24:37.30,1:24:40.39,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Let me put it this way\N让我这样说吧
Dialogue: 0,1:24:40.39,1:24:41.89,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,You own a house\N你拥有一套房子
Dialogue: 0,1:24:41.89,1:24:43.96,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,This house is worth 1 million dollars.\N这栋房子价值一百万美元。
Dialogue: 0,1:24:43.96,1:24:48.32,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Your annual mandatory expenses amount to 20 dollars.\N您的年度强制性支出为 20 美元。
Dialogue: 0,1:24:48.32,1:24:52.85,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Your annual mandatory expenses are approximately $340,000.\N您的年度强制性支出约为 340,000 美元。
Dialogue: 0,1:24:52.85,1:24:54.81,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,which is 3% of the total house price\N相当于房屋总价的 3%。
Dialogue: 0,1:24:54.81,1:24:56.18,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,nearly 4%\N近 4%
Dialogue: 0,1:24:56.18,1:24:59.18,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Sometimes what does home insurance even cover? Like if it burns down\N有时候，房屋保险到底能赔付哪些费用？比如房屋被烧毁的情况。
Dialogue: 0,1:24:59.18,1:25:04.26,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,rebuild a Li wedding dress for you\N为您重新设计一件李氏婚纱
Dialogue: 0,1:25:04.26,1:25:05.00,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Thank you\N谢谢
Dialogue: 0,1:25:05.00,1:25:06.72,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Country, hmm, OK, oh\N乡村，嗯，好的，哦
Dialogue: 0,1:25:06.72,1:25:08.59,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,If the price of a house in the U.S. drops\N如果美国房价下跌
Dialogue: 0,1:25:08.59,1:25:10.75,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,the previously increased property fees and property taxes\N此前增加的物业费和物业税
Dialogue: 0,1:25:10.75,1:25:12.90,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Do you still have to pay based on the highest historical property price?\N是否仍需按照历史最高房价支付？
Dialogue: 0,1:25:12.90,1:25:15.81,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,No, the tax reduction will not be granted.\N不，减税申请将不予批准。
Dialogue: 0,1:25:15.81,1:25:18.01,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,First, the house price has dropped\N首先，房价下跌了。
Dialogue: 0,1:25:18.01,1:25:21.93,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,If the drop in housing prices is due to your actions\N如果房价下跌是由于你的行为造成的
Dialogue: 0,1:25:21.93,1:25:24.32,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,you'll just have to wait for liquidation\N你只能等清算了。
Dialogue: 0,1:25:24.32,1:25:25.05,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Someone said\N有人说
Dialogue: 0,1:25:25.05,1:25:26.78,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Why is it that I'm speaking now\N我为什么现在要说话呢？
Dialogue: 0,1:25:26.78,1:25:29.05,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Why do all social classes in the United States\N为什么美国所有社会阶层
Dialogue: 0,1:25:29.05,1:25:31.68,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,For example, the middle class needs to maintain their dignity\N例如，中产阶级需要维护他们的尊严。
Dialogue: 0,1:25:31.68,1:25:34.89,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,You have to maintain, you have to maintain housing prices\N你必须维持，你必须维持房价
Dialogue: 0,1:25:35.18,1:25:37.42,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,This is different from the Chinese logic\N这与中国的逻辑不同。
Dialogue: 0,1:25:37.42,1:25:40.61,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,As long as it's a major city, housing prices will rise everywhere.\N只要是主要城市，房价就会上涨。
Dialogue: 0,1:25:40.61,1:25:41.25,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,rising everywhere\N到处都在上升
Dialogue: 0,1:25:41.25,1:25:43.67,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,This is not the American way\N这不是美国的方式
Dialogue: 0,1:25:43.67,1:25:45.64,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,The U.S. is specifically divided into communities.\N美国明显划分为不同的社区。
Dialogue: 0,1:25:45.64,1:25:49.39,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,The housing prices in your community are collectively maintained by all the residents living there\N您所在社区的房价是由所有居民共同维持的。
Dialogue: 0,1:25:49.39,1:25:51.19,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,collectively maintained\N集体维护
Dialogue: 0,1:25:51.39,1:25:52.81,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,What it means in the US is\N在美国，它的意思是：
Dialogue: 0,1:25:52.81,1:25:55.15,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,a building is worth only one dollar\N一栋建筑物只值一美元。
Dialogue: 0,1:25:55.15,1:25:58.09,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,and a building worth $10 million\N还有一栋价值 1000 万美元的建筑
Dialogue: 0,1:25:58.09,1:25:59.81,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,may be adjacent\N可能相邻
Dialogue: 0,1:25:59.81,1:26:00.48,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,two communities\N两个社区
Dialogue: 0,1:26:00.48,1:26:02.89,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,separated by just one street\N仅隔一条街道
Dialogue: 0,1:26:03.02,1:26:03.76,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Got it?\N知道了？
Dialogue: 0,1:26:03.76,1:26:06.65,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,two communities on either side of the street\N街道两旁是两个社区
Dialogue: 0,1:26:06.65,1:26:09.30,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Here, a house can be sold for just one dollar\N在这里，一套房子只需一美元就能卖掉。
Dialogue: 0,1:26:09.30,1:26:11.85,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,a house over there sells for 10 million\N那边的一栋房子卖 1000 万美元。
Dialogue: 0,1:26:12.86,1:26:13.86,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Do you know what I mean?\N你明白我的意思吗？
Dialogue: 0,1:26:15.31,1:26:17.81,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,It doesn't consider the overall development of the city.\N它没有考虑到城市的整体发展。
Dialogue: 0,1:26:17.81,1:26:22.25,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,how the people in your community maintain the community\N你所在社区的人们如何维护社区
Dialogue: 0,1:26:22.25,1:26:24.52,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,determines the housing prices in this community\N决定该社区房价的因素
Dialogue: 0,1:26:24.52,1:26:25.60,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Then tell me\N然后告诉我
Dialogue: 0,1:26:25.60,1:26:27.82,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Can you afford not to maintain appearances?\N你能承担不维护体面的后果吗？
Dialogue: 0,1:26:27.82,1:26:30.32,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Do you dare not maintain this decency\N你竟敢违背这份体面？
Dialogue: 0,1:26:30.32,1:26:34.94,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,The homeowners association can force you into compulsory liquidation\N业主协会可以强制你进行清算。
Dialogue: 0,1:26:34.94,1:26:37.04,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,forcing you to sell your house\N迫使你卖掉房子
Dialogue: 0,1:26:37.65,1:26:39.83,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Why don't they lower housing prices sometimes\N为什么他们有时不降低房价呢？
Dialogue: 0,1:26:39.83,1:26:41.77,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,pay less taxes\N少缴税
Dialogue: 0,1:26:43.47,1:26:45.80,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Telling me this is pretty much useless, right?\N告诉我这些基本没用，对吧？
Dialogue: 0,1:26:46.84,1:26:49.92,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Go tell that to the rich people\N你去跟有钱人说说这话。
Dialogue: 0,1:26:53.27,1:26:58.13,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Oh, you're talking about that 1% property insurance, huh?\N哦，你说的是那 1%的财产保险啊？
Dialogue: 0,1:26:58.44,1:27:01.17,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Like those in California,\N就像加州的那些人一样，
Dialogue: 0,1:27:01.17,1:27:02.68,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Last time there was a big fire, weren't there many wealthy people\N上次发生大火的时候，是不是有很多富人？
Dialogue: 0,1:27:02.68,1:27:05.13,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,they choose to be in that kind of\N他们选择处于那种状态
Dialogue: 0,1:27:05.13,1:27:06.89,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Well, I don't know\N嗯，我不知道。
Dialogue: 0,1:27:06.89,1:27:08.03,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,in their case\N就他们而言
Dialogue: 0,1:27:08.03,1:27:09.03,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Do they have a community?\N他们有自己的社区吗？
Dialogue: 0,1:27:09.03,1:27:11.52,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,that is, the kind of standalone luxury homes in the forest\N也就是说，森林里那种独立的豪华住宅。
Dialogue: 0,1:27:11.52,1:27:13.39,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,It's considered to have a community\N它被认为拥有一个社区
Dialogue: 0,1:27:13.39,1:27:15.00,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,or is there no community\N或者根本没有社区
Dialogue: 0,1:27:17.30,1:27:19.53,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,I'm quite curious about this.\N我对此很好奇。
Dialogue: 0,1:27:19.53,1:27:21.23,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,a standalone mansion in the forest\N森林中的一座独立豪宅
Dialogue: 0,1:27:21.23,1:27:22.65,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,That's what you see in the photos\N这就是你在照片里看到的。
Dialogue: 0,1:27:22.65,1:27:25.52,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,You think you're in a standalone mansion in the forest\N你以为自己身处森林中一座独立的豪宅里
Dialogue: 0,1:27:25.52,1:27:26.89,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,You look at the satellite map\N你查看卫星地图
Dialogue: 0,1:27:26.89,1:27:27.75,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,you will know\N你会知道
Dialogue: 0,1:27:27.75,1:27:29.89,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,It must definitely be in a community.\N它肯定位于某个社区内。
Dialogue: 0,1:27:29.89,1:27:30.88,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,most likely\N最有可能的
Dialogue: 0,1:27:30.88,1:27:32.48,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,not in the same community\N不属于同一个社区
Dialogue: 0,1:27:32.48,1:27:36.51,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Who built the road right up to your house?\N谁修了这条直通你家门口的路？
Dialogue: 0,1:27:36.51,1:27:39.27,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Where does your sewer discharge to?\N你们的污水排放到哪里？
Dialogue: 0,1:27:39.27,1:27:42.18,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Who's your daddy for water, electricity, heating, and ventilation?\N谁负责你的水、电、暖气和通风？
Dialogue: 0,1:27:42.18,1:27:45.32,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,It's nothing more than a higher density compared to the others.\N它只不过是比其他材料密度更高而已。
Dialogue: 0,1:27:45.32,1:27:48.14,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,It simply has a lower density with each household occupying a larger area\N它的密度较低，每户家庭占用的面积更大。
Dialogue: 0,1:27:48.14,1:27:49.46,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,but not without neighborhoods\N但并非没有社区
Dialogue: 0,1:27:49.46,1:27:52.62,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,the kind that literally occupies an entire hill\N那种占据整座山丘的山丘
Dialogue: 0,1:27:52.62,1:27:54.86,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,that kind of self-developed property without neighbors\N那种没有邻居的自建房产
Dialogue: 0,1:27:54.86,1:27:57.78,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,That's not something ordinary wealthy people can afford.\N那是普通富人负担不起的。
Dialogue: 0,1:27:57.78,1:27:59.78,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,That requires someone extremely wealthy.\N那需要极其富有的人。
Dialogue: 0,1:27:59.78,1:28:02.22,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,and there was also a historical opportunity\N此外，还有一个历史性的机遇。
Dialogue: 0,1:28:02.22,1:28:04.23,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,back in the pioneering days, right\N回到拓荒时代，对吧？
Dialogue: 0,1:28:04.23,1:28:05.96,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,your family occupied this land\N你的家族曾居住在这片土地上。
Dialogue: 0,1:28:05.96,1:28:07.46,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,then this fist might be yours\N那么，这只拳头可能就是你的了。
Dialogue: 0,1:28:07.46,1:28:10.18,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,That doesn't necessarily mean you can buy it or get it, you know.\N但这并不意味着你就能买到或得到它。
Dialogue: 0,1:28:10.18,1:28:12.22,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,You also want a prime urban location\N您还需要一个优越的城市位置。
Dialogue: 0,1:28:12.22,1:28:13.92,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,It also needs to be a mountaintop\N它还必须是一座山顶
Dialogue: 0,1:28:13.92,1:28:17.53,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Can you figure this out?\N你能解决这个问题吗？
Dialogue: 0,1:28:17.53,1:28:19.50,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,not your turn\N还没轮到你呢
Dialogue: 0,1:28:20.93,1:28:23.52,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Well, this brings us to another issue\N嗯，这就引出了另一个问题。
Dialogue: 0,1:28:23.52,1:28:26.64,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,It's just that everyone in China might be quite accustomed to saying\N只是在中国，每个人可能都相当习惯说这句话。
Dialogue: 0,1:28:26.64,1:28:29.89,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Oh well, I can't buy land anyway, right?\N唉，反正我也买不起地，对吧？
Dialogue: 0,1:28:29.89,1:28:31.15,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,I buy a house, what am I buying\N我买了一套房子，我到底买了什么？
Dialogue: 0,1:28:31.15,1:28:34.14,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Isn't it just openly available on the market?\N难道它不是在市场上公开销售的吗？
Dialogue: 0,1:28:34.14,1:28:34.82,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,right\N正确的
Dialogue: 0,1:28:34.82,1:28:37.14,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,You think everything is between buyers\N你认为一切都只关乎买家。
Dialogue: 0,1:28:37.14,1:28:37.78,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,the seller has agreed\N卖方已同意
Dialogue: 0,1:28:37.78,1:28:40.07,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Let's go to a trading center, right?\N咱们去交易中心吧？
Dialogue: 0,1:28:40.07,1:28:41.23,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,What else is there that can't be sold?\N还有什么东西是不能卖的？
Dialogue: 0,1:28:41.23,1:28:45.52,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Well, in the vast majority of other countries around the world\N嗯，在世界其他绝大多数国家都是如此。
Dialogue: 0,1:28:45.64,1:28:48.23,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Many things are not so easily movable.\N很多东西并不容易搬动。
Dialogue: 0,1:28:48.23,1:28:50.60,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,the family has held it for generations\N这个房子是家族世代拥有的。
Dialogue: 0,1:28:50.60,1:28:53.17,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,The family might be in a family trust or something like that.\N这个家庭可能加入了家族信托或其他类似的机构。
Dialogue: 0,1:28:53.17,1:28:55.17,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,just like the old Dutton kind\N就像老达顿家族那样
Dialogue: 0,1:28:55.17,1:28:56.60,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Right, yeah\N对，是的
Dialogue: 0,1:28:56.60,1:28:58.48,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Is this something you can just buy whenever you want?\N这是你想买就能买的东西吗？
Dialogue: 0,1:28:58.48,1:29:00.36,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Can you sell it whenever you want?\N你想卖就卖，可以随时卖吗？
Dialogue: 0,1:29:08.77,1:29:12.88,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Well, it really depends on luck, right?\N嗯，这真的要看运气，对吧？
Dialogue: 0,1:29:12.88,1:29:13.85,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,depends on financial capability\N取决于财务能力
Dialogue: 0,1:29:13.85,1:29:17.89,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,It also depends on a little bit of luck, hmm.\N这其中也需要一点运气，嗯。
Dialogue: 0,1:29:19.21,1:29:22.46,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,You're saying this property insurance is a must-have, aren't you?\N你是说这份财产保险是必备的，对吧？
Dialogue: 0,1:29:22.46,1:29:23.52,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Unfortunately\N很遗憾
Dialogue: 0,1:29:23.52,1:29:26.02,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,just like the other insurances I mentioned before\N就像我之前提到的其他保险一样。
Dialogue: 0,1:29:26.02,1:29:28.57,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,you almost have no choice\N你几乎别无选择
Dialogue: 0,1:29:30.65,1:29:33.92,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,You have no choice, understand?\N你别无选择，明白吗？
Dialogue: 0,1:29:35.07,1:29:38.47,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Some people say this real estate company, well, many people are saying this.\N有人说这家房地产公司，嗯，很多人都这么说。
Dialogue: 0,1:29:38.47,1:29:38.88,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,getting back to the point\N回到正题
Dialogue: 0,1:29:38.88,1:29:40.31,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Fortunately, I still had some experience in real estate.\N幸运的是，我还有一些房地产方面的经验。
Dialogue: 0,1:29:40.31,1:29:40.96,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Let me interrupt\N让我打断一下。
Dialogue: 0,1:29:40.96,1:29:41.39,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Sorry\N对不起
Dialogue: 0,1:29:41.39,1:29:42.65,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,ALEX uh\N亚历克斯呃
Dialogue: 0,1:29:43.77,1:29:47.20,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,East's protection of property rights\N东方对财产权的保护
Dialogue: 0,1:29:47.20,1:29:49.22,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,I dare not say it's the best in the world\N我不敢说它是世界上最好的。
Dialogue: 0,1:29:49.22,1:29:53.79,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,at least it is much stronger compared to the West\N至少与西方相比，它要强大得多。
Dialogue: 0,1:29:53.79,1:29:56.07,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,The Eastern Power has no property tax\N东部电力公司没有房产税。
Dialogue: 0,1:29:56.07,1:29:56.97,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,personal residences\N私人住宅
Dialogue: 0,1:29:56.97,1:29:57.79,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,limited to personal residences\N仅限个人住宅
Dialogue: 0,1:29:57.79,1:30:00.96,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Commercial properties are subject to taxes, while personal residences are not\N商业地产需要缴税，而个人住宅则不需要。
Dialogue: 0,1:30:00.96,1:30:02.85,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,You, you, your property fees\N你，你，你的房产费
Dialogue: 0,1:30:02.85,1:30:04.80,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Even if you don't pay the property management fees\N即使你不支付物业管理费
Dialogue: 0,1:30:04.80,1:30:05.56,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,at most they'll cut you off\N最多也就是断了你的电。
Dialogue: 0,1:30:05.56,1:30:06.11,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,cut off water and electricity\N切断水和电
Dialogue: 0,1:30:06.11,1:30:06.84,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,You can still make a scene\N你仍然可以制造场面
Dialogue: 0,1:30:06.84,1:30:08.61,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,don't let them cut off your water and electricity\N别让他们切断你的水和电。
Dialogue: 0,1:30:08.61,1:30:09.55,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,right\N正确的
Dialogue: 0,1:30:09.55,1:30:12.35,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,That homeowners association cannot sell your house\N业主协会无权出售你的房子
Dialogue: 0,1:30:12.35,1:30:13.13,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,right\N正确的
Dialogue: 0,1:30:13.13,1:30:15.17,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,You don't have to buy insurance\N你不必购买保险。
Dialogue: 0,1:30:15.17,1:30:20.65,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Even if you do this and that, you do a lot of good things, uh...\N即使你做了这样那样的事，你也做了很多好事，嗯……
Dialogue: 0,1:30:20.65,1:30:22.34,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Everyone, open your property certificate\N各位，请打开你们的房产证
Dialogue: 0,1:30:22.34,1:30:23.34,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,You might have forgotten about it\N你可能已经忘记了这件事。
Dialogue: 0,1:30:23.34,1:30:25.65,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,and then go to that bedside drawer to look for it\N然后去床头柜抽屉里找它。
Dialogue: 0,1:30:25.65,1:30:28.50,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Turn to the second last page of the property ownership certificate\N翻到房产所有权证书的倒数第二页。
Dialogue: 0,1:30:28.50,1:30:29.22,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,If I remember correctly\N如果我没记错的话
Dialogue: 0,1:30:29.22,1:30:31.35,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,It should be called the right of pledge\N它应该被称为质押权。
Dialogue: 0,1:30:31.35,1:30:34.56,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,For the vast majority of easterners, the term 'other rights'\N对于绝大多数东方人来说，“其他权利”一词
Dialogue: 0,1:30:34.56,1:30:37.36,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,There has only ever been one thing called a mortgage loan\N抵押贷款只有一种东西。
Dialogue: 0,1:30:37.36,1:30:38.05,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,right\N正确的
Dialogue: 0,1:30:38.05,1:30:39.35,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Only when you take out a loan\N只有当你贷款时
Dialogue: 0,1:30:39.35,1:30:42.29,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Your certificate carries someone else's rights\N你的证书承载着他人的权利。
Dialogue: 0,1:30:42.29,1:30:46.18,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,This is called an easement, where there's something on the easement, you see.\N这叫做地役权，地役权范围内有东西，你看。
Dialogue: 0,1:30:46.18,1:30:48.47,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,In Xida, as mentioned earlier\N如前所述，在西达。
Dialogue: 0,1:30:48.47,1:30:49.80,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,HA stands for the homeowners association\NHA 代表业主协会。
Dialogue: 0,1:30:49.80,1:30:52.73,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,The homeowners' association checks if your grass has grown to 12 centimeters\N业主协会会检查你的草坪是否长到 12 厘米。
Dialogue: 0,1:30:52.73,1:30:53.73,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,as stipulated by the community\N根据社区的规定
Dialogue: 0,1:30:53.73,1:30:55.89,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,But the limit is ten centimeters, and it's exceeded by two centimeters\N但限度是十厘米，而这里超出了两厘米。
Dialogue: 0,1:30:55.89,1:30:57.09,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,step forward onto the ground for you\N向前一步，走到地面上，为你而来。
Dialogue: 0,1:30:57.09,1:31:01.93,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Take note if you've painted the wrong color.\N注意不要涂错颜色。
Dialogue: 0,1:31:01.93,1:31:04.47,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Note down whether it has been pre-registered\N记下是否已预先注册。
Dialogue: 0,1:31:04.47,1:31:05.22,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,before you lift it\N在你举起它之前
Dialogue: 0,1:31:05.22,1:31:07.81,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,you cannot transfer it\N你不能转让它
Dialogue: 0,1:31:07.81,1:31:10.61,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,may even accumulate over time\N甚至可能随着时间的推移而积累
Dialogue: 0,1:31:10.61,1:31:11.38,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,may involve fines\N可能涉及罚款。
Dialogue: 0,1:31:11.38,1:31:12.21,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,involves auction\N涉及拍卖
Dialogue: 0,1:31:12.21,1:31:14.17,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Not only is this about the insurance\N这不仅仅关乎保险。
Dialogue: 0,1:31:14.17,1:31:15.59,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,You don't have insurance\N你没有保险
Dialogue: 0,1:31:15.59,1:31:18.29,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,You still want to pay property taxes for that\N你仍然想为此缴纳房产税。
Dialogue: 0,1:31:18.29,1:31:19.50,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,What else do you want\N你还想要什么？
Dialogue: 0,1:31:19.50,1:31:21.76,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Is it possible for him to be registered at the upper level of power?\N他有可能被列入权力高层吗？
Dialogue: 0,1:31:21.76,1:31:22.81,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,In the West\N在西方
Dialogue: 0,1:31:22.81,1:31:24.14,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Why do people dislike buying houses\N为什么人们不喜欢买房
Dialogue: 0,1:31:24.14,1:31:25.69,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,just because you bought a house\N仅仅因为你买了一套房子
Dialogue: 0,1:31:25.69,1:31:27.14,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,you're the sucker\N你才是傻瓜
Dialogue: 0,1:31:27.14,1:31:29.36,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Everyone can take a cut from you\N每个人都可以从你身上分一杯羹。
Dialogue: 0,1:31:29.36,1:31:31.15,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Yes\N是的
Dialogue: 0,1:31:32.30,1:31:36.03,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Ah, and even more commonly, including many historically accumulated issues\N啊，更常见的情况是，还包括许多历史遗留问题。
Dialogue: 0,1:31:36.03,1:31:39.25,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,A resident behind me has an easement right\N我身后的一位居民拥有地役权
Dialogue: 0,1:31:39.25,1:31:41.68,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,can pass through the road from my property\N可以从我的房产穿过这条路
Dialogue: 0,1:31:41.68,1:31:43.48,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,I want to repair my road\N我想修路
Dialogue: 0,1:31:43.48,1:31:44.97,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,must leave enough width for him\N必须给他留出足够的空间。
Dialogue: 0,1:31:44.97,1:31:45.48,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,enough what\N够了什么
Dialogue: 0,1:31:45.48,1:31:46.36,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,or else there will be another lawsuit\N否则将面临另一场诉讼。
Dialogue: 0,1:31:46.36,1:31:50.18,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Otherwise there will be some contact of mine with this piece of land\N否则，我将与这块土地产生某种联系。
Dialogue: 0,1:31:50.18,1:31:51.69,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,On one hand, there is a water\N一方面，有水
Dialogue: 0,1:31:51.69,1:31:53.47,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Me a slope cannot exceed a certain limit\N坡度不能超过一定限度
Dialogue: 0,1:31:53.47,1:31:55.97,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Otherwise, if I am upstream\N否则，如果我在上游。
Dialogue: 0,1:31:55.97,1:31:57.73,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,I will tilt toward my neighbor's downstream\N我会向下游邻居的方向倾斜。
Dialogue: 0,1:31:57.73,1:31:59.46,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,What is the water causing it to accumulate?\N是什么水导致它积聚？
Dialogue: 0,1:31:59.46,1:32:00.93,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,It's another water-related product\N这是另一种与水有关的产品。
Dialogue: 0,1:32:00.93,1:32:03.03,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,You buy a piece of land\N你买了一块地
Dialogue: 0,1:32:03.03,1:32:05.07,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,There are many items in the subsequent property rights content\N后续产权内容中包含许多项目。
Dialogue: 0,1:32:05.07,1:32:06.96,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,and even includes hydrographic charts\N甚至还包括水文图表
Dialogue: 0,1:32:06.96,1:32:07.38,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Why\N为什么
Dialogue: 0,1:32:07.38,1:32:09.02,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,because I've done it\N因为我已经做到了。
Dialogue: 0,1:32:11.31,1:32:13.73,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,You and you, you open your property deed\N你，还有你，你打开你的房产证
Dialogue: 0,1:32:13.73,1:32:16.15,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Damn clean\N干净得一尘不染
Dialogue: 0,1:32:24.64,1:32:29.00,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Sometimes it increases painful consumption\N有时它会增加痛苦的消费
Dialogue: 0,1:32:29.00,1:32:34.94,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,It's about many of your essential or quasi-essential items\N它关系到你许多必需品或准必需品。
Dialogue: 0,1:32:34.94,1:32:36.55,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,pull off this kind of thing\N搞定这种事
Dialogue: 0,1:32:36.55,1:32:39.68,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,He forces you to spend money\N他强迫你花钱。
Dialogue: 0,1:32:39.68,1:32:43.17,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,And this money makes you spend it in a particularly painful way\N而这笔钱会让你以一种特别痛苦的方式花掉它。
Dialogue: 0,1:32:44.05,1:32:46.97,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,To put it bluntly, even if you spend less, it's still not enough\N坦白地说，即使你少花钱，也还是不够。
Dialogue: 0,1:32:46.97,1:32:49.48,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Spending less only slightly reduces your pain\N少花钱只能略微减轻你的痛苦
Dialogue: 0,1:32:49.48,1:32:50.59,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,but still painful\N但仍然很痛苦
Dialogue: 0,1:32:50.59,1:32:53.03,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,You can only avoid the pain by spending a lot of money\N只有花很多钱才能避免痛苦。
Dialogue: 0,1:32:53.03,1:32:55.64,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,And this relief from pain only lasts for a short while\N而且这种疼痛缓解只能持续很短的时间。
Dialogue: 0,1:32:57.88,1:32:59.22,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Ah\N啊
Dialogue: 0,1:33:05.69,1:33:08.50,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,You might say this is creating a false sense of necessity, right?\N你可能会说，这制造了一种虚假的必要性，对吧？
Dialogue: 0,1:33:08.50,1:33:11.50,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Right, creating rigid demand, mhm\N没错，人为制造僵化需求，嗯。
Dialogue: 0,1:33:12.61,1:33:13.93,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Fiercely creating rigid demand\N猛烈制造僵化需求
Dialogue: 0,1:33:13.93,1:33:15.68,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,The GDP is skyrocketing\N国内生产总值正在飙升
Dialogue: 0,1:33:15.68,1:33:17.84,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Oh my god\N我的天啊
Dialogue: 0,1:33:22.27,1:33:26.77,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,And also, with this home insurance\N而且，还有这份房屋保险
Dialogue: 0,1:33:26.77,1:33:28.85,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,What exactly does it cover?\N它具体涵盖哪些内容？
Dialogue: 0,1:33:29.02,1:33:31.30,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,My house is hit by an earthquake\N我的房子被地震袭击了。
Dialogue: 0,1:33:31.30,1:33:32.72,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,caught fire\N着火了
Dialogue: 0,1:33:32.72,1:33:33.57,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,flooded\N被淹
Dialogue: 0,1:33:33.57,1:33:35.17,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,He can compensate me.\N他可以补偿我。
Dialogue: 0,1:33:35.17,1:33:39.44,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Hey, does everyone still remember the Los Angeles wildfire?\N嘿，大家还记得洛杉矶山火吗？
Dialogue: 0,1:33:40.22,1:33:43.01,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,You bought home insurance, right?\N你买了房屋保险，对吧？
Dialogue: 0,1:33:43.01,1:33:49.81,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,I secretly canceled your insurance just a few days before the wildfire came.\N就在山火来临前几天，我偷偷取消了你的保险。
Dialogue: 0,1:33:49.81,1:33:52.88,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,You can't not buy Me insurance\N你不能不给我买保险
Dialogue: 0,1:33:52.88,1:33:55.93,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,but I can cancel at any time\N但我可以随时取消。
Dialogue: 0,1:33:56.53,1:33:57.38,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Got it\N知道了
Dialogue: 0,1:33:57.38,1:34:01.30,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,That's exactly why I say it's a painful consumption.\N正因如此，我才说这是一种痛苦的消费。
Dialogue: 0,1:34:01.30,1:34:02.26,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,that you have to buy\N你必须购买
Dialogue: 0,1:34:02.26,1:34:04.53,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,but in reality, it's practically useless\N但实际上，它几乎毫无用处。
Dialogue: 0,1:34:06.52,1:34:09.00,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Well, they're just doing business, right?\N他们只是在做生意而已，对吧？
Dialogue: 0,1:34:09.00,1:34:11.06,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,They first went to the California court\N他们首先去了加利福尼亚州法院。
Dialogue: 0,1:34:11.06,1:34:13.82,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,that legislation over there, right\N那边的立法，对吧？
Dialogue: 0,1:34:13.82,1:34:20.43,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,In a certain year's legislation, a clause was added called the 'at, uh, policy'\N在某一年的立法中，增加了一项名为“at, uh, policy”的条款。
Dialogue: 0,1:34:20.43,1:34:22.09,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,What is an as well policy\N什么是良好政策
Dialogue: 0,1:34:22.09,1:34:25.02,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,that is fair and reasonable for both parties\N对双方而言都是公平合理的
Dialogue: 0,1:34:25.02,1:34:28.61,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,It can be terminated if it's reasonable, right?\N如果理由合理，就可以终止合同，对吧？
Dialogue: 0,1:34:28.61,1:34:30.35,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,You pay for one day at a time\N你按天付费
Dialogue: 0,1:34:30.35,1:34:32.80,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,I provide insurance coverage day by day, right?\N我每天都在提供保险保障，对吧？
Dialogue: 0,1:34:32.80,1:34:36.07,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,We are fair, reasonable, and equal parties, alas.\N可惜，我们都是公平、理性、平等的各方。
Dialogue: 0,1:34:36.07,1:34:36.73,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Well then\N那好吧
Dialogue: 0,1:34:36.73,1:34:37.80,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Now it's June\N现在是六月
Dialogue: 0,1:34:37.80,1:34:39.80,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,July is just around the corner\N七月即将到来
Dialogue: 0,1:34:39.80,1:34:42.72,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,After a series of complex calculations by my insurance company\N经过我的保险公司一系列复杂的计算后
Dialogue: 0,1:34:42.72,1:34:44.68,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Microstar aquitard groundwater layer calculation\NMicrostar 隔水层地下水层计算
Dialogue: 0,1:34:44.68,1:34:47.60,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,I think the probability of a risk occurring in July\N我认为七月份发生风险的概率很高。
Dialogue: 0,1:34:47.60,1:34:49.60,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,may exceed the rate I charge\N可能超过我收取的费用。
Dialogue: 0,1:34:49.60,1:34:51.35,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,But then I did the calculations again\N但我后来又重新计算了一遍。
Dialogue: 0,1:34:51.35,1:34:53.65,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,I realized that if I increase the premium further\N我意识到，如果我进一步提高保费……
Dialogue: 0,1:34:53.65,1:34:55.11,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,may trigger adverse selection\N可能引发逆向选择
Dialogue: 0,1:34:55.11,1:34:57.27,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,A lot of people would come to me to cancel their insurance, right?\N很多人都会来找我取消他们的保险，对吧？
Dialogue: 0,1:34:57.27,1:35:00.06,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Then what I'm doing is not increasing this rate\N那么我所做的，并不是提高这个比率。
Dialogue: 0,1:35:00.06,1:35:02.31,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Because I know that increasing it would be thankless and unappreciated\N因为我知道增加它既得不到感激，也不会有人领情。
Dialogue: 0,1:35:02.31,1:35:05.33,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,I also couldn't collect that money, right?\N我也没能收到那笔钱，对吧？
Dialogue: 0,1:35:05.33,1:35:06.45,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,and it also ruins my reputation\N而且这还会损害我的名誉。
Dialogue: 0,1:35:06.45,1:35:07.43,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Then I'll just give it to you\N那我就直接给你吧
Dialogue: 0,1:35:07.43,1:35:08.68,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,I'll just cut it off\N我把它剪掉就行了。
Dialogue: 0,1:35:08.68,1:35:09.93,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Sigh, it's written in the law\N唉，法律上是这么规定的。
Dialogue: 0,1:35:09.93,1:35:10.32,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,I can\N我可以
Dialogue: 0,1:35:10.32,1:35:13.11,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,You and I are fair and reasonable parties, right?\N你我都是公平合理的当事人，对吧？
Dialogue: 0,1:35:13.11,1:35:14.07,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,You pay to get on the bus\N你需要付费才能上车。
Dialogue: 0,1:35:14.07,1:35:14.92,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,I'm not charging for this\N我不会为此收费。
Dialogue: 0,1:35:14.92,1:35:16.42,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Of course I can ask you to get off the car.\N我当然可以要求你下车。
Dialogue: 0,1:35:16.42,1:35:19.85,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,We are fair and reasonable.\N我们公平合理。
Dialogue: 0,1:35:19.85,1:35:22.71,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Ah, everyone, think about it\N啊，各位，好好想想。
Dialogue: 0,1:35:23.59,1:35:28.01,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,So, in plain terms, does this home insurance actually work or not?\N那么，简单来说，这种房屋保险到底有没有用呢？
Dialogue: 0,1:35:28.01,1:35:31.33,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,he said it's a high-risk period means it's a high-risk period\N他说这是高风险时期，意思就是这是高风险时期。
Dialogue: 0,1:35:31.33,1:35:35.44,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,The definition of the risk period is not in your hands\N风险期的定义并非由您决定。
Dialogue: 0,1:35:35.44,1:35:38.03,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,even though you're the one who bought the insurance\N即使是你自己购买的保险。
Dialogue: 0,1:35:38.03,1:35:40.60,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,The insurance company says it's now a high-risk period.\N保险公司表示，现在是高风险时期。
Dialogue: 0,1:35:40.60,1:35:42.68,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,they can cut off your coverage at any time\N他们可以随时终止你的保险。
Dialogue: 0,1:35:44.01,1:35:45.37,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Got it\N知道了
Dialogue: 0,1:35:46.56,1:35:47.43,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Some say it's a gamble\N有人说这是赌博。
Dialogue: 0,1:35:47.43,1:35:48.27,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,This is not a bet\N这不是打赌
Dialogue: 0,1:35:48.27,1:35:49.65,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,This is a one-sided breach of agreement\N这是单方面违反协议的行为。
Dialogue: 0,1:35:49.65,1:35:52.53,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Bro, this is no bet at all.\N兄弟，这根本不是打赌。
Dialogue: 0,1:35:52.53,1:35:53.92,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Of course it's a bet\N当然，这是一场赌博。
Dialogue: 0,1:35:53.92,1:35:56.10,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,You can also choose not to report at any time\N您也可以随时选择不举报。
Dialogue: 0,1:35:56.10,1:35:59.01,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,I can also opt out at any time, right?\N我也可以随时选择退出，对吗？
Dialogue: 0,1:35:59.01,1:36:01.02,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,but as the property owner\N但作为业主
Dialogue: 0,1:36:01.02,1:36:02.68,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,You are legally required\N您依法必须
Dialogue: 0,1:36:02.68,1:36:05.28,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,You must have these items like water insurance and fire insurance.\N您必须购买水险和火灾险等保险。
Dialogue: 0,1:36:05.28,1:36:06.05,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,no matter who you choose\N无论你选择谁
Dialogue: 0,1:36:06.05,1:36:07.09,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,You have to find PICC\N你需要找到 PICC 导管。
Dialogue: 0,1:36:07.09,1:36:07.68,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,right?\N正确的？
Dialogue: 0,1:36:07.68,1:36:08.51,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Of course\N当然
Dialogue: 0,1:36:08.51,1:36:09.40,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Here\N这里
Dialogue: 0,1:36:09.40,1:36:11.05,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,There are only three insurance companies in total\N总共只有三家保险公司。
Dialogue: 0,1:36:11.05,1:36:13.05,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Both are controlled by the same shareholder\N两者均由同一股东控制。
Dialogue: 0,1:36:13.05,1:36:14.01,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Don't ask, okay\N别问了，好吗？
Dialogue: 0,1:36:14.01,1:36:16.00,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,They'll just say it's the free market at work\N他们只会说这是自由市场运作的结果。
Dialogue: 0,1:36:16.00,1:36:18.00,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,There are actually only two options\N实际上只有两种选择
Dialogue: 0,1:36:18.00,1:36:20.23,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Take it or leave it\N接受或拒绝
Dialogue: 0,1:36:21.84,1:36:24.60,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,As for why the one from the neighboring county can't come, you say\N至于为什么邻县的人来不了，你说……
Dialogue: 0,1:36:24.60,1:36:24.96,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,right\N正确的
Dialogue: 0,1:36:24.96,1:36:26.03,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Shall we present the legal provisions?\N我们是否应该列出相关法律条文？
Dialogue: 0,1:36:26.03,1:36:28.07,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,We can request that you consider our county, right\N我们可以请求您考虑一下我们县的情况，对吗？
Dialogue: 0,1:36:28.07,1:36:29.56,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,must have this insurance license\N必须持有此保险执照
Dialogue: 0,1:36:29.56,1:36:30.72,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,still requires 123\N仍然需要 123
Dialogue: 0,1:36:30.72,1:36:31.92,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,He doesn't have it\N他没有。
Dialogue: 0,1:36:31.92,1:36:32.84,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,How could he be allowed to sell it?\N他怎么能被允许出售它？
Dialogue: 0,1:36:32.84,1:36:35.38,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Don't forget the ultraviolet light box for jaundice we mentioned earlier.\N别忘了我们之前提到的用于治疗黄疸的紫外线灯箱。
Dialogue: 0,1:36:35.38,1:36:38.65,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Every Smith agent has to make money.\N每个史密斯经纪人都得赚钱。
Dialogue: 0,1:36:39.10,1:36:48.01,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Ah, so all I can say is, sigh, it's still too much\N唉，我只能说，唉，还是太多了。
Dialogue: 0,1:36:48.01,1:36:53.51,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,This group of people can really twist this law to their advantage.\N这群人真的能利用这条法律为自己谋利。
Dialogue: 0,1:36:53.51,1:36:54.53,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,That's really\N那真是
Dialogue: 0,1:37:01.52,1:37:06.72,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Really, huh, sigh\N真的吗，唉……
Dialogue: 0,1:37:08.92,1:37:16.06,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Just like this?\N就是这样吗？
Dialogue: 0,1:37:18.56,1:37:22.52,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Hahahaha hey\N哈哈哈哈，嘿
Dialogue: 0,1:37:27.96,1:37:28.52,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Really\N真的
Dialogue: 0,1:37:30.64,1:37:33.80,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Sometimes that kind of rhetoric from above can easily lead to trouble\N有时候，这种来自上层的言论很容易引发麻烦。
Dialogue: 0,1:37:33.96,1:37:35.42,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Sigh, rest assured cultural relics\N唉，放心吧，文化遗迹
Dialogue: 0,1:37:35.42,1:37:36.80,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,I can say this without fear\N我可以毫无畏惧地说出这句话。
Dialogue: 0,1:37:36.80,1:37:39.39,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,peanuts haven't been eaten even after recording an entire episode\N即使录制完一整集节目，花生也没吃。
Dialogue: 0,1:37:39.68,1:37:42.07,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Ah, I really am Chinese\N啊，我真是个中国人。
Dialogue: 0,1:37:42.07,1:37:44.38,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,I'm not afraid to eat this either\N我也不怕吃这个。
Dialogue: 0,1:37:44.93,1:37:47.11,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,This is the goodness of being Chinese that you've seen\N这就是你所看到的中国人的优点。
Dialogue: 0,1:37:47.11,1:37:49.26,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,You slam your Chinese passport on the table\N你把中国护照重重地摔在桌子上。
Dialogue: 0,1:37:49.26,1:37:51.89,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,He really takes you seriously\N他真的很认真对待你。
Dialogue: 0,1:37:52.85,1:37:56.61,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Hmm, you're saying how come it's only Route Level 1?\N嗯，你是说为什么只有 1 级路线？
Dialogue: 0,1:37:57.27,1:37:59.60,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Don't you understand Victoria's selective breeding of races?\N你难道不了解维多利亚州对不同种族进行的选择性育种吗？
Dialogue: 0,1:38:00.68,1:38:04.67,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Ah, and why was he promoted to Route Level 1?\N啊，他为什么会被提升到 1 级路线？
Dialogue: 0,1:38:04.67,1:38:07.47,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Because he's not Anglo-Saxon.\N因为他不是盎格鲁-撒克逊人。
Dialogue: 0,1:38:08.35,1:38:12.88,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,The name Luigi is an Italian name.\N路易吉（Luigi）是一个意大利名字。
Dialogue: 0,1:38:13.84,1:38:16.31,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Right, the Anglo-Saxons just aren't cut out for it\N没错，盎格鲁-撒克逊人根本不适合做这件事。
Dialogue: 0,1:38:18.80,1:38:22.06,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,This brings us to the inherent flaws of the Anglo-Saxon people.\N这就引出了盎格鲁-撒克逊民族固有的缺陷。
Dialogue: 0,1:38:22.39,1:38:24.10,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Luigi is of Italian descent\N路易吉是意大利裔
Dialogue: 0,1:38:25.35,1:38:27.60,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,He is indeed not an Anglo-Saxon.\N他确实不是盎格鲁-撒克逊人。
Dialogue: 0,1:38:29.68,1:38:31.68,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,He had black hair and black eyes\N他有一头黑发和一双黑眼睛
Dialogue: 0,1:38:31.68,1:38:35.72,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,He is of Italian nationality.\N他是意大利国籍。
Dialogue: 0,1:38:36.65,1:38:39.57,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Pure Anglo-Saxons are still not quite up to par\N纯种盎格鲁-撒克逊人仍然不够格
Dialogue: 0,1:38:41.84,1:38:44.88,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Sigh, the Anglo-Saxons are just too tolerant.\N唉，盎格鲁-撒克逊人真是太宽容了。
Dialogue: 0,1:38:44.88,1:38:51.47,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,How about letting you Anglo-Saxons witness the old-school Roman way, huh?\N不如让你们盎格鲁-撒克逊人见识一下古老的罗马方式，怎么样？
Dialogue: 0,1:38:51.47,1:38:57.52,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Hahaha, yeah, when you think about it, it's still damn hard to take\N哈哈，是啊，仔细想想，还是很难接受。
Dialogue: 0,1:38:57.52,1:38:59.14,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Some say Americans don't know how to resist\N有人说美国人不懂得如何抵抗
Dialogue: 0,1:38:59.14,1:39:00.61,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,except with Luigi\N除了路易吉
Dialogue: 0,1:39:00.61,1:39:04.42,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Actually, Luigi isn't of Anglo-Saxon descent.\N事实上，路易吉并非盎格鲁-撒克逊人后裔。
Dialogue: 0,1:39:06.26,1:39:09.76,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Luigi really isn't, ah\N路易吉真的不是，啊
Dialogue: 0,1:39:13.06,1:39:14.92,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Sigh, sometimes dark hair and dark eyes\N唉，有时是黑发和黑眼睛
Dialogue: 0,1:39:14.92,1:39:17.38,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Is this in some sense an imitation of the Romans?\N这在某种意义上是对罗马人的模仿吗？
Dialogue: 0,1:39:17.38,1:39:19.68,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Right, hmm\N对，嗯。
Dialogue: 0,1:39:19.68,1:39:21.68,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Is it the Anglo-Saxons or are they just too tolerant\N是盎格鲁-撒克逊人的性格使然，还是他们过于宽容了？
Dialogue: 0,1:39:21.68,1:39:26.23,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Queen Victoria's selection is still so persuasive\N维多利亚女王的选择至今仍然如此具有说服力。
Dialogue: 0,1:39:26.23,1:39:28.14,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Brothers, hmm\N兄弟们，嗯。
Dialogue: 0,1:39:28.14,1:39:29.72,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Listen to me, kids, okay\N孩子们，听我说，好吗？
Dialogue: 0,1:39:29.72,1:39:33.60,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,This is Victoria's strict selection\N这是维多利亚的严格筛选标准。
Dialogue: 0,1:39:33.60,1:39:37.85,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Brothers, there's nothing to criticize.\N兄弟们，没什么可批评的。
Dialogue: 0,1:39:45.10,1:39:46.93,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Alright bro, let me check what time it is\N好的兄弟，我看看现在几点了。
Dialogue: 0,1:39:46.93,1:39:48.02,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,It's past nine o'clock.\N现在已经过了九点。
Dialogue: 0,1:39:48.02,1:39:50.69,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Alright guys, I'm calling it a night. Goodbye, everyone.\N好了各位，今天就到这里吧。再见，各位。
Dialogue: 0,1:39:50.69,1:39:52.57,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,I'm out too\N我也退出了。
Dialogue: 0,1:39:52.57,1:39:55.31,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Rest rest rest rest rest, um\N休息休息休息休息休息，嗯
Dialogue: 0,1:39:55.31,1:39:58.14,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Wait a second, let me take a screenshot of this\N等一下，让我截个图。
Dialogue: 0,1:39:58.94,1:40:03.43,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Take a screenshot\N截屏
Dialogue: 0,1:40:05.61,1:40:07.73,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Um, OK, I'm done for the day.\N嗯，好了，我今天就到这里了。
Dialogue: 0,1:40:07.73,1:40:09.19,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Good night, bros\N晚安，兄弟们。
Dialogue: 0,1:40:09.19,1:40:12.68,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Good night, good night, good night, bro\N晚安，晚安，晚安，兄弟。
Dialogue: 0,1:40:15.39,1:40:18.89,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Thank you Brother Sanna 4H for the 30 popularity tickets\N感谢 Sanna 4H 兄弟赠送的 30 张人气券。
Dialogue: 0,1:40:18.89,1:40:21.06,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Thank you to the brother JERRY for sending the popularity tickets\N感谢杰瑞兄弟寄来的人气门票。
Dialogue: 0,1:40:21.06,1:40:22.27,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Thank you, brothers\N谢谢各位兄弟。
Dialogue: 0,1:40:22.27,1:40:25.97,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Thank you thank you, good night good night bros\N谢谢谢谢，晚安晚安兄弟们
Dialogue: 0,1:40:25.97,1:40:27.57,BottomCenter,,0,0,0,,Thank you thank you thank you\N谢谢，谢谢，谢谢！